(1, 'AT-IND-03', 'CL-AT-IND-01', 'M31', 'Regulation on bans and restrictions of HFCs, PFCs, SF6', 'Substantial reduction of of emissions of gases with high GWP', 'In December 2002, the relevant Austrian Ordinance entered into force. It aims at reducing and phasing-out respectively the use of HFCs, PFCs and SF6 in all relevant applications on the basis of the Federal Chemicals Act. That measure has been the most important step of the Austrian government&rsquo;s strategy to mitigate or avoid future GHG emissions from fluorinated gases. Without the regulation, emissions were expected to grow by about 50% by 2010, mainly due to increased use of HFCs as a substituting substance for ozone layer depleting CFCs (e.g. for cooling or insulation materials). Applications affected by the reduction and phase-out plan are:<br />&bull; Insulation material (HFC)<br />&bull; Construction foams (HFC)<br />&bull; Refrigeration (HFC)<br />&bull; Stationary and mobile air conditioning (HFC)<br />&bull; Fire-fighting systems<br />&bull; SF6 in sound-absorbing windows<br />&bull; SF6 in tires<br />&bull; SF6 insulated switchgear installations and semi-conductors', '2002', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CL-AT-IND-01', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2, 'AT-IND-04', 'CL-AT-IND-01', 'M32', 'Public procurement and support measures', 'Substantial reduction of of emissions of gases with high GWP', 'In order to give incentives to the market for &ldquo;early phase-out&rdquo;, prior to full entry into force of the above-mentioned regulation, the Federation and the L&auml;nder are capable to refrain from the use of products equipped with fluorinated gases within public procurement guidelines, either for deliveries (e.g. cooling equipment) or construction services. Practicable options to that end are to be evaluated. Some provinces have also integrated or have the intention to integrate a ban of fluorinated gases in housing support schemes, meaning that applicants can only expect public financial support when they refrain from using construction products equipped with those gases. Given the dominant role of public housing support for new construction of dwellings, regional construction business is expected to quickly make use of available alternatives, also accelerating adaptation and price-cuttings on behalf of producers.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CL-AT-IND-01', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(3, 'AT-IND-05', NULL, 'M33', 'Avoidance of leakage', 'Substantial reduction of of emissions of gases with high GWP', 'The EU Regulation which will enter into force in mid-2006 aims at reducing emission by leakage control and inspections on a regular basis, especially in the sector of refrigeration and air conditioning, but also in other smaller sectors. This will help to reduce emissions from existing equipment, in addition to the national measures by chemicals legislation mentioned under AT-IND-03', '2006', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'not quantified', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(4, 'CL-AT-IND-01', 'CL-AT-IND-01', 'CL (M31, M32)', 'Cluster: Aggregated emission reduction effect of M31, M32', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1200', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(5, 'AT-ENC-02', 'CL-AT-ENC-01', 'M1', 'Minimum thermal standards for buildings', 'Reduce energy use for new buildings', 'Minimum thermal standards for buildings are defined in the Technical Construction Regulations of the states by way of U-values (=k-values) for different construction components,and / or certain energy demand codes for the whole building in line with the new Directive on energy performance of buildings. In most provinces it is a prerequisite fir reeceiving financial support through the housing support schemes taht energy indicators are better than the corresponding minimum standards of the Technical Construction Regulation.   Almost all states have improved U-values over the past years and in some cases have also gone well beyond minimum standards within the existing Agreement on Energy Saving of 1995 on the basis of Article 15a of the Federal Constitution Act between the federation and the nine provinces. In general, technical construction regulations apply only to newly constructed buildings (except, for example, change of windows). As long as no obligatory standards for renovation measures exist, thermal standards of the old building stock therefore need to be influenced mainly by other instruments, especially public support schemes for renovation.', '1995', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CL-AT-ENC-01', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'AT-Climate Strategy 2007, p.74', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(6, 'AT-ENC-03', 'CL-AT-ENC-01', 'M2', 'Housing support schemes - Constitutional Treaty between Federation and Laendern', 'Reduce energy use for existing and new buildings theorugh housing support schemes', 'Financial support for new construction and renovation of existing buildings is linked to energy performance. The Environment Minister entered into a constitution based treaty with the L&auml;nder aiming at optimising the use of subsidies for housing schemes by introducing minimum standards with respect to energy profiles. This type of treaty is legally binding and needs to be implemented in legal terms by the Parties until January 2007. The agreement provides for: &bull; shift of subsidies from construction of new dwelling to thermal renovation of existing dwellings; &bull; high quality standards for thermal renovation, including the whole building shell (exterior walls, windows and doors, ceilings and roof); &bull; maximum energy performance codes for newly constructed buildings that go well beyond standards that are foreseen in general construction codes; &bull; replacement of old fossil fuel heating systems by highly efficient systems based on renewable energy (solar or biomass) or natural gas. A common reporting format, including performance indictors, will provide for monitoring in terms of CO2 emissions reductions and associated costs.', '2005', '2008', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CL-AT-ENC-01', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'AT-Climate Strategy 2007, p.74', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(7, 'AT-ENC-06', 'CL-AT-ENC-01', 'M3', 'Third Party Financing (&quot;Contracting&quot;) for public buildings', 'Energy-savings in public and private sector buildings', 'The federal government decided in March 2001 to launch a Programme on Third Party Financing (Contracting) in the field of energy-saving investments for federal public buildings.  About 300 properties were selected for the project with about 500 suitable buildings for EPC. After two years for nearly 400 buildings suitable energy saving contractors have already been found. Average savings of 20% of the annual energy costs are guaranteed for these buildings within the contract period (ten years). Public high schools are currently mostly affected by the programme. The federal government will be able to save about 1.4 million &euro; in energy costs annually during the 10-year contract. After the end of the contract duration the federal government then enjoys the benefits of the entire energy savings (approx. 6.9 Mio. &euro;/year). Through the contracting offensive, 10 % of the CO2 emissions will be saved among all BIG owned buildings. Through ongoing general renovations of additional federal buildings, another 7% of the CO2 emissions can be reduced. Therefore the initiative is expected to result in a total reduction of CO2 emissions by 70-100.000 t p.a. by 2012.', '2001', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CL-AT-ENC-01', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'AT-Climate Strategy 2007, p.74', NULL, NULL, '463000', 'Costs for invitation to tender and project controlling', NULL, NULL),
(8, 'AT-ENC-08', 'CL-AT-ENC-01', 'M4', 'Improvement of technical building standards and energy codes for buildings', 'Transparent and comparable declaration of energy consumption of buildings', 'Technical agreement on a common scheme for an energy code for buildings.  Member States need to implement the laws, regulations and administrative provisions necessary to comply with the Directive of energy performance of buildings by 2006. The basic objective underlying this Directive is to promote the improvement of the energy performance of buildings within the EU, ensuring in so far as possible that only such measures as are the most cost-effective are undertaken.The preparations in Austria to bring the Directive into force are still under way and the implementation into national law will be finished during 2006.', '2006', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CL-AT-ENC-01', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'AT-Climate Strategy 2007, p.75', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(9, 'CL-AT-ENC-01', 'CL-AT-ENC-01', 'CL (M1,M2, M3, M4, E.1)', 'Cluster: Aggregated emission reduction effect of M2, M3, M4 (energy efficiency of buildings)', NULL, 'The emission reduction assumes an intensification of M2, M3 and M4', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1600', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'AT-Climate Strategy 2007, p.75', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(10, 'AT-ENC-09', 'CL-AT-ENC-01', 'E.1', 'Further increase of total energy efficiency of building stock and shift to renewable energy and efficient district heating', 'Increase of thermal reconstruction to at least 3% (2008-2012)', 'Incentives (housing subsidy), fiscal privilege, for credits contracting modells, establishment of reconstruction programmes etc.', '2007', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CL-AT-ENC-01', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'AT-Climate Strategy 2007, p.70/71', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(11, 'AT-ENC-501', NULL, 'M26', 'Promotion of energy efficiency and renewable energy projects in industry', 'Energy savings and increasing share of renewables in industry', 'Energy-saving measures and the use of renewable energy sources in industry gain public support under the scheme of the Federal Environment Fund. About 250 industrial projects with climate change mitigating effects were supported between 2000 and 2003, resulting in CO2 mitigation effect of 645 000 tons annually. Specific attention was given to biomass boilers and cogeneration (bio fuels or natural gas), thermal solar energy and district heating from industrial boilers.<br />Implemented through Vereinbarung zwischen dem Bund und den L&auml;ndern gem&auml;&szlig; Art. 15a B-VG &uuml;ber die Einsparung von Energie, BGBl. Nr. 388/1995', '1996', NULL, NULL, NULL, '1100', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'AT-Climate Strategy 2007, p.80', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(12, 'AT-ENS-02', NULL, 'M6', 'Public support for renewable energy projects and district heating', 'Raising share of heat production from renewable energy sources and CHP', 'Climate change response measures in the field of renewable energy and energy efficiency have been supported through federal funding schemes with a total amount of 163.5 million &euro; between 2002 and 2005. The Federal Environment Fund is enabled to fund environment projects with a total budget frame of 69.2 million &euro; in 2005. In 2005, 81% of the funding sum was dedicated to domestic projects with direct implications on GHG emissions, and that share will even be extended. Over the past years, funding focused on biomass and biogas district heating, entrepreneurial biomass central heating systems, solar panels and energy efficiency measures, small hydro and wind power stations and thermal renovation of entrepreneurial buildings.; Rural funding schemes for energy from biomass: The Ministry for Agriculture, the L&auml;nder and the EU also provide funding for rural biomass energy projects. Total public funding for those projects, like district heating from wood chippings, biogas CHP or individual biomass heating systems in average amounted to roughly 14 million &euro; annually over the past years, involving total investment costs of 39 million &euro;. In 2004 and 2005 alone, electricity capacity of biogas plants could be increased by more than 400%. At present a total capacity of 71 MWel have been approved and has to be build up until the end of 2007.', '1997', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '40875000', '40,875 million/a federal funding schemes between 2002 -2005', NULL, NULL),
(13, 'AT-ENS-11', NULL, 'E6', 'Implementation of cogeneration directive', 'Increase the share of cogeneration', 'Establishement of good framework and financing conditions for cogeneration plants. Use of heat for cooling. Identification and use of waste heat.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'AT-Climate Strategy 2007, p.78f', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(14, 'AT-ENS-05', NULL, 'M7', 'Further development of targets for renewable energy sources and implementation of the EU directive on renewables', 'Raising the share of renewable energy sources in electricity supply. Austria has to set an indicative national target equivalent to an increase of the share of electricity from renewable energy sources from 70% in 1997 to 78.1% in 2010. The figures include large hydro as well as a broader definition of the term &lsquo;biomass&rsquo; and are, therefore, not directly comparable with &lsquo;new renewables&rsquo; targets from the Electricity Act.', 'The indicative target would be equivalent to additional 19&ndash;20 TWh electricity from renewable energy sources by 2010 compared to around 39 TWh supplied by all renewables in 1997. An amendment to the Green Electricity Act has been adopted by Parliament in 2006 (BGBl. I No. 105/2006). According to the adopted legislation, the share of &ldquo;new&rdquo; renewable energy sources for electricity production (wind, biomass, PV, geothermal) has to reach 10% of total production in 2010. In addition, a new investment funding scheme is planned for medium sized hydropower plants (10-20 MW) and highly efficient fossil fuel CHP plants. However, the targets will only be in reach when supplementary efforts will be made to slow down the growth in electricity demand.', '2003', NULL, NULL, NULL, '1700', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'AT-Climate Strategy 2007, p.79f', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(15, 'AT-ENS-10', NULL, 'M5', 'Promotion for electricity from renewable energy sources', 'Raising share of electricity production from renewables', 'The Green Electricity Act entered into effect on 1 January 2003 and is aimed at:<br />&bull; A single federal support payment scheme for &ldquo;other&rdquo; green power, small hydro and combined heat and power (CHP) was introduced; <br />&bull; A uniform feed-in tariff scheme was introduced for all eligible renewable energy sources;<br />&bull; The minimum target contribution from small hydro in 2008 was raised from 8 % to 9 % of total supply;<br />&bull; The minimum target contribution from &ldquo;other&rdquo; green power in 2008 was set at 4 %;<br />&bull; Increasing the share of &ldquo;green&rdquo; power from 70% (status in 1997) to the indicative target of 78.1% in 2010 in accordance with Directive 2001/77/EC;<br />&bull; The targets for &ldquo;other&rdquo; green power and small hydro relate to Austria as a whole;<br />&bull; Uniform feed-in tariffs and surcharges (support contributions) were introduced for the whole of Austria. Under this support system the control area managers have a take or pay obligation in their role as &ldquo;green&rdquo; power balancing group representatives. They must allocate &ldquo;green&rdquo; power to the electricity traders in proportion to the latter&rsquo;s annual sales volume. This order applies to all new plant licensed up to the end 2004 and built up to June 2006, as well as existing small hydro plants. Biomass-plants and hydropower-plants have to build up until the end of 2007. The entry into force of the Green Electricity Act led to a substantial expansion of green electricity generating capacity as a whole. In absolute terms the greatest increase between the first half of 2003 and the same period of 2005 was in wind power capacity (from 131 GWh to 711 GWh). Small hydro makes the largest contribution to power supplies, at 4,000 GWh per year. According to E-Control forecasts, the 4 % target for &ldquo;other&rdquo; green power (wind, biomass, etc.) by 2008 will be reached already in 2005. Implemented through Bundesgesetz, mit dem Neuregelungen auf dem Gebiet der Elektrizit&auml;tserzeugung aus erneuerbaren Energietr&auml;gern und auf dem Gebiet der Kraft-W&auml;rme-Kopplung erlassen werden (&Ouml;kostromgesetz), BGBl. I Nr. 149/2002 and for cogernation: Bundesgesetz, mit dem das Elektrizit&auml;tswirtschafts- und &ndash;organisationsgesetz, das Gaswirtschaftsgesetz, das Energielenkungsgesetz 1982, das Erd&ouml;l-Bevorratungs- und Meldegesetz 1982, das Energie-Regulierungsbeh&ouml;rdengesetz, das Bundesgesetz gegen den unlauteren Wettbewerb 1984 und das Wettbewerbsgesetz ge&auml;ndert werden (Energie-Versorgungssicherheitsgesetz 2006), BGBl. I Nr. 106/2006.', '2003', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'AT- Climate Strategy 2007, p.78', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(16, 'AT-ENC-91', NULL, 'M8', 'Energy Efficiency Programme (Implementation of Energy Efficiency Directive)', 'Reduction of energy intensity of at least 5% up to 2010 and 20% up to 2020', 'At EU level, the Council and the Parliament decided on a directive on energy efficiency and energy services by March 2006. The main target of the directive is to decrease energy end use intensity by 9 percent over a period of 9 years. The directive needs to be legally implemented by Member States until spring 2007. As a first step, Member Sates are obliged to elaborate energy efficiency action plans which need to be reported to the European Commission by 30 June 2007. Due to Austria&rsquo;s Draft Climate Strategy II, efforts are in a planning stage to considerably decrease energy end use intensity in the households, services and industry sectors with a view to meeting an indicative target of 2% annually. According to the new climate strategy 2007 the reduction in electricity demand in the mentioned sectors could result in a cut of CO2 emissions by approximately 0.8 million tons annually.', '2007', NULL, NULL, NULL, '800', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'AT- Climate Strategy 2007, p.77', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(17, 'AT-ENC-10', NULL, 'E.3', 'Inclusion of energy efficiency aspects in land use planning', 'Increase energy efficiency', 'Incentives within the framework of housing subsidies. Consideration of waste heat potentials from industry in land use planning. Control of legal, technical and economic conditions for feeding biogas into natural gas grid.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'not quantified', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'AT- Climate Strategy 2007, p.76', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(18, 'AT-WAM-01', NULL, 'M9', 'Waste Management Act 1990', 'Framework law regulating waste management &ndash; minimisation of environmental impacts', 'At the national level the Federal Waste Management Act (Abfallwirtschaftsgesetz) determines the objectives and principles of waste management in Austria, in general. The Overall Targets of the Waste Management Act include: Preservation of energy and other resources; Minimisation of landfill volume; Final disposal of waste only when guaranteed, that following generations will not be endangered. Austrian waste management policy follows as leading principles:<br />1. Prevention of waste;<br />2. Waste recovery (recycling or incineration with energy recovery);<br />3. Controlled disposal of waste, which cannot be further utilised (after biological, thermal or chemical-physical treatment).', '1990', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'not quantified', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(19, 'AT-WAM-02', NULL, 'M10', 'Landfill Regulation 1996', 'Minimisation of CH4 emissions from waste landfilling', 'The Landfill Regulation sets very strict limits in respect of Total Organic Carbon (TOC) disposed on landfills. TOC may not exceed 5 Vol.%. As a consequence, e.g., no residual waste (from households and comparable fractions from business) may be disposed of, without prior treatment (mechanical, biological, physical). Landfill management (private and municipal) have to comply fully with the high standards of the landfill regulation since 2004 (in certain circumstances 2008), effectively banning deposition of untreated residual waste since 2004. This implied an extension of waste treatment capacities other than landfilling. In 1996, 33.5% of residual waste was combusted in incineration plants. In the expected scenario for 2010, 50% of residual waste will be incinerated, and the other 50% will be subject to mechanical-biological treatment. In an enforced scenario, the share of waste incineration is likely to reach a dimension of 60%, with beneficial impacts on GHG mitigation when electricity and heat are produced by efficient cogeneration.<br />Implemented through Verordnung des Bundesministers f&uuml;r Umwelt &uuml;ber die Ablagerung von Abf&auml;llen (Deponieverordnung), BGBl. Nr 164/1996, i.d.F. BGBl. II Nr. 49/2004', '2004', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'not quantified (in earlier puplications: 900)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(20, 'AT-WAM-03', NULL, 'M11', 'Landfill Charge Act 1989', 'Reduction of disposal of waste on landfills; earmarking of revenue for clean-up of contaminated land', 'Leading principles:<br />1. Disposal of waste on landfills (domestic or abroad) is subject to a charge 2. Rate of charge depends on type of waste 3. Charge raised step by step until 2006 4. Supplemental charges for disposal on landfills without gas recovery 5. Revenue of charge earmarked for clean-up of contaminated land. The charge for residual waste is 87 &euro; per tonne. A supplemental charge of &euro; 29 applies when the landfill is not equipped with a landfill seal, and another &euro; 29 for landfills without landfill gas recovery of current technical standard.On &ldquo;worst case&ldquo; landfills, which rarely exist<br />anymore, the charge can, therefore, total up to 145 &euro; per tonne. The charge for residual waste is lowered to 26 &euro; per tonne for landfills meeting the state of the art according to the Landfill Regulation 1996. The high costs of full compliance with the Landfill Regulation in combination with the landfill charge will implicitly benefit waste recovery (recycling or incineration with energy recovery).', '2001', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'not quantified', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(21, 'AT-WAM-06', NULL, 'M12', 'Efficient energy recovery from waste', 'energy recovery from waste incineration (CHP)', 'On the basis of the Environmental Subsidy Act a subsidy was introduced for incineration plants with an energy efficiency rate of at least 65%. District heating grids should be extended in parallel and in conjunction with space planning measures.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'not quantified', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(22, 'AT-WAM-07', NULL, 'M13', 'Other programmes to launch waste prevention and recovery', 'prevention and recovery of of waste; higher share of energy recovery / recycling', 'The Federal Ministry of Agriculture and Forestry, Environment and Water Management has established working groups composed of representatives of the economic, scientific and administrative sectors to develop prevention and recovery concepts for specific sectors of the industry. Other programmes: PREPARE programmes examine and actively implement waste minimisation in selected companies, covering as many industrial sectors as possible.&Ouml;KOPROFIT programmes compile empirical information on integrated environmental protection within a given region, e.g. an urban area, by covering a sufficient number (around 30) of small and medium-sized companies. PREGAS is a project for the reduction of hazardous waste in Styria &bull; Ecological management consulting is offered in several L&auml;nder of Austria. &bull; NUS (Lower Austrian Environmental System) supports and subsidises environmental efforts of Lower Austrian enterprises, institutions and municipalities.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'not quantified', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(23, 'AT-WAM-08', NULL, 'M14', 'Define technical state of art for mechanical-biological treatment of waste', 'Better investment security for operators of waste treatment sites with respect to technical standards', 'A legally binding definition of technical state of art, as referred to in legal acts, is under preparation.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'not quantified', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(24, 'AT-TRA-01', NULL, 'M15', 'CO2 labelling and other measures to reduce emissions from passenger cars', 'Raising market share of advanced engine technlogiers with low fuel consumption', 'Federal law has implemented EU directive 1999/94/EC on compulsory labelling for new passenger car&rsquo;s fuel consumption and per kilometre CO2 emissions by February 2001. The labelling scheme is one element of an EU strategy to bring down average CO2 emissions from new passenger cars to 120 g/km (corresponding to an average fuel consumption of about 5 litres/100 km for petrol engines and 4.5 litres/100 km for diesel engines) by 2010 at the latest. In 2004, the average level of CO2 emissions from newly registered cars in Austria was 168 g/km for petrol engines and 159 g/km for diesel engines. The most important step towards that ambitious target was the conclusion of agreements between the EC and ACEA, JAMA and KAMA, covering more than 95% of the European market for passenger cars. According to these agreements, average CO2 emissions from newly registered cars will not be higher than 140 g/km by the year 2008. For reaching that target in Austria, a reduction of about 3% per year of the average CO2 emissions is necessary. That still leaves a gap of 20 g/km, which has to be bridged by supplementary measures.<br />Implemented through Bundesgesetz &uuml;ber die Bereitstellung von Verbraucherinformationen beim Marketing f&uuml;r neue Personenkraftwagen (Personenkraftwagen-Verbraucherinformationsgesetz &ndash; Pkw-VIG), BGBl. I Nr. 26/2001 i.d.F. BGBl. I Nr. 34/2006', '2001', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'not quantified (previous submissions 500)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(25, 'AT-TRA-02', NULL, 'M16', 'Fuel consumption based taxation', 'Fiscal incentive for low fuel consumption vehicles', 'Passenger car registration tax in Austria is based on standard fuel consumption, giving a clear incentive to buy energy efficient cars. The highest tax rate is 16% for cars exceeding a certain standard fuel consumption (petrol engines: 11 litres; diesel engines: 10 litres). Extremely efficient cars (less than two litres diesel or three litres petrol) are exempted from the tax. Tax base is the net price of the car. The registration tax is part of the tax base of VAT. Furthermore annual current taxes on passenger cars and motor bicycles have been increased in 2000 by about 50 %. Tax is based on motor power and therefore indirectly on fuel consumption, as there is a clear increase of fuel consumption with increasing power.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(26, 'AT-TRA-05', NULL, 'M19', 'Support of combined transport', 'Shift from road-only freight transport to combined transport road/rail/ship', 'In the framework of Austrian transport policy, combined transport is considered to be of central importance for solving present and future problems with regard to freight transport. In the time-period between the years 1983 and 2004 a total of about 8.5 Mio. loading units have been transported in accompanied and unaccompanied transport in Austria. In the year 2005 199.418 trucks where transported on rolling roads in Austria. Additionally 773.787 loading units (11.862.809 tons) were transported in unaccompanied transport in 2005. Within the Programme for the promotion of combined goods transport road/rail/ship 2003&ndash;2008 approximately 3 million &euro; per year are provided to support investments in installations, systems and equipment for combined transport. The programme aims at improved co-operation between road, rail and shipping as well as optimised traffic flows. Support is provided up to a maximum of 30 % of the accountable  investment costs for physical investments and up to a maximum of 50 % of the accountable costs for feasibility studies and training measures. <br />Emission reduction through improved freight traffic is calculated as 100 Gg/year. <br />Implemented through Bundesgesetz vom 30.April 2004 zur &Auml;nderung des Eisenbahngesetzes, BGBl.I Nr.38/2004 for the &ldquo;First Railway Package&ldquo;, &ldquo;Second Railway Package&ldquo; (partly) implemented by various acts and ordinances.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '100', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'AT-Climate Strategy 2007, p.93f', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(27, 'AT-TRA-07', 'CL-AT-TRA-01', 'M21', 'Model projects and programmes for environmentally sound mobility', 'Model projects with the aim to raise public awareness and to demonstrate new technologies', 'The Ministry of Environment initiated several pilot and model projects in the area of mobility management aiming at a reallocation of passenger transport from private cars towards public transport services, cycling and walking. In three different project categories, covering business (employees mobility behaviour), large events andtourism, it was possible to show that alternative mobility concepts find high acceptance when appropriate information (e.g. on schedules) is provided and services manage to adapt to the needs of people. In recent years (since NC3) these initiatives included the following model projects: The pilot project &ldquo;soft mobility &ndash; car free tourism&rdquo;, Alps Mobility II &ndash; &ldquo;Alpine Pearls&rdquo;, &bdquo;Alpine Awareness&ldquo;, MOBILALP, Pilot projects on sustainable transport and Tourism in Sensitive Areas on the Example of the Lake Neusiedl/Fert&ouml; t&oacute;-Region (2002-2007), Mobility management for business. Car sharing, Car pooling, bike and ride, park and ride etc.', '1998', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CL-AT-TRA-01', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'AT-Climate Strategy 2007, p.85ff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(28, 'AT-TRA-09', NULL, 'M17', 'Mileage based toll for lorries', 'Internalisation of external costs for road transport', 'Internalisation of external costs of road transport is one of the leading principles of Austrian transport policies. Accordingly, a non-discriminatory mileage based highway toll for lorries and trucks with a total weight of more than 3.5 tons was introduced on 1st January 2004. The former timely based &ldquo;vignette&rdquo;, which had to be purchased for highways use with vehicles, has been partly replaced by the electronic mileage-based system. Lorries with a total weight of more than 3.5 tons are now charged under the new system, whereas for passenger cars the &ldquo;vignette&rdquo;-system continues to apply.', '2004', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'not quantified (previous submissions 300)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(29, 'AT-TRA-10', NULL, 'M23', 'Promotion of energy efficient and alternative motor concepts', 'Reduction of fleet fuel consumption', 'New and alternative motor concepts, like electric vehicles, fuel cells, bio diesel, hydrogen and hybrid vehicles are being promoted by means of pilot programmes (e.g. in tourist areas and ecologically sensitive regions, towns and public service), strengthened emissions and fuel standards (in line with respective EU policies) and research and technological development programmes.<br />Negotiation for a new CO2 standard on EU level.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'not quantified ( previous submissions 100)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'AT-Climate Strategy 2007, p.82f', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(30, 'AT-TRA-11', 'CL-AT-TRA-01', 'M22', 'Public awareness raising measures', 'Influencing mobility behaviour of private and business drivers/demanders', 'Measures focused on raising public awareness with regard to climate-friendly modes of mobility. ECO-DRIVING Austria (&ldquo;Spritspar-Initiative&rdquo;): The Austrian Federal Ministry of<br />Agriculture, Forestry, Environment and Water Management, in co-operation with the Austrian Energy Agency and the Federal Branch Association of Driving Schools started aiming to accelerate the establishment of ECO-DRIVING in Austria. The European carfree day: A goal of this European initiative is it to sensitize the citizens for pollution free mobility to create awareness for transport problems and offer sustainable solutions. Walking, cycling and use of public transport is especially promoted on 22 September since the year 2000. In Austria the carfree day 2005 was one of the most successful public awareness campaigns regarding transport. With the slogan &quot;save fuel &ndash; go with bus and train!&quot; and a peak participation of 323 cities and municipalities altogether it shows that the increasing problem of road traffic in the municipalities causes people to check critically their own transport behaviour.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CL-AT-TRA-01', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'AT-Climate Strategy 2007, p.85ff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(31, 'CL-AT-TRA-01', 'CL-AT-TRA-01', 'M22, M21', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '300', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(32, 'AT-TRA-13', NULL, 'M25', 'Further internalisation of externalities of road transport', 'Internalisation of external costs of road transport/private traffic', 'The existing legal situation within the EU does not allow full reflection of environmental costs and other externalities in road duties. Austria is among those Member States arguing strongly in favour of internalisation of external costs, at least for &ldquo;sensitive regions&rdquo; like the Alps. That should also enable Member States to finance railway infrastructure across modes of  transport. Taxes and tolls on road use should, therefore, be modified in a way that better reflects impact on human health and environment. Fuel taxes in Austria were increased in 2004 in accordance with the Directive 2003/96/EC and should be further developed at EU level. Currently taxes on motor fuels still are relatively low compared to some neighbour states with the effect that a large share (approximately 25%) of motor fuel sold in Austria is used outside the country because of the existing price differences. The existing Car Registration Tax, which is designed as a sales tax, should also be further differentiated in the future. However, the federal government has not made a decision yet on an appropriate mix of fiscal measures to meet GHG reduction targets in the transport sector. Extension of fiscal instruments to promote environmentally friendly cars, fuel and mobility. Establishement of further incentives for the use of public transport.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1900', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'AT-Climate Strategy 2007, p.97f', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(33, 'AT-TRA-14', NULL, 'M24', 'Promotion of walking and cycling', 'Shifting modal split, improving living conditions and safety', 'The &quot;master plan cycling&quot; is one of the implementation of the Austrian strategy against PM (particulate matter), the Austrian climate strategy and the WHOCEHAPE. It is done in parallel with the strategy &ldquo;klima:aktiv&reg;mobil&rdquo;, the &ldquo;mobility management program&rdquo;, in particular also the awareness raising campaign. Principal purpose of this master plan is promoting cycling.<br />Upgrading of infrastructure and improvement of intermodal connection with public transport.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Not quantified (previous submissions: 100-300', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'AT-Climate Strategy 2007, p.89f', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(34, 'AT-TRA-17', NULL, 'M18', 'Promotion of biofuels', 'Minimum shares for transport fuels from renewable energy sources', 'In November 2004, the Bio Fuel Directive 2003/30/EC was transposed into Austrian national law with an amendment to the Fuel Ordinance. This amendment stipulates that all companies that put fuels in circulation must, from 1 October 2005, replace 2.5% of the total energy quantity put in circulation by biofuels. From 2007, this percentage will increase to 4.3%, and in 2008 the target of 5.75%, as stipulated in the Directive, will have to be achieved. Together with the amendment to the Fuel Ordinance, the Mineral Oil Tax has been revised. Accordingly, tax concessions will be granted with a biofuel share of at least 4.4% (for diesel since 1. October 2005, for gasoline starting at 1 October 2007). However, to be able to profit from the tax concessions, the fuel must also be sulphur-free (less than 10 mg sulphur per kg of fuel). The use of pure biofuels as motor fuel is exempt from tax.<br />Implemented through &Auml;nderung der Kraftstoffverordnung, BGBl II Nr.417/2004.', '2005', NULL, NULL, NULL, '1400', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'AT-Climate Strategy 2007, p.84f', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(35, 'AT-TRA-18', NULL, 'M20', 'Promotion of public transport systems', 'Increase the share of public transport in passenger transport by promoting and optimising transport and tariff associations', 'Public transportation plays from an historical point of view an important role in Austria. Nevertheless there is a trend in the modal split in favour of motor vehicles. As a countermeasure public authorities have promoted unified fares systems; since the end of the 1990ies the areas of 8 transport and tariff associations cover the whole of Austria. During the last years the L&auml;nder in cooperation with municipalities have started to optimise the public transportation network based on comprehensive regional traffic concepts. These concepts are based on better understanding of regional and local transport demands and aim at increased linking between different operators. High technical quality in the transportation systems, optimised time-tables and sufficient information for passengers are key features of a successful strategy to promote public transportation.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'AT-Climate Strategy 2007, p.85', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(36, 'AT-TRA-19', NULL, 'V.7', 'Adaptation of legal framework to climate protection goals', 'Reduction of emission from transport sector', 'Extension of parking sites and adaptation of tariffs. Speed restriction, increased speed control. Calculated emission reduction for speed restriction 400 Gg/year.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '400', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'AT-Climate Strategy 2007, p.90f', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(37, 'AT-TRA-20', NULL, 'V.13', 'Air traffic', 'Reduction of emission from air traffic', 'Reduction and limitation of emission from air traffic by integration in EU-ETS. <br />Research and development. Use of alternative fuels and power engines, reduction of total weight for reduced fuel consumption.', '2007', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'not quantified', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'AT-Climate Strategy 2007, p.100', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(38, 'AT-TRA-21', NULL, 'V.12', 'Adaptation of land use and regional planing', NULL, 'Integration of shopping centres in housing development areas for better accessibility by public transport, walking or cycling. Short way concept for settlement areas and access to public transport.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'AT-Climate Strategy 2007, p.99', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(39, 'AT-TRA-22', NULL, 'V.8', 'Increase of efficiency and shifting to energy efficient vehicles and transport systems, increased application of telematic systems', 'Reduction of emissions from transport sector', 'Implementation of e-traffic for optimal use of infrastructure (multimodality). Increase of rail and shipping transport through IT supported connections. Reduction of motorized private traffic, increase of lorry load etc.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'not quantified', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'AT-Climate Strategy 2007, p.91f', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(40, 'AT-CRS-08', NULL, 'M34', 'Energy related taxes and earmarking for climate change related measures', 'Revenue-raising with positive side-effect of potential GHG reductions', 'Austria introduced an energy tax on electricity and natural gas in 1996. Consequently, most fossil fuels (except coal) and electricity are covered by energy related taxes, since heating oil and transport fuels are taxed on an EU-wide common basis. In June 2000, the electricity tax was raised by 100% in order to compensate for demand-driving electricity price-cuttings. The latter is a consequence of the electricity market liberalisation since 1999. <br />In 2004 the taxes on natural gas and mineral oil for heating purpose were increased significantly (approx. 50%) and tax on coal was introduced. These changes, together with an adjustment of the maximum energy tax burden for energy intensive companies, were sufficient to meet the requirements of the council directive 2003/96/EC of 27 October 2003 concerning the restructuring of the community framework for the taxation of energy products and electricity. The revenue of the energy tax amounts to 785 million &euro; in 2005.The total revenue of the mineral oil tax amounts to 3.6 billion &euro; in 2004. Implemented through Bundesgesetz, mit dem das Energieabgabenverg&uuml;tungsgesetz ge&auml;ndert wird, BGBl. I Nr. 92/2004,<br />Bundesgesetz, mit dem das Kohleabgabegesetz ge&auml;ndert wird, BGBl. I Nr. 91/2004', '1996', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'not quantified (previous submissions 300)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(41, 'AT-CRS-300', NULL, 'M35', 'Implementation of emissions trading sheme', 'Cost-effective GHG emissions reductions for large stationary emitters', 'By implementation of EU directive 2003/87/EC, the European Emissions Trading Scheme (EU ETS) entered into effect by 1 January 2005. In case of Austria, around 200 energy intensive installations from industry and energy production sectors are covered by the scheme. Those installations are responsible for around 36% of Austria&rsquo;s total domestic GHG emissions (or 40% of CO2 emissions). Within the affected sectors, between 85 and 90% of emissions are covered. The emissions cap for the EU ETS sectors during the pilot trading phase 2005-2007 provides for CO2 emissions reductions of approximately 1.65 Mt (in comparison to business as usual scenarios). Excess emissions need to be compensated by purchase of additional allowances on the market. By 30 June 2006, Member States are obliged to submit their National Allocation Plans for the second trading phase, 2008-2012, to the European Commission for approval. The draft National Allocation Plan of Austria for the second trading phase is currently under preparation, being one of the instruments for Member States to comply with Kyoto Protocol targets during the commitment period 2008-2012. Implemented by: Bundesgesetz &uuml;ber ein System f&uuml;r den Handel mit Treibhausgasemissionszertifikaten<br />(Emissionszertifikategesetz &ndash; EZG), BGBl. I Nr. 46/2004.', '2005', NULL, NULL, NULL, '5500', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(42, 'AT-CRS-301', NULL, 'M36', 'Austrian JI/CDM Programme', 'Public purchase of ERUs and CERs', 'Within the scope of the Programme are:<br />&bull; Purchase of emission reduction credits from JI or CDM projects,<br />which lead to avoidance or reduction of greenhouse gas emissions;<br />&bull; financing of particular immaterial services, such as Baseline Studies<br />etc., which are necessary with respect to JI or CDM projects.<br />Based on the amendment of the Environmental Support Act the Programme was launched in August 2003. Kommunalkredit Public Consulting (KPC) was appointed for the Programme Management. Several calls for JI and CDM projects have been published since the launch of the programme and a relevant number of projects are already contracted, corresponding<br />to emissions reductions in the order of 7.5 Mt CO2-equivalent during the commitment period 2008-2012. A purchase budget of 36 million &euro; annually from 2006 to 2012 is guaranteed by law (after 1 million &euro; in 2003, 12 million &euro; in 2004 and 24 million &euro; in 2005). The total budget available for purchase of emissions reductions therefore will amount to 289 million &euro;.', '2003', NULL, NULL, NULL, '8500', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(43, 'AT-AGR-01', NULL, 'M27', 'Extension of ecological farming', 'Protection of rural environment (soil, water, natural and cultural habitats); production of high quality food', 'In the agricultural sector use of mineral fertiliser (nitrogen, phosphate, potassium) continues to decrease due to measures administered under the Austrian Programme for Environmentally Compatible Agriculture (&Ouml;sterreichisches Programm zur F&ouml;rderung einer umweltgerechten, extensiven und den nat&uuml;rlichen Lebensraum sch&uuml;tzenden Landwirtschaft, &Ouml;PUL), which is co-financed by the EU, and because of structural changes in the general economic framework. Meanwhile, an improved &Ouml;PUL programme is in force and a new programme taking into consideration the evaluation results found so far is being elaborated. At the same time, the share of organic farming increased substantially until the late 1990ies. Rising consumers&rsquo; demand for food products from organic farming also backed that development. In 2004, about 20,000 organic farms, i.e. 13.1 % of the farms registered under IACS existed in Austria, representing about 14.4% of the farmland of those farms which are registered under IACS. The federal government, the L&auml;nder and the EU gave compensation payments to organic farmers amounting to 90.62 million &euro; in 2004.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'not quantified', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(44, 'AT-AGR-02', NULL, 'M28', 'Cultivation of oil-seed crops', 'Extension of crops for production of biodiesel', 'Oil-seeds from rape and sun flower are also used as substitutes for mineral oil products (diesel). Oil-seeds acreage was around 7 500 ha for this purpose in 1999 and 2000, after 3 000 ha on average between 1997 and 1998. To support the development, liquid bio fuels have been entirely exempted from mineral oils taxes.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'not quantified', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `pam` (`id`, `pam_identifier`, `cluster`, `pam_no`, `name_pam`, `objective_of_measure`, `description_pam`, `start`, `ende`, `red_2005_val`, `red_2005_text`, `red_2010_val`, `red_2010_text`, `red_2015_val`, `red_2015_text`, `red_2020_val`, `red_2020_text`, `cumulative_2008_2012`, `explanation_basis_of_mitigation_estimates`, `factors_resulting_in_emission_reduction`, `include_common_reduction`, `documention_source`, `indicator_monitor_implementation`, `general_comment`, `reference`, `description_impact_on_non_ghg`, `costs_per_tonne`, `costs_per_year`, `costs_description`, `costs_documention_source`, `remarks`) VALUES
(45, 'AT-AGR-03', NULL, 'M30', 'Further enforcement of measures to reduce methane and N2O emissions', 'Protection of rural environment with more specific focus on GHG mitigation', 'A lot of measures within the agri-environmental programme contribute directly or indirectly to GHG emission reduction (e.g. manure management and reduced use of mineral fertilisers). These measures will be given even more emphasis in the future programme. As an accompanying measure, training programmes for farmers on ecologically sound production methods will be improved and intensified. In the current agri-environmental programme, in areas sensitive to groundwater aspects a particular measure was offered: spreading of liquid manure close to the<br />soil, which has proved to be efficient in reducing methane emission. Thus, it is planned to offer this measure as climate protection measure to all farmers. In order to raise consumers&rsquo; demand for food products from organic farming &ldquo;from the region&rdquo;, public service facilities are recommended to offer &ldquo;organic&rdquo; meals and products in restaurants (e.g. in schools, hospitals etc.). Some L&auml;nder and municipalities consider introducing obligatory quotas for calls for tender in this respect.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '200', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(46, 'AT-LUC-01', NULL, 'M29', 'Maintenance and extension of vital forests', 'Maintaining biodidversity, productivity, regeneration capacity and vitality of forests', 'Austrian forest management mainly focuses on the targets to maintain the biodiversity, productivity, regeneration capacity and vitality of forests and to improve adaptation to changing &ndash; specifically climatic &ndash; conditions. In order to be able to cope with the diverse interest in the utilisation of forests in future, all the national institutions, public and private interest groups, and all forest stakeholders are called upon to further develop a responsible forest management. For this purpose, the Federal Minister of Agriculture, Forestry, Environment and Water Management initiated a broad-based social dialogue process in April 2003 to develop an Austrian Forest Programme. Under the motto &ldquo;The forest concerns us all!&rdquo;, all forest stakeholders are invited to participate actively in the Austrian Forest Dialogue. The aim of the Forest Dialogue is to develop a comprehensive forest programme by the end of 2005, in which concrete proposals for political action on all major forest issues will be presented. The forest programme to be developed in the course of the Austrian Forest Dialogue is also a major contribution towards implementation of the Austrian Sustainability Strategy.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'not quantified', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(47, 'BE-CRS-02', NULL, 'M2', 'Kyoto Flexible Mechanism', 'Emission reduction from JI and CDM projects', 'Each entity has decided to use the flexibility mechanisms, either in the form of direct financing of projects, or via multilateral or bilateral funds.<br />In May 2005, the federal government launched its first JI/CDM tender for the purchase of emission reduction from CDM and JI projects, with an initial budget of &euro; 9,3 million. The call for Expressions of Interest (first phase of the tender) was open from May until September 2005 and 36 projects were received from countries in Asia, Africa, South America, Europe and Russia. In November 2005, the candidates selected during the first phase will be invited to submit a full proposal by March 2006. The projects selected during the second phase will be invited (indicative date - May 2006) to engage in negotiations with the federal government and to sign an ERPA (Emission Reduction Purchase Agreement), which constitutes a formal undertaking by the project participants to sell the emission reductions to Belgium. A new tender may be launched in early 2006 since the federal government&#39;s objective is to buy &euro; 12.3 million worth of emission reduction credits for the period 2008-2012.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BelgianReportMM15March2007_final, p.24', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(48, 'BE-CRS-300', NULL, 'M1', 'National Allocation Plan', 'National allocation plan for EU ETS', 'For the implementation of Directive 2003/87/EC, the regions are in charge of issuing greenhouse gas emission permits and the allocation plan for installations on their territories, excluding the support and safety installations for nuclear plants, which are the responsibility of the federal government. The Belgian National Allocation Plan is based on the sum of the three regional plans plus the federal plan.<br />The National allocation Plan is based on the sum of the three regional plans plus the federal plan. The Belgian federal government has published its National Allocation Plan (NAP) for CO2 emissions under the EU Emission Allowance Trading Scheme. The NAP is to allocate 183.2 Mt CO2 to installations covered by the scheme for the 2005-07 period. The regions were in charge of issuing GHG emission permits and drafting an allocation plan for installations on their territories. The European Commission has approved this National Allocation Plan.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BelgianReportMM15March2007_final, p.23', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(49, 'BE-AGR-03', NULL, NULL, 'Council Regulation (EC) No 1782/2003 of 29 September 2003 establishing common rules for direct support schemes under the common agricultural policy and establishing certain support schemes for farmers and amending Regulations (EEC) No 2019/93, (EC) No 1452/2001, (EC) No 1453/2001, (EC) No 1454/2001, (EC) 1868/94, (EC) No 1251/1999, (EC) No 1254/1999, (EC) No 1673/2000, (EEC) No 2358/71 and (EC) No 2529/2001', 'National PAM already in force before CCPM was adopted', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(50, 'BE-AGR-04', NULL, NULL, 'FR: Rural development programme', 'Improvement of agricultural practices', 'Flemish rural development plan 2000-2006, activities to extend organic farming and the marketing of organic products; involvement of farmes and horticulturists in the management of the natural environment; conversion towards sustainable water management, measures for energy savings in greenhouses and afforestation of agricultural land. Limit on increase of livestock until 2005.', NULL, NULL, '600', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(51, 'BE-AGR-09', NULL, NULL, 'WR: Rural Development Plan', 'Improvement of agricultural practices', 'measures to stimulate investment in reduction of pollutants of agricultural origin; financial support for training; grants for application of management plans; awareness rising; conservation of organic matter in soils; waste recovery', '2000', '2006', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(52, 'BE-AGR-10', NULL, 'A03', 'Agri-environmental measures', 'Improvement of agricultural practices', 'Among the agri-environmental measures, the following will have a significant impact on the emission of greenhouse gases from the agricultural sector:<br />- the introduction of extensive strips of meadow or grassland on the edge of crop fields along waterways to avoid seepage of nitrogen and pesticides into surface water;<br />- the introduction of seeded crops between other cultivated crops in order to reduce the loss of nitrates by leaching or run-off by 50%.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BelgianReportMM15March2007_final, p.21', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(53, 'BE-AGR-11', NULL, 'A02', 'Limitation/reduction of methane and NO2 emissions (WR)', 'Optimization of fertilization', 'Optimizing the techniques and practices of storage, spreading, composting and production of bio methane via environmental agreements and with financial support of public authorities', NULL, '2010', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(54, 'BE-AGR-12', NULL, 'A01', 'CO2 savings in greenhouse horticulture', 'Increase Energy saving and use of natural gas', 'The Flemish Region implements following measures for the reduction of CO2-emissions from greenhouse horticulture:<br />&bull; extend the gas network<br />&bull; CHP-certificates for the use of CO2 as fertiliser<br />&bull; Clustering of greenhouses<br />&bull; Financial incentives for investments in energy savings<br />&bull; Knowledge centre on rational energy use and energy technologies<br />Incentives for energy-saving measures in glasshouse horticulture take the form of subsidies from the Flemish Investment Fund and demonstration projects on the rational use of energy in the cultivation of ornamental plants and vegetables, inter alia.<br />The installation of CHP motors offers possibilities in horticulture. In recent years, it has mainly been a matter of projects in cooperation with energy producers, in which larger natural gas engines are installed, equipped with catalytic flue gas cleaning system for CO2 &ndash; fertilisation.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BelgianReportMM15March2007_final, p.20/21', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(55, 'BE-AGR-13', NULL, 'A02', 'Limitation/reduction of methane and NO2 emissions (FR)', 'Reduction of livestock systems to reduce emissions from manure', 'The agriculture sector achieves considerable reductions mainly by reducing the livestock (both financial incentives to halt production (2001-2003) and natural decline in cattle-breeding and by reduced use of artificial fertilizer. The reduction in livestock is supported by decoupling for animals.<br />The reduction in the number of animals and the tightening up of the manure policy also contribute to reduced use of manure, which in turn reduces the direct and indirect emission of nitrous oxide from the soil. Technical measures with regard to feed have only a limited impact on the emission of methane for the well-fed cattle in Flanders.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BelgianReportMM15March2007_final, p.21', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(56, 'BE-ENC-27', NULL, 'E05', 'Financial incentives for investments in energy efficiency', 'Improving energy efficiency', 'Tax deductions, subsidies and grants are provided for cost of investments increasing energy efficiency by the federal government as well as by the regions. Since 1992, a tax deduction has been granted for 13.5% of the cost of investments aiming to ease energy efficiency in the industrial sector (including the use of renewable energy resources).<br />The legislation provides that investments eligible for tax deductions must concern real property fallinginto one of the categories of Annex II of the Royal Decree/CIR92. The investments must concern more rational use of energy, improvement of industrial processes with regard to energy or the recovery of energy in industry.', '1992', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BelgianReportMM15March2007_final, p.12', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(57, 'BE-ENC-30', NULL, 'E07', 'Public service obligation on rational use of energy', 'Improving energy efficiency', 'To ensure that energy companies continue RUE actions in the liberalised market, the regional governments impose RUE public service obligations on the electricity grid managers. They are obliged to save an amount of primary energy every year.<br />Flanders: Electricity grid operators are obliged to decrease primary energy usage of end users every year. For high voltage clients the efficiency increase has to be 1%/yr.<br />Wallonia: Electricity and gas suppliers have to provide information on consumption and primary energy use together with bills.', '2002', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BelgianReportMM15March2007_final, p.13', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(58, 'BE-ENC-301', NULL, 'I01', 'Energy-efficiency in the industrial sectors', 'Improve energy efficiency in energy-intensive industries', 'The different regions have concluded agreements with the industrial sectors to maximize energy-efficiency and to reduce greenhouse gas emissions<br />The benchmarking covenant was definitively approved by the Flemish government on 29 November 2002 and applies to large energy-intensive companies (with an annual consumption of at least 0.5 PJ) and companies which fall under the European Emissions Trading Directive. By signing the benchmarking covenant, companies undertake to be among the most energy-efficient in the world by 2012 at the latest.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BelgianReportMM15March2007_final, p.20', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(59, 'BE-ENC-31', NULL, 'E06', 'Energy audits', 'Information and advice on energy consumption', 'In Flanders and Wallonia a free consultation service for small and medium sized companies has been set up to promote the rational use of energy. In Brussels, energy audits are subsidised up to 75% for installations covered by the European Emissions Trading Scheme and up to 50% for all other installations.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BelgianReportMM15March2007_final, p.13', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(60, 'BE-ENC-32', NULL, 'E08', 'Financial incentives for the rational use of energy', 'Improving energy efficiency', 'Tax deductions and subsidies for the replacement of old boilers, improvement of heat insulation of buildings and the use of solar panels by the federal government and the regions.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BelgianReportMM15March2007_final, p.13', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(61, 'BE-ENC-33', NULL, 'E09', 'Energy perfomance and certification of buildings', 'Reduce heating demand', 'The energy performance regulation implies minimum obligations regarding energy performance and indoor climate conditions for new buildings and renovation activities requiring an urban development licence.<br />Various actions are being undertaken with the goal of defining, harmonising and improving the application of energy performance standards among the regions.<br />Cooperation between the regions for inspecting building insulation and ventilation is being conducted under the auspices of the Belgian Building Research Institute (BBRI). Various actions are being undertaken with the goal of defining, harmonising and improving the application of energy performance standards. <br />* FL: Introduction of energy performance requirements in buildings and a strict enforcement framework (based on the as-built declaration and administrative fines that correspond to approximately three times the costs not invested).<br />WR: Concerning new dwellings, the &#39;Building with Energy&#39; action is a transitional stage. It gives architects and building contractors the opportunity to anticipate the transposition of Directive 2002/91/EC on the energy performance of buildings and encourages future owners to opt for new dwellings with high energy performance. A charter sets out the technical conditions required to reduce energy consumption. When the conditions are fulfilled, a certificate is issued for the building. This certificate describes the building&#39;s different energy features and can be considered its<br />&#39;identity card&#39;. With regard to existing dwellings, an energy consulting procedure provides an audit, on a voluntary basis, with a view to energy performance certification.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BelgianReportMM15March2007_final, p.13', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(62, 'BE-ENC-34', NULL, 'E10', 'Rational use of Energy (RUE) in public Buildings', 'Promote energy efficiency in public buildings', 'FED: The Belgian federal government has established the Belgian Energy Service Company (ESCO) to promote energy efficiency, mainly in public buildings. ESCO has been set up with &euro; 1.5 million in government financing from the Kyoto Fund and will seek &euro; 5 million in private funding. ESCO will invest in projects for which energy reduction would be profi table, but the investment cost for the owner or building administrator is too high. The savings on the energy bill will first be used to reimburse ESCO and will then benefit the client. An environmental management system will become compulsory for all federal agencies by the end of 2005. &#39;Sustainable development units&#39; will be created in each federal agency to that effect.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BelgianReportMM15March2007_final, p.14', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(63, 'BE-ENC-35', NULL, 'E11', 'Promotion of Rational use of Energy with local authorities', 'Promote sustainable local environment strategies', 'FR: The Flemish government has concluded a voluntary agreement with the local authorities, the 2002-2007 Cooperation Agreement, to promote a sustainable local environment policy. Through the energy section of this agreement, the municipalities and provinces have freedom of choice to encourage rational use of energy with ambitions at various levels. One of the main targets of the energy section is the emphasis on the exemplary role of the local level of administration. The most important components of this section are the start-up of energy accounting and of an energy supply system for urban, municipal or provincial buildings, infrastructures and domains.<br />WR: With EP-URE, the Walloon Region grants subsidies to municipalities for the replacement of public lighting (up to 70% of the cost of the investment). Another Walloon subsidy programme promotes energy effi ciency for municipal, provincial and regional buildings and also for schools and hospitals. This UREBA programme allows a subsidy rate of:<br />- 50% for energy accountancy<br />- 30% for energy audit<br />- 30% for investments up to a certain level of energy performance<br />- 30% for CHP and renewable energy investments.<br />BCR: From 1 January 2005, subsidies to encourage investments to reduce energy consumption in the services sector are available from SIBELGA. The investments can concern improvements to lighting and electric installations, HVAC and heating efficiency. A regional subsidy known as BRUREBA has also been put in place. BRUREBA is a set of RUE subsidies to improve building energy effi ciency via energy audits, feasibility studies, implementation of energy accountability, use of renewable energy sources, quality CHP installations and other RUE investments.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BelgianReportMM15March2007_final, p.15', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(64, 'BE-ENC-36', NULL, 'E12', 'Labelling of appliances', 'Efficiency requiements for new hot water boilers and labelling of appliances', 'FED: In accordance with EU Directive 92/42/EEC on efficiency requirements for new hot-water boilers, Belgium has changed its national legislation: the Royal Decree of 18 March 1997 sets efficiency requirements for new hot-water boilers fired with liquid or gaseous fuels. To comply with Directive 92/75/EEC on the energy labelling of household appliances, the Belgian federal government has adopted a number of Decrees concerning:<br />- refrigerators, deep freezers and combined devices;<br />- washing machines, dryers and combined devices;<br />- dishwashers;<br />- electric light bulbs.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BelgianReportMM15March2007_final, p.15', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(65, 'BE-ENC-502', NULL, NULL, 'I02: Energy efficiency criteria in the environmental permits', 'Implementation of IPPC Directive on energy efficiency', 'Implementation of IPPC regulation on energy efficiency: obligation of energy study for each new installation with energy use above 0.1 PJ and an energy plan for each above 0.5 PJ.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(66, 'BE-ENC-503', NULL, 'I01', 'Energy-efficiency in the industrial sectors', 'improve energy efficiency in industry', 'The voluntary branch agreement were signed with the 13 main industrial sectors. These accords engaged the partenairs to improve their energy efficiency.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(67, 'BE-ENS-02', NULL, 'E01', 'Green Certificate Schemes', 'Establish a system of renewable energy certificates', 'With a view to ensuring the placing on the market of a minimum volume of green electricity, a system GCs was established, both at the regional and federal levels. Electricity suplliers are obliged to provide a minimum amount of electricity sold form renewable energy sources. This minimum share increases up to 6% in 2010 (FR). A minimum price has been fixed for GCs.', '2001', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BelgianReportMM15March2007_final, p.11', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(68, 'BE-ENS-20', NULL, 'E03', 'Support for electricity generation from CHP', 'Promotion of CHP', 'In addition to Green Certificates, different tools have been set up to promote CHP: Electricity suppliers are obliged to submit yearly CHP certificates for an increasing percentage of their supplies. The generation of electricity from CHP is further encouraged by increased investment deduction (lower tax). Chapter XVIII of the general law of 27 December 2004 establishes an exemption from the energy tax for fuels supplying a CHP installation.', '2004', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BelgianReportMM15March2007_final, p.11', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(69, 'BE-ENS-21', NULL, 'E02', 'Support for electricity generation from RES and CHP', 'Promote electricity generation from renewables and CHP', 'In addition to the Green Certificates scheme, the Belgian authorities have implemented several measures to promote generation from RES. RES and CHP producers enjoy priority access to the grid in all regions. Existing legal and practical barriers (e.g. emission standards, reference efficiencies, fine on tariffs for imbalance, etc) are being addressed.', '2002', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BelgianReportMM15March2007_final, p.11', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(70, 'BE-ENS-22', NULL, 'E04', 'Demonstration projects, information actions and facilitators to promote RES and CHP', 'Promote electricity generation from renewables and CHP', 'To promote the use and know-how of RES and CHP, facilitators have been appointed. Target groups include industry, project developers, local authorities, education institutions and so on.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BelgianReportMM15March2007_final, p.12', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(71, 'BE-ENS-23', NULL, NULL, 'Production of green heat', 'Promote heat production from renewables', 'Grid managers provide subsidies to stimulate the production of green heat with solar energy and heat pumps.<br />Increased tax advantage for green heat production systems.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BelgianReportMM15March2007_final, p.12', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(72, 'BE-ENC-37', NULL, NULL, 'Energy performance targets in public housing and the medical &ndash; social sector', 'Increase energy efficiency', 'The Flemish Governments sets more ambitious energy performance targets for the public housing and the medical &ndash; social sector, than those required by the energy performance regulation.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BelgianReportMM15March2007_final, p.13', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(73, 'BE-ENC-38', NULL, NULL, 'Accreditation of energy experts', 'Increase energy efficiency', 'An energy audit in private and tertiairy buildings in the Flemish Region is only eligible for federal tax deduction if it is carried out by an expert accredited by the Flemish Region.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BelgianReportMM15March2007_final, p.14', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(74, 'BE-ENC-39', NULL, NULL, 'Extended maintenance of heating appliances', 'Increase energy efficiency', 'The measure involves the regular maintenance and inspection of specified heating boilers and a compulsory one-off inspection of boilers older than 15 years. The new obligations will apply from 2009 onwards in the Flemish Region.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BelgianReportMM15March2007_final, p.14', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(75, 'BE-ENC-40', NULL, NULL, 'Modernisation of school infrastructure', 'Increase energy efficiency', 'Via Public Private Partnerships, the Flemish Government will invest in an accelerated modernisation of school buildings. In addition, it invests in rational energy use in schools.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BelgianReportMM15March2007_final, p.14', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(76, 'BE-ENS-90', NULL, 'A06', 'Wood energy plan', 'Recovery of energy from wood', 'A Wood Energy Plan is targeted at initiating and implementing several projects for automatic wood heating, gas generation or other wood-use technologies designed to secure energy from wood. This plan essentially concerns municipalities and communities, whether or not connected to district heating systems.', '2001', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BelgianReportMM15March2007_final, p.22', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(77, 'BE-IND-02', NULL, 'I03', 'Covenant to reduce N20 emissions by the chemical industry', 'Reduction of N2O emission from the productions of nitric acid', 'Covenants were concluded between the regional governments and the nitric acid producers to reduce N2O emissions per tonne nitrous acid produced to the lowest possible level by applying state-of-the-art technology for the reduction of N2O emissions to each individual plant.<br />FR: Industrial nitric acid production constitutes the main source of nitrous oxide emissions in Flanders. There is one manufacturer in the Flemish Region. On 18 November 2005, a covenant was concluded between the Flemish government and this firm. The aim is to reduce N2O emissions per tonne nitrous acid produced to the lowest possible level by applying state-of-theart technology for the reduction of N2O emissions to each individual plant.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BelgianReportMM15March2007_final, p.20', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(78, 'BE-IND-03', NULL, 'I04', 'Reducing industrial emissions of fluorinated greenhouse gases', 'Reduced emissions of fluorinated greenhouse gases', 'In application of Regulation (EC) 2037/2000 on substances that deplete the ozone layer, the Member States have to adopt national regulations to reduce emissions of ozone-depleting refrigerant gases (HCFCs and CFCs). They must take all precautionary measures practicable to prevent and minimise leakages of these gases and must define the minimum qualification requirements for the personnel involved. The three regions recently adopted or will soon adopt regulations related to stationary applications containing refrigerant gases (refrigeration, air conditioning and heat pump equipment)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BelgianReportMM15March2007_final, p.20', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(79, 'BE-LUC-04', NULL, 'A04', 'Measures for encouraging reforestation and prohibition of deforestation', 'reforestation; afforestation', 'The authorities of the Flemish Region have set up, under the town and country planning act (&ldquo;Flanders Structural Town and Country Plan&rdquo;), measures aiming to extend the amount of woodland. The Flemish Region policy of reforestation is based on two strategies: firstly the authorities are pursuing a purchasing policy aiming to create new areas of woodland; secondly they are pursuing a policy of financial support aiming to initiate reforestation initiatives by local authorities or individuals.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BelgianReportMM15March2007_final, p.20', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(80, 'BE-LUC-06', NULL, 'A05', 'Preservation of the ecological stability of forests (Walloon region)', 'Forest conservation', 'The implementation of these policies results in the preservation of land, limiting changes in land use and consequently the loss of soil carbon.<br />WR: The Rural Development Plan 2000-2006 provides compensation for the lack of income for owners who practice forest conservation, through a policy of awarding allowances to private owners for setting up, managing and conserving private forest reserves.<br />Two important European Directives on nature protection &ndash; the Habitat and Birds Directive and the Natura 2000 Directive &ndash; have been transposed into law in Wallonia.', '2000', '2006', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BelgianReportMM15March2007_final, p.22', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(81, 'BE-LUC-07', NULL, 'A05', 'Preservation of the ecological stability of forests (Flemish region)', 'Support sustainable development', 'Preservation of ecological stability is an integral part of the concept of sustainable forest management (SFM) as defined in Flemish forest legislation. This principle was reiterated by the adaptation of criteria for sustainable forest management by the Flemish government.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(82, 'BE-LUC-08', NULL, NULL, 'Harmonisation of forest and climate policies (Flemish region)', 'Maintain storage capacity of GHG by forest', 'The Flemish forestry policy recently developed informative and incentive instruments to orient forestry more towards sustainable forest management (Decrees of the Flemish government of 27 June 2003 on sustainable forest management criteria + subsidies, management outlook for public forests).', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(83, 'BE-LUC-09', NULL, 'A08', 'Production of renewable energy and biofuels', 'Increase renewable energy production', 'The Flemish governments stimulates the production of biomass through:<br />- specific subsidies<br />- a knowledge centre regarding fresh woody biomass to provide technical support to growers<br />- adaptation of legislation and licensing procedures regarding production of biomass<br />In spring 2003, the demonstration project &ldquo;Application of ligneous biomass crops for sustainable energy production within farms in Flanders&rdquo; was started up for the purpose inter alia of investigating the sales market and acceptability of energy crops in Flanders. In addition, a study was started up to investigate the legal, economic, social and eological and technical aspects of short-rotation forestry in Flanders. The implementation of Directive 2003/30/EC can act as a significant stimulus to energy crops in Flanders.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BelgianReportMM15March2007_final, p.22', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(84, 'BE-TRA-05', NULL, NULL, 'Implementation of the European Biodiesel Directive', 'Promoting the use of biofuels to reduce emissions', 'The Federal Government has adopted the Biofuels Directive. The implementation should ensure that a minimum proportion of biofuels and other renewable fuels (2% in 2005, 5.75% in 2010) is placed on the market.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(85, 'BE-TRA-06', NULL, 'T06', 'Reduction in vehicle emissions - Clean vehicles for the public services', 'Progressive shift of public service fleet vehicles to cleaner models', 'The Federal Government is planning a progressive shift of the fleet of vehicles of the public services towards clean vehicles. This is planned through <br />1. Renewal of the car fleet of the federal administrations; <br />2. voluntary agreements between federal state and public companies (post, train, polices...)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(86, 'BE-TRA-07', NULL, 'T06', 'Promotion of public transport for daily mobility - Free train service for commuters', 'Reduction in emissions by shifting transport mode away from passenger car', 'Free train service for travel between home and the workplace was introduced on 1 March 2004 for federal civil servants and the staff of autonomous undertakings. From 1 January 2005, this possibility was offered to private companies provided they bear at least 80% of the cost of the train pass for their employees. The federal government compensates the railway for the loss of earnings.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(87, 'BE-TRA-08', NULL, 'T05', 'Improvement of multimodal systems - Subsidies for freight transport by rail', 'Support for movement of freight by rail as opposed to road, to reduce emissions', 'Several actions has been taken to promote the multimodal platforms. <br />A subvention is available for freight transport by rail on distance longer than 50 km (22 EUR per unit + 0.4 EUR per kilometer. This support for combined transport aims to consolidate and reorganise shuttles between interior terminals, notably due to the transhipment costs specifi c to this type of transport. The measure is meant to prevent short-distance combined transport from disappearing from railtraffic (this currently concerns nearly 300 000 shipments). The initial budget (&euro; 15 million for 2005) will rise to 30 million a year in 2006 and 2007.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BelgianReportMM15March2007_final, p.17', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(88, 'BE-TRA-09', NULL, 'T06', 'Reduction of vehicle emissions - Tax cut for the purchase of clean vehicles', 'Fiscal deductability for purchasing cleaner vehicles', 'Fiscal deductibility for the pruchase of clean vehicles: up to 15% of the vehicle price (max. 4000 EUR) for cars with CO2 emissions lower than 105 g/km, and upt to 3% of the vehicle price (max. 750 EUR) for cars with CO2 emissions between 105 and 115 g/km).', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(89, 'BE-TRA-10', NULL, 'T01', 'Improvements of the quality of public transport - Regional level', 'Increase the provision and improve the quality of public transport', 'Development of the links and points of connection between networks<br />- increased amount of urban and regional transport<br />- measures intended to increase traffic flow; priority regulations for public transport<br />- improvement of user safety on public transport<br />- development of new services such as systems of giving travellers information about all modes of transport from one centralised source', '2001', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(90, 'BE-TRA-11', NULL, 'T01', 'Improvements of the quality of public transport', 'Increase the provision and improve the quality of public transport', 'An ambitious investment plan in the railways (EUR 17 billion), was approved by the Federal Government on 13 July 2001. This plan, spread over several years (2001-2012), will allow the SNCB/NMBS to optimise the services it offers to transport people and goods by improvements in capacity, safety and speed. So investments will be made to improve the service to the clientele and to increase the regularity plus the speed of the traffic. The investments will be targeted at improved maintenance and capacity, on improving the rolling stock, on high speed train (TGV) infrastructure and on improving mobility in Brussels. This plan will also the subject of a co-operation agreement with the Regions.', '2001', '2012', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BelgianReportMM15March2007_final, p.15', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(91, 'BE-TRA-12', NULL, 'T02', 'Promotion of public transport for daily mobility', 'The use of public transport and car pooling for home/ work journeys', 'The federal and regional policies to promote modal shift encompasses a series of measures like free train service for commuters, extension of the tax deduction for expenses incurred for home-work travel when using alternative transport, etc. <br />Contributions by employers to the cost of a season ticket from a public transport company for making journeys between home and the place of work can from now on be wholly set against tax (up to a limit of EUR 125 per year). Previously the tax exemption had been limited to the quota corresponding to the contribution the employer was obliged to make. This measure applies to both the private and public sector and comes into force in the 2001 tax year, that is to say for the income of the year 2000. The employer&rsquo;s contribution for car-pooling is also free of tax. The amount exempted is in this case limited to the price of a first class train season ticket for a distance equal to the distance the worker has to travel by public transport.', '2001', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BelgianReportMM15March2007_final, p.15', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(92, 'BE-TRA-13', NULL, 'T02', 'Promotion of public transport for daily mobility - Extension of the tax deduction for expenses incurred for home-work travel when using alternative transport', 'Use of alternative means of transport for home/work journeys', 'In order to encourage taxpayers to journey between home and the place of work otherwise than in a motor car, the deductible professional expenses relating to such journeys are fixed at a set level of EUR 0.15 /km, even if the real cost is lower (Art. 9 of the above-mentioned law). At present this deduction only concerns journeys by motor car, hybrid vehicle or minibus; so it is being extended to all modes of journey, whether this be walking, by bicycle, public transport or even car-pooling. For the 2002 tax year (income from 2001), the maximum distance allowed for is fixed at 50 km for the round trip. It has since been raised to 100 km (2003 tax year), 150 km (2006 tax year) and 200 km (2007 tax year).', '2001', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(93, 'BE-TRA-14', NULL, 'T02', 'Promotion of public transport for daily mobility - Tax deduction for collective transport organised by private companies', 'Collective transport of company personnell', 'Employers may deduct 100 % of expenses agreed to for the operation of collective transport of members of staff (Art. 62 of the law of 10 August 2001). Currently, this deductibility is limited, in certain cases, to 75 %. The investments and expenses to be taken into consideration are: investments in minibuses, buses and coaches that are used for the collective transport of workers from home to the place of work; the expenses directly incurred by these vehicles, such as maintenance and repairs, the road tax, the insurance, the fuel, etc.; the expenditure paid to companies that, in place of the employer or the group of employers, undertake the collective transportation of workers from home to the place of work. This measure will be applied starting with the 2002 tax year (2001 income). From the 2003 tax year onwards (income earned in 2002), the amount that can be deducted will rise to 120 % (Art. 63).', '2002', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(94, 'BE-TRA-15', NULL, 'T08', 'Implementation of transport mobility plans (schools and business) - FR', 'Collective transport (school children and company personnel)', 'The regional mobility measures indicate that an incentive, support and coordination policy should be developed for companies. <br />FR: The Flanders mobility plan indicates that an incentive, support and coordination policy should be developed for companies. In addition, the possibilities and limitations will be examined of commitments between the government and companies, with each party implementing the available instruments to good effect. As regards school transport, the Flemish government has decided to transfer the transport of schoolchildren from the Education department to the Flemish transport company De Lijn. In the future, this must develop towards cross-network collection services for the transport of schoolchildren.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BelgianReportMM15March2007_final, p.18', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(95, 'BE-TRA-17', NULL, 'T08', 'Implementation of transport mobility plans - WR', 'Collective transport of company personnell', 'An agreement between Walloon Region and the Walloon Business Federation for a campaign to make people aware of issues in managing the mobility of Walloon companies;<br />- the production, in collaboration with the &quot;UWE Mobility Cell&quot; and based on existing experiences, of a methodological guide intended to help companies draw up a Company Transport Plan (PTE);<br />- running training courses for company mobility advisors;<br />- agreements between the Walloon Region and companies (public or private) to conduct pilot transport plan experiments.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(96, 'BE-TRA-20', NULL, 'T03', 'Promotion of bicycle use - WR, FR, Brussels region', 'Use of bicycles and walking for short journeys', 'Extension of a functional network for pedestrians and cyclists; improvement of cycle paths and facilities for bicycles. The general opening of one-way streets in two directions for cyclists in Brussels capital region. Installation of appropriate facilities (bicycle stands, bicycle hire and minor maintenance) at the main stops and stations of Brussels public transport;', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BelgianReportMM15March2007_final, p.16', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(97, 'BE-TRA-21', NULL, 'T05', 'Improvement of multimodal systems - Improvement of transport infrastructure around the Port of Antwerp', 'Use of different modes of transport', 'A new platform connecting different types of transport (the Main Hub) was inaugurated on 29 August 2001 at the port of Antwerp. This container terminal, representing an investment of<br />approximately BEF two billion (nearly EUR 50 millions), is intended to respond to the present and future strong growth of maritime container traffic. By 2005 it will cater for 6 to 700 000 movements per year, and is called to play a major role in the development of integrated continental transport.<br />- Access to the port of Antwerp will be improved, by creating a second rail access, and reopening the &ldquo;Iron Rhine&rdquo; (rail link between Antwerp and the Ruhr via Roermond).', '2001', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(98, 'BE-TRA-25', NULL, 'T02', 'Promotion of public transport for daily mobility - Analysis of travel between home and workplace', 'Use of alternative means of transport for home/work journeys', 'A national survey on travel between home and the workplace will be conducted at all companies with more than 100 employees based on the situation existing on 30 June 2005. After a consultation of workers or their representatives, the analysis will be transmitted, no later than 30 April 2006, to the FPS Mobility and Transport. An evaluation will subsequently be conducted to determine whether this data base is used by employers as a basis for establishing enterprise transport plans, by the public authorities as support for their mobility policy and by institutions involved in research on mobility issues.', '2005', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(99, 'BE-TRA-26', NULL, 'T05', 'Improvement of multimodal systems - WR', 'Changing betweeen modes of tranport', 'Development project for the independent port of Clabecq and creation on this site of a third hub for three modes of transport that will allow the development of integrated transport from the Charleroi- Brussels canal.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(100, 'BE-TRA-28', NULL, 'T05', 'Improvement of multimodal systems - Intermodal platform Brussels', 'Changing betweeen modes of tranport', 'An intermodal platform integrating rail, waterway and road transport systems has been placed into service. The availability of land will enable the port to develop logistics activities.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(101, 'BE-TRA-29', NULL, 'T06', 'Reduction of vehicle emissions - Modulation of the road tax', 'Promotion of less polluting vehicles', 'A law introduces a differentiation of the amount payable in European road tax in accordance with &ldquo;EURO&rdquo; standards, in such a way as to encourage vehicles to meet the most recent standards for polluting emissions.', '2001', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(102, 'BE-TRA-31', NULL, 'T06', 'Reduction of vehicle emissions - Promotion of LPG vehicles', 'Promotion of less polluting vehicles', 'The purchase of new LPG vehicles is promoted through a reduction (&euro; 298) of the car registration tax for cars fitted from the outset with LPG (in practice, this makes car registration tax-free for the smallest vehicles); a working group is studying regulatory measures to authorise access for LPG vehicles to underground car parks.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(103, 'BE-TRA-33', NULL, 'T06', 'Reduction of vehicle emissions - Promotion of  renewal of the car fleet', 'Promotion of less polluting vehicles', 'The car registration tax for second-hand vehicles will only be reduced by 5% per year dating from the 5th year after they were initially put onto the road, instead of 10%.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `pam` (`id`, `pam_identifier`, `cluster`, `pam_no`, `name_pam`, `objective_of_measure`, `description_pam`, `start`, `ende`, `red_2005_val`, `red_2005_text`, `red_2010_val`, `red_2010_text`, `red_2015_val`, `red_2015_text`, `red_2020_val`, `red_2020_text`, `cumulative_2008_2012`, `explanation_basis_of_mitigation_estimates`, `factors_resulting_in_emission_reduction`, `include_common_reduction`, `documention_source`, `indicator_monitor_implementation`, `general_comment`, `reference`, `description_impact_on_non_ghg`, `costs_per_tonne`, `costs_per_year`, `costs_description`, `costs_documention_source`, `remarks`) VALUES
(104, 'BE-TRA-35', NULL, 'T06', 'Reduction of vehicle emissions - CO2 guide', 'Changing the behaviour patterns of consumption', 'Modification of behaviour patterns of consumption in favour of vehicles that emit low amounts of pollutants; Internet database stating the fuel consumption of every new motor car distributed in<br />Belgium.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(105, 'BE-TRA-36', NULL, 'T11', 'Traffic regulation', 'Reduce polluting emissions due to car traffic', 'Avoiding speeding offences and abrupt changes of speed offer potential. These measures are also important to meet the air quality standards<br />FR: Consumption and emissions rise sharply from 90 to 100 km/hour. Avoiding speeding offences and abrupt changes of speed offer potential. These measures are also important to meet the air quality standards:<br />- tightening up of control on compliance with the imposed speed limits;<br />- introduction of intelligent speed adaptors;<br />- unmanned cameras.<br />WR: From the mid-1990s, a large-scale project was launched for the coordination of traffi c management actions on the system of motorways and trunk roads: WHIST (Walloon Highway Information System for Traffic). It is based on the use of road telematics tools, also known as intelligent transport systems, and on an operations centre, PEREX. Traffi c optimisation and monitoring are meant to limit bottlenecks and to keep speed under control, leading to a decrease in GHG emissions.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BelgianReportMM15March2007_final, p.19', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(106, 'BE-TRA-41a', NULL, NULL, 'Improvements to public transport (Walloon  Region)', 'Increase the provision and improve the quality of public transport', 'Development of bus and tram lines (changes to the metro, new lines to the suburbs)<br />- Integration of the fare structure to encourage the use of different forms of transport<br />- Priority routes for trams and buses<br />- Increased frequency of trams, buses and metro trains<br />- Increased operating speed of trams and buses', '2001', '2005', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(107, 'BE-TRA-41b', NULL, 'T03', 'Promotion of bicycle use - Stop Principle and Bike Plan', 'Giving priority to the use of least polluting and most appropriate means of transport, Promotion of cycling', 'The STOP principle consists in giving priority to the use of the least polluting and most appropriate means of transport. To implement the principle, the federal government will take various measures to improve the safety and comfort of walking, cycling and public transport. In 2004, a Bike Plan meant to define a coherent policy integrating cycling into the overall system of traffic and transport, was developed and submitted to the Council of Ministers. Its implementation is set to begin shortly.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(108, 'BE-TRA-43', NULL, 'T05', 'Improvement of multimodal systems - Marco Polo Programme', 'Shift the expected increase in international road transport of freight to short-distance maritime freight service, rail and inland waterways', 'Programme of financial support for modal shift. Developing projects involving Belgium stakeholders in transport, logistics and production.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(109, 'BE-TRA-44', NULL, 'T05', 'Improvement of multimodal systems - Diabolo Plan', 'Improvement of infrastructure', 'Building of a new railway infrastructure to make Brussels-National Airport directly accessible from the north and east of the country. The airport is expected in time to be connected to the REN and TGV rail systems.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(110, 'BE-TRA-45', NULL, 'T12', 'Green procurement rules for public service vehicle fleets', 'Emission reductions', 'The governments strive towards a gradual shift towards cleaner vehicles in the public service fleet. This is realised through:<br />&bull; the application of the Ecoscore in government purchase of new vehicles;<br />&bull; voluntary agreements with public companies (post office, railway, police, Regional transportation companies (De Lijn), etc.)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BelgianReportMM15March2007_final, p.19', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(111, 'BE-TRA-46', NULL, 'T10', 'Eco-driving Campaign', 'Promotion of less polluting driving habits and specific actions fro driving schools', 'Driving style and habit determine the energy consumption of a vehicle and therefor the emission of CO2 and air pollutants.<br />The FR integrates environmentally friendly driving behaviour in driving lessons.<br />Organisation of campaign that inform drivers about different ways of driving more fuel-efficiently. Aims at a change in behaviour as regard the driving style of both private and professional drivers. Eco driving must become automatic reactions.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BelgianReportMM15March2007_final, p.19', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(112, 'BE-TRA-48', NULL, 'T04', 'Car Sharing', 'Promotion of car sharing', 'To implement the mobility plan, more promotion will be carried out on professionally supported car-sharing, like reservation of a lane of traffic, internet site, &hellip;<br />In FR car-sharing projects will exist in most urban areas by 2009. The FR also studies car-sharing projects for businesses and has set up pilot projects.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BelgianReportMM15March2007_final, p.16', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(113, 'BE-TRA-49', NULL, 'T05', 'Improvements of multimodal systems - Flanders Mobility Plan', 'General improvement of transport', 'Flanders mobility plan, through changes in modes of transport, aims to limit the increase in the number of tonnes/kilometre over the road network to 33% in 2010/2012 (compared to 1998). The increase in the number of vehicle kilometres remains limited to 17% as a result of the improved transport efficiency. The Flemish Government adopted the Mobility Plan on Oct 17th 2003. The plan described 5 policy packages to come to sustainable road transport: more alternatives for cars and trucks, better infrastructure, promotion of modal shift, efficient use of means of transport, more efficient and safe car park.', '2003', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(114, 'BE-TRA-50', NULL, 'T06', 'Reduction of vehicle emissions - Taxation of company cars', 'Promotion of less polluting vehicles', 'The programme law of 27 December 2004 imposes, from 1 January 2005, a lumpsum minimum monthly contribution of &euro; 20.83 on company cars (passenger cars, minibuses, tractors, light trucks); this contribution varies in terms of the rate of CO2 emissions in grammes per kilometre.', '2005', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(115, 'BE-TRA-51', NULL, 'T06', 'Reduction of vehicle emissions - Gentlements agreement with car manufacturers', 'Promotion of less polluting vehicles', 'The federal government supports the European Commission initiative to lower average CO2 emissions by cars up to 120 g CO2/km by 2012.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(116, 'BE-TRA-52', NULL, 'T06', 'Reduction of vehicle emissions - FR, BCR', 'Promotion of less polluting vehicles', 'The regions and the federal government promote environmentally friendly cars through the use of the Ecoscore, representative for the impact of the vehicle on the environment.<br />The FR will calculate its annual road tax on the basis of the Ecoscore from 2009 onwards.<br />FR: The Flemish Region includes CO2 and other greenhouse gasses in an overall emission label called &#39;Ecoscore&#39;. The methodology is explained on the website www.milieuvriendelijkvoertuig.be, which presents the Ecoscore for both new and older cars, heavy duty vehicles and twowheelers, as well as information on CO2 emissions, the Euro standard and clean vehicles and fuels. An action plan on ecologically sound vehicles focuses on different measures.<br />BCR: Communication tools have been developed, including the &#39;Ecoscore&#39; software tool available on the website www. ibgedim.be, which calculates the environmental score of any vehicle (air and noise). The Brussels Air and Climate Plan (March 1999) provides for a shift in the public service fl eet to clean vehicles: the regional administrations must own a minimum of 20% clean vehicles in their fl eet by 2008. A model call for bids for the purchase of clean vehicles has been developed for public administrations.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BelgianReportMM15March2007_final, p.17', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(117, 'BE-TRA-53', NULL, 'T02', 'Promotion of public transport for daily mobility - WR, BCR', 'Use of alternative means of transport for home/work journeys', 'WR: In addition to these measures targeting workers, business mobility plans are also developed to encourage the use by employees of alternatives to cars (public transport, transport service organised by the company, car sharing, etc.), as well as school mobility plans designed to improve the conditions in which pupils travel between home and school and to reduce the share of car travel.<br />BCR: A complement to the federal measure for free travel between home and the workplace: from 1 January 2005, private companies may provide for their employees to be entitled to free travel between home and the workplace on public transport with the use of combined train passes.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(118, 'BE-TRA-54', NULL, 'T08', 'Implementation of transport/mobility plans (School, business) - BCR', 'collective transport (school children and company personnel)', 'BCR: A decree approved by the Brussels Government on 4 February 2004 makes staff mobility plans compulsory for all companies with more than 200 employees. To facilitate the preparation of mobility plans, technical information and a manual are available on the IBGE?s website and specific training sessions are organised. Once fully implemented, the business mobility plans will concern the mobility of about 200 000 workers.<br />The regional and local authorities, in collaboration with the STIB, will build 10 pilot areas with specific mobility plans. The STIB will develop specific strategies for any event bringing together more than 3 000 people. Municipalities have authority to create &#39;30 zones&#39; (speed limit of 30 km/h) on their roads. The regional objective for &#39;30 zones&#39; is 77% of local roads by 2010.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(119, 'BE-TRA-55', NULL, 'T07', 'Mobility plans at local level', 'Promote alternative means of transport, improve infrastructure', 'The Regions have implemented mobility plans at town and municipality levels<br />FR: In 2002, transport was included in the environment contracts concluded between the Flemish Region and local governments. Local authorities can subscribe to one of three stages: <br />- ecologically sound vehicles: drawing up an inventory of vehicle fleet + environmental check + drawing up of action plan to arrive at a more ecologically sound vehicle fleet + taking concrete measures;<br />- ecologically sound transport of own staff: analysis of working at home and shifting of services + drawing up action plan to arrive at ecologically sound travel + carrying out of concrete measures;<br />- targeted awareness campaigns on the environment and mobility.<br />WR: The Walloon Region has implemented mobility plans at town and municipality level, with the assistance of external consultants.<br />BCR: Each of the 19 municipalities of the Brussels-Capital Region is strongly encouraged to implement a Local Mobility Plan: if the local and regional administrations sign a cooperation agreement, the Region finances a large part of the Plan&#39;s development. Some municipalities are already putting the Plan into operation.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BelgianReportMM15March2007_final, p.18', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(120, 'BE-TRA-56', NULL, 'T09', 'Optimal road traffic management', 'Increasing capacity of main road network', 'The FR and WR will expand its dynamic traffic management through actively steering traffic flows on the road network, through influencing traffic lights and through the furter development of a traffic flow module<br />FR: Not only very high speeds and abrupt changes of speed but also heavily congested traffic results in higher consumption and higher emissions. Increasing the capacity of the main road network, in view of the expected growth in road transport, is one of the solutions. The elimination of capacity restrictions at bottlenecks on the main road network, dynamic traffi c management and facilitation in the case of capacity-reducing incidents are measures to be taken.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BelgianReportMM15March2007_final, p.19', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(121, 'BE-TRA-57', NULL, NULL, 'Implementation of biofuel directive', 'Increase proportion of biofuels and other renewable fuels in transport to 5.75 % by 31 December 2010', 'The federal government has adopted the Directive on the promotion of the use of biofuels and other renewable fuels for transport (Royal Decree of 4 march 2005). For Belgium, the minimum proportion of biofuels and other renewable fuels set as national indicative target is 2 % calculated on the basis of energy content of all petrol and diesel for transport purposes placed on the Belgian market by 31 December 2005.  This percentage will be  increased yearly by  0.75 % to (reach) 5.75 % by 31 December 2010.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BelgianReportMM15March2007_final, p.17', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(122, 'BE-TRA-58', NULL, NULL, 'Teleworking', 'Decrease commuter travel', 'The FR promotes teleworking and wishes to remove in consultation with the federal government to remove legal obstacles to teleworking. Government officials of the FR are stimulated to &ldquo;telework&rdquo; either at home, either in so-called &ldquo;satellite offices&rdquo;.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BelgianReportMM15March2007_final, p.18', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(123, 'BE-TRA-59', NULL, NULL, 'Model shift in freight transport', 'Increase shipping and rail transport', 'The Belgian entities encourages and promotes inland shipping and rail transport as alternative transport modes through:<br />&bull; the investment in infrastructure (a.o. removing missing links), both for rail and network of main waterways;<br />&bull; appointment of transport experts to audit the optimisation of the flow of goods in companies.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BelgianReportMM15March2007_final, p.18', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(124, 'BE-WAM-10', NULL, 'W02', 'Improvement of energy efficiency of existing and new incineration plants', 'Energy efficiency', 'FR: New waste incineration plants are required to produce a high energy yield. Existing plants with energy recovery must optimise their energy yield to the maximum. On the basis of a feasibility study with a BAT perspective (best available techniques), energy performance measurement formulas were definitively established in 2004.<br />BCR: The Region has only one waste incinerator (535 000 tonnes) in use. This household waste incinerator has to comply with standards for dioxins and will be equipped with denitrifi cation equipment.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BelgianReportMM15March2007_final, p.23', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(125, 'BE-WAM-90', NULL, 'W01', 'Maintenance of elimination obligations and reinforcement of regulations on the use of gas from landfills', 'Reduce GHG emissions from landfills', 'It requires the operators of landfill sites, which do not have a system for putting gases from landfill sites to good use to submit a study demonstrating that this is not technically and economically feasible. If it is possible to put these gases to good use, the system must be installed.<br />The programme to treat former landfill sites will be continued and intensified; this programme is intended to make sure that all emissions are recovered and treated correctly.<br />FR: The VLAREM amendment on the recovery of gases from landfill sites was definitively adopted by the Flemish government on 14 March 2002 (BS/MB 13/02/2004). It requires the operators of landfill sites which do not have a system for putting gases from landfill sites to good use to submit a study by 1 July 2004 demonstrating that this is not technically and economically feasible. If it is possible to put these gases to good use, the system must be installed by 30 June 2005.<br />WR: The programme to treat former landfill sites will be continued and intensified; this programme is intended to make sure that all emissions are recovered and treated correctly. Biogas recovery is also being encouraged and has developed considerably since 1993. According to the annual survey of solid waste disposal sites and estimated total emissions, more than 70% of methane is now being recovered, which is directly refl ected in net emissions. Depending on methane content, the biogas is flared or used for energy purposes. Biogas recovery is the main measure in the waste sector and has led to a substantial decrease of emissions since 1990.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BelgianReportMM15March2007_final, p.23', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(126, 'BG-ENS-01', NULL, 'E1', 'Improvement of the operation of nuclear power plant Kozloduy (NPP-K)', 'Improvement of the existing plants', 'One of the most important branches of Bulgarian energy sector is nuclear energy, which does not release any GHG emissions during the production of electricity. Kozloduy units 1-4 were gradually put out of operation (units 1 and 2 in 2002, and units 3 and 4 in 2006). Decommissioning of units 1 to 4 was in accordance with the EU requirements. To preserve the share of nuclear energy in the overall production of electricity in the country measures have to be implemented to further improve the operation of units 5 en 6 and modernize them. The introduction of new methods for control and planned repairs leads to reduction of the planned demurrage and fuel recharge. In this way, an effective load up to 7200 hours per year can be achieved as well as an increase of electricity production of 1.28 TWh per year. After 2010 commissioning of a new unit at NPP Belene is envisaged. The forecasted electricity production at NPP-K for 2010 is 12.4 TWh.', '2005', '2008', NULL, NULL, '946', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BG-NC4, p.54/55, BG-subMM 07, p.7', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(127, 'BG-ENS-02', NULL, 'E2', 'Accelerated development of hydro energy', 'Construction of hydro cascade Gorna Arda and Sredna Vucha (expected start up 2012)', 'The existing hydropower plants (HPPs) have been rehabilitated as a considerable part of them had outdated equipment. New automation and control systems were introduced. 70 % of the hydro potential is already utilized. New capacities of 400 MW could be built for an annual operation of 2 000 to 3 000 hours.', '2005', '2008', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '408', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BG-NC4, p.54/55, BG-subMM 07, p.8', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(128, 'BG-ENS-03', NULL, 'E3', 'Small and micro HPP', 'Construction of small and micro HPP in different country regions', 'Hydropower stations with capacity up to 10 MW are classified as small or micro HPPs. The total installed capacity of micro HPPs amounted to 63 MW in 2004. The potential for electricity production from MHPPs is thoroughly studied and is assessed at 0.7 TWh per year.  MHPPs could be constructed at locations with artificial lakes or fast-flowing water. So far, high investments costs and the low annual utilization of the installed capacity (app. 2500 hours per year) impede the installation of new capacities.', '2005', '2008', NULL, NULL, '200', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BG-NC4, p.54/55, BG-subMM 07, p.8', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(129, 'BG-ENS-04', NULL, 'E4', 'Upgrading of cogeneration plants and district heating boilers', 'Upgrading of cogeneration plants and district heating boilers by natural gas turbines', 'The overall efficiency could be increased to 80-90%, which is much higher than that of existing cogeneration units or heat boilers. The introduction of new natural-gas combined cycle for replacing capacities at some of the existing thermal power plants and district heating plants forms part of the Implementation Programme for the Directive on Large Combustion Plants for the period after 2007.', '2005', '2008', NULL, NULL, '867', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BG-NC4, p.54/55, BG-subMM 07, p.9', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(130, 'BG-ENS-05', NULL, 'E5', 'Electricity transmission and distribution losses', 'Decreasing of losses in the distribution and transmission networks', 'Losses of electricity can be reduced through rehabilitation, modernisation and improving the exploitation of the transmission and distribution networks. A reduction of the electricity losses will lead to fewer GHG emissions as a result of lower electricity production in coal-fired plants. According to experts&rsquo; assessment these are about 20-30 % of the losses in transmission networks and 30-40% of the losses in distribution networks.', '2005', '2008', NULL, NULL, '1100', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BG-NC4, p.54/55, BG-subMM 07, p.9', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(131, 'BG-ENS-06', NULL, 'E6', 'Heat transmission and distribution losses', 'Decreasing of losses in the heat transmission networks', 'Losses of heat can be reduced through rehabilitation, modernization and improving the exploitation of the transmission and distribution networks. A reduction of the heat losses will lead to fewer GHG emissions as a result of lower heat production in heat boilers.', '2005', '2008', NULL, NULL, '900', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BG-NC4, p.54/55, BG-subMM 07, p.9', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(132, 'BG-ENS-07', NULL, 'E7', 'Biomass for electricity and heat production', 'Biomass for electricity and heat production', 'Biomass includes firewood, waste wood, agricultural solid waste (vegetal residues), agricultural liquid waste (liquid manure and others), combustible industrial waste (paper, chips) and municipal solid and liquid waste. <br />Fire wood and agricultural waste (vegetal residues) are traditionally used as energy source in Bulgaria. The potential for biomass utilization is high. <br />The assessment of the theoretical potential resulted in the following figures: firewood &ndash; 7.7 PJ per year; waste paper - 0.3 PJ per year; agricultural solid waste - 77.1 PJ per year; waste from live-stock breeding -11.3 PJ per year; municipal solid waste - 12.5 PJ per year and industrial waste wood - 0.4 PJ per year.<br />There are several ways for biomass conversion (e.g. combustion, pyrolysis and gasification), but combustion of biomass for production of electricity and thermal energy seem to be the most promising for Bulgaria.', '2005', '2008', NULL, NULL, '50', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BG-NC4, p.54/55, BG-subMM 07, p.10', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(133, 'BG-IND-01', NULL, 'I1', 'Reduction of thermal losses in industry', 'Reduction of thermal losses in industry', 'The use of heat in the form of steam and hot water is an important part of the industrial energy consumption. Reduction of heat losses can be realized through thermal insulation, redesign and replacement or updating of heat exchangers leading to reduction of fuel consumption for its<br />production.', '2005', '2008', NULL, NULL, '120', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BG-NC4, p.55/57, BG-subMM 07, p.12', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(134, 'BG-IND-02', NULL, 'I2', 'Natural gas supply to the industry by development of gas infrastructure', 'Increased use of natural gas in industry by new gas infrastructure', 'Industry is a large consumer of energy. Substituting liquid fuels with natural gas is profitable for industry when infrastructure is available. Fuel switch contributes to lower emissions of GHG emission and higher efficiency. One of the main obstacles to the fuel switch, however, is the high investment costs for developing distribution networks.', '2005', '2008', NULL, NULL, '50', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BG-NC4, p.56/57, BG-subMM 07, p.12', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(135, 'BG-IND-03', NULL, 'I3', 'Introduction of monitoring systems for energy consumption', 'Control of energy consuming systems in industry', 'One way to achieve improvement of the efficiency of production processes is the establishment of systems for monitoring and control of energy consumption at different technological stages. This enables companies to have more insight in their energy consumption in various parts of the<br />process, showing where measures could be taken for increase of efficiency.This would lead to a lower amount of energy used per unit product. Savings can be made both in electricity and heat use, as well as natural gas, residual and gas oil consumption.', '2006', NULL, NULL, NULL, '110', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BG-NC4, p.56/57, BG-subMM 07, p.13', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(136, 'BG-IND-04', NULL, 'I4', 'Upgrading of steam and heat generation and compressed-air plants', 'Modernization of steam and compressed-air installations', 'In the light industry, food processing industry, machine building and metalworking, electrical and electronic industry can all reduce about 20 % of the energy consumption. This can be done through modernization of steam and compressed-air installations, regulation of the heat energy<br />systems, energy management and control and introduction of small-scale co-generation at the relevant enterprises.', '2007', NULL, NULL, NULL, '20', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BG-NC4, p.56/57, BG-subMM 07, p.13', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(137, 'BG-IND-05', NULL, 'I5', 'Renovation of construction machines', 'Introduction of highly-efficient construction machines using diesel fuel (25 % replacement)', 'Construction is an industrial branch of which emissions from residual oil consumed in road-transportation machines represents a considerable share in the overall GHG emissions of the country. Defining standards for efficiency of those machines and strengthening inspections would lead to the gradual phase out of these machines, increasing the average efficiency of the remaining machine park.', '2006', NULL, NULL, NULL, '70', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BG-NC4, p.56/57, BG-subMM 07, p.13/14', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(138, 'BG-IND-06', NULL, 'I6', 'Reduction of fuel consumption in production of building materials', 'Replacement of part of the fuel by motor-car tyres and other combustible waste', 'Cement industry is a key GHG emissions source. Production of structural ceramics and quicklime consume large amounts of fuels (both liquid and solid) as well. The energy use in this sector can be reduced by replacing part of the fuel by combustible waste such as car tires.', '2005', '2008', NULL, NULL, '340', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BG-NC4, p.56/57, BG-subMM 07, p.14', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(139, 'BG-ENS-08', NULL, 'H1', 'Gas supply to households', 'Household gas supply', 'The Residential Gasification has the following advantages in comparison with the central heating:<br />&bull; there is no necessity for construction of huge thermal plants<br />&bull; investments in gas distribution networks are much lower<br />&bull; heat losses during distribution of heat are eliminated<br />&bull; it is favorable for the work of the energy system.<br />The Gas Supply Program for Residential and Servicing sector of MEE plans for additional households to be connected towards 2020, which should lead to a reduction of 6.9 Mton ??2 Eq. Assuming annual new connections about 290 thousand additional households will be supplied towards 2010, leading to an emission reduction of 2.3 Mton.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2300', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BG-NC4, p.57/58, BG-subMM 07, p.16/17', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(140, 'BG-ENS-09', NULL, 'H2', 'Solar collectors', 'Installation of solar collectors', 'The geographical situation of the country provides for a substantial solar energy potential. The solar collectors transform solar energy in useful thermal energy. Due to the relatively low single capacities these panels are suitable for installation at institutional buildings and private homes.', '2007', '2008', NULL, NULL, '20', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BG-NC4, p.58, BG-subMM 07, p.17', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(141, 'BG-TRA-01', NULL, 'T1', 'Transports dispatching system', 'Introduction of transport dispatching system for cargo', 'A considerable part of the return trips of freight vehicles is done without cargo. Both from an economic and environmental point of view, this is not very efficient. The implementation of central information dispatching system for the loads will lead to a decrease of empty or semiloaded return trips of Lorries and trains.', '2007', '2008', NULL, NULL, '30', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BG-NC4, p.58, 60, BG-subMM 07, p.19', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(142, 'BG-TRA-02', NULL, 'T2', 'Railway transport power dispatching system', 'Introduction of railway transport power dispatching system', 'Supply of electricity to the electrified sections of the railway network and reduction of electricity losses require introduction of an automated system for collecting information and dispatching control. It will lead to an increase of the security of the electricity supply and, as a consequence,<br />to a decrease of the emissions.', '2005', '2008', NULL, NULL, '90', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BG-NC4, p.58, 60, BG-subMM 07, p.20', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(143, 'BG-TRA-03', NULL, 'T3', 'Modernization of Railways', 'Modernization', 'The consumption of residual oil and electricity for transportation of one cargo unit or passenger at a given distance is much lowers that in the road transportation. There are technical solutions that can lead, if applied, to additional reduction of the consumption of oil and electricity. The proposed measures have direct and indirect effects on the increase of the passengers and load flows in the railway transport as well as on GHG emissions reduction.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '40', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BG-NC4, p.58/59/60, BG-subMM 07, p.20', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(144, 'BG-TRA-04', NULL, 'T4', 'Improving the public transportation, reducing transportation flows in cities and renewing the transport park', 'Improvement of public transport and reduction of transportation flows in cities', 'The improvement of public transportation and the reduction of private transportation in cities might contribute to lower GHG emissions from transportation. An increasing share of public transport in total transportation activities can however only is reached when policies are<br />accompanied with instruments which make the use of cars less attractive (e.g. increased fuel or road taxes, introduction of parking taxes, introduction of car-free zones in city centres). The strengthening of the control and quality in the accomplishment of the periodical technical<br />examinations will lead to the renewing of the transport park.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'not valued', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BG-NC4, p.59/60, BG-subMM 07, p.20/21', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(145, 'BG-TRA-05', NULL, 'T5', 'Introduction of biofuels', 'Increased use of biofuels', 'The implementation of this measure will lead to reduction of GHG emissions. Bulgaria has the possibility to produce a substantial amount of biomass. Production of biofuels has a positive effect on employment in the agricultural sector.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'not valued', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BG-NC4, p.59/60, BG-subMM 07, p.21', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(146, 'BG-AGR-01', NULL, 'A1', 'Manure management', 'Manure management', 'Manure is one of the most considerable methane sources in agriculture. The modern manure management practices are not applied in Bulgaria.<br />In liquid manure management are used transportation tanks, underground disposal at cattlebreeding farms and poultry-farming sites, separation of manure into liquid and solid fraction at pig-breeding farms, etc.', '2005', '2008', NULL, NULL, '70', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BG-NC4, p.59/61, BG-subMM 07, p.23', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(147, 'BG-AGR-02', NULL, 'A2', 'Fertilization and irrigation', 'Improving fertilization practices<br />Elaboration of irrigation technologies aiming at water use reduction', 'During the last years fertilization was conducted in an uncontrolled manner. The amounts of nitrous fertilizers applied to soils often exceeded the recommended ones. The requirements for quality of production and lower prime costs grew strict due to expanded import of agricultural<br />goods from the neighbouring countries.', '2005', '2008', NULL, NULL, '170', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BG-NC4, p.59/61, BG-subMM 07, p.23/24', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(148, 'BG-WAM-01', NULL, 'W1', 'Utilization of the captured methane for production of electricity', 'Utilization of captured methane for production of electricity', 'At this moment the energy generated during the flaring of the captured methane is not utilized. The captured methane can be utilized in piston gas motors where electricity is generated. Because of the presence of mixtures in methane, a comparatively low efficiency is accepted for<br />this type of machines (30 %). The received electrical energy from the burning of one ton captured methane will be about 4.2 MWh under the assumption that the diesel-generators operate 6 000 hours per year. This utilization of equipment for electricity production means an installed<br />capacity of 19,517 kW.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '90', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BG-NC4, p.60/61, BG-subMM 07, p.25', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(149, 'BG-CRS-01', NULL, NULL, 'Act amending the Environmental Protection Act', NULL, 'Act amending the Environmental Protection Act concerning the transposition of Directive 2003/87/EC of the European Parliament and of the Council establishing a scheme for greenhouse gas emission allowance trading within the Community (published in State Gazette, No.77/27.09.2005)', '2005', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BG-NC4, p.49/50', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(150, 'BG-CRS-02', NULL, NULL, 'Ratification act of Bilateral Cooperation Agreements', NULL, 'Five Ratification acts of Bilateral Cooperation Agreements in the field of Joint Implementation Projects under the Kyoto Protocol, respectively with Netherlands, Austria, Switzerland, Denmark, World Bank&#39;s Prototype Carbon Fund, Sweden.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BG-NC4, p.50', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(151, 'CY-CRS-01', NULL, '1', 'Campaigns for promoting renewable energy sources (RES) and rational use of energy (RUE)', 'Increase of electricity generation from RES, to reach 6% of the total electricity consumption in 2010, 9% in 2015 and 12% in 2020.', 'Measures and actions taken (but not yet fully implemented) at national level for the promotion of RES and RUE, include &lsquo;SAVEnergy&rsquo; exhibition, organising public hearings and RES info days, school presentations to promote &ldquo;energy awareness&rdquo;, introduction of awards for the households with the best record in energy saving and promotion of the creation of a theme park.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CY-0703 projections_DRAFT, p.3', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(152, 'CY-CRS-02', NULL, '2', 'Enhanced application procedures for investment in RES and RUE', 'Increase of electricity generation from RES, to reach 6% of the total electricity consumption in 2010, 9% in 2015 and 12% in 2020.', '? Introduction of simpler and faster procedures for submitting and evaluating applications;<br />? In order to facilitate applications and speed up the procedures for licenses and applications the Council of Ministers has recently approved the introduction of the &ldquo;ONE STOP SHOP&rdquo; for large investments in RES.<br />? Increase in the subsidy intensity and the maximum amount of grant in many categories of the scheme.<br />? Broadening the range of eligible applicants for thermal insulation (Construction companies are now eligible applicants)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CY-0703 projections_DRAFT, p.3', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(153, 'CY-ENS-01', NULL, '3', 'Construction of energy centre', 'Import of liquefied natural gas', 'Plans to construct an Energy Centre that would allow the import of liquefied natural gas (LNG). The planned Energy Centre (through which liquefied natural gas will be available to the energy sector and more widely) may result in a significant reduction in CO2 emissions, but these developments are too uncertain to quantify at present', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CY-0703 projections_DRAFT, p.5', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(154, 'CY-ENS-02', NULL, '4', 'Combined cycle gas turbine', 'Increase use of natural gas', 'Plans by Electricity Authority of Cyprus to construct additional combined cycle gas turbine (CCGT) units to be fuelled by natural gas', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CY-0703 projections_DRAFT, p.5', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(155, 'CY-ENS-03', NULL, '5', 'Construction of generation plants using natural gas', 'Increase use of natural gas', 'Plans by other companies to construct generation plants that would compete with Electricity Authority of Cyprus, again using natural gas as a fuel.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CY-0703 projections_DRAFT, p.5', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(156, 'CY-ENS-04', NULL, '6', 'Use of natural gas in power plants', 'Increase use of natural gas', 'All power plants to be constructed after 2012 will be using natural gas', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CY-0703 projections_DRAFT, p.5', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(157, 'CY-ENS-05', NULL, '7', 'Use of natural gas in Vassilio power station', 'Increase use of natural gas', 'The 4th unit of Vassiliko power station whose construction has started will be using natural gas.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CY-0703 projections_DRAFT, p.5', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(158, 'CY-ENS-06', NULL, '8', 'Decommissioning of Moni and Dekelia power units', 'Increase use of natural gas', 'Decommissioning of Moni and Dekelia power units (after 2012) and replacement by units using natural gas.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CY-0703 projections_DRAFT, p.5', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(159, 'CY-ENS-07', NULL, '9', 'Support Scheme for the promotion of RES and Energy Conservation', 'Promotion of biomass use for heating and electricity production', 'A Support Scheme for the promotion of RES and Energy Conservation, which includes the provision of grants on the investment for production of biofuels, utilization of biomass for heating/cooling, tele-heating/ tele-cooling and the co-generation from biomass.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CY-0703 projections_DRAFT, p.6', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(160, 'CY-ENS-08', NULL, '10', 'New support scheme for electricity generation from biomass', 'Promotion of biomass use for heating and electricity production', 'A new support scheme for electricity generation from biomass has just been approved. The scheme for electricity generation from biomass is more generous and provides operational grant (Feed-in purchase price per KWh) up to 12.38 euro cents per KWh depending upon the technology used and raw biomass.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CY-0703 projections_DRAFT, p.6', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(161, 'CY-ENC-01', NULL, '11', 'Grant sheme', 'Reduction of the total energy consumption by 1% per annum', 'The new 2004 grant scheme includes two categories of which Category A is Energy conservation, and refers to investments which aim at energy conservation as well as the installation of combined heat and power. Energy conservation investments are defined as investments on energy conservation systems which can achieve at least 10% energy saving out of the total energy consumption.<br />Energy efficiency is enhanced by measures such as introduction of new technologies and promotion of proper maintenance of the systems used in industries. Up to June 2006, 1747 applications of thermal insulations have been approved, corresponding to an investment (on behalf of the Republic of Cyprus) of CYP&pound;1.5 million. The corresponding annual reduction in conventional fuel consumption corresponds to 2800 tonnes (0.035%). According to data of the Energy Service (June 2006), energy saving projects have been granted ranging from 15.5% to 63% reduction in energy consumption.', '2004', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CY-0703 projections_DRAFT, p.6', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(162, 'CY-ENC-02', NULL, '12', 'Reduction of losses from the transfer and distribution system', 'Reduction of the total energy consumption by 1% per annum', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CY-0703 projections_DRAFT, p.6', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(163, 'CY-ENC-03', NULL, '13', 'Improvement of the thermal behaviour of buildings in the residential sector', 'Reduce energy consumption in the residential and tertiary sector', 'This measure implies: (a) formulation and mandatory - after 2007 - implementation of a space heating regulation for all new buildings in the residential sector and (b) roof insulation in buildings constructed before 2007, so that 50% of those buildings in 2010 and 100% of those buildings in 2020 end-up in having such an insulation.', '2007', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CY-0703 projections_DRAFT, p.7', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(164, 'CY-ENC-04', NULL, '14', 'Improvement of the thermal behaviour of buildings in the tertiary sector', 'Reduce energy consumption in the residential and tertiary sector', 'This measure implies formulation and mandatory - after 2007 - implementation of a space heating regulation for all new buildings in the tertiary sector and the insulation of roof/openings in buildings constructed before 2007. The penetration rate of the measure is 60% of buildings in the public sector and 50% of buildings in the sector of services by 2010, while in 2020 the measure will cover all buildings.', '2007', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CY-0703 projections_DRAFT, p.7', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(165, 'CY-ENC-05', NULL, '15', 'Maintenance of central heating boilers', 'Reduce energy consumption in the residential and tertiary sector', 'The maintenance of central heating boilers on an annual basis could lead to an improvement of their performance up to 10%, depending on the boiler&rsquo;s condition before its maintenance. The penetration rate of the measure is 60% (in 2010) and 100% (in 2020) of the existing boilers of the residential and tertiary sector.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CY-0703 projections_DRAFT, p.7', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(166, 'CY-ENC-06', NULL, '16', 'Replacement of central heating boilers', 'Reduce energy consumption in the residential and tertiary sector', 'Replacement of old boilers with new ones with a high-energy performance. The penetration rate of the measure is 25% for 2010 and to 50% for 2020 of the existing central heating boilers in the residential sector, while the penetration rate in the public sector is 50% and 75% respectively.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CY-0703 projections_DRAFT, p.7', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(167, 'CY-ENC-07', NULL, '17', 'Use of high efficiency air conditioning systems', 'Reduce energy consumption in the residential and tertiary sector', 'The energy conservation by unit is estimated approximately to 20%. The penetration rate of new, energy-efficient units, is 75% in 2010 and 100% in 2020 of the total installed units in the residential and tertiary sector.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CY-0703 projections_DRAFT, p.7', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(168, 'CY-ENC-08', NULL, '18', 'Use of high efficiency electric appliances', 'Reduce energy consumption in the residential and tertiary sector', 'The penetration of energy-efficient electric appliances (note: this measure applies to the residential sector only) is 75% in 2010 and 100% in 2020 of the total appliances.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CY-0703 projections_DRAFT, p.7', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(169, 'CY-ENC-09', NULL, '19', 'Use of energy-efficient lighting bulbs', 'Reduce energy consumption in the residential and tertiary sector', 'The penetration rate is 80% (in 2010) and 100% (in 2020) of the conventional lighting bulbs in the residential and tertiary sector.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CY-0703 projections_DRAFT, p.7', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
