(255, 'UK-AGR-10', NULL, '64', 'Rural development', 'Enable land managers and other businesses in rural communities to mitigate and adapt to climate change', 'The England Rural Development Programme  (the mechanism for delivering the current EU Rural Development Regulation (RDR) in England) tackles climate change issues directly, for example through the Energy Crops Scheme, and less directly through measures under existing agri-environment schemes. The new EU RDR for the period 2007-13 is currently being negotiated.  Discussions on the Welsh Rural Development Plan 2007-2013 are also underway.<br />In Scotland, the Scottish Rural Development Plan  will include measures to enable land managers and other businesses in rural communities to mitigate and adapt to climate change. A pilot scheme for farmers growing crops for biofuel has also been announced.  Following new research on soils Ministers have decided to develop a new Scottish Soils Strategy, to be published in 2007. The preservation and enhancement of carbon in soils will be a key consideration in the strategy. A Soil Monitoring Network is also being developed which will enable any changes in the carbon stored in soils to be monitored.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'GB subMM19_03_07, p.35', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(256, 'UK-AGR-11', NULL, '65', 'Environmental stewardship', 'Reduce emissions and increase sequestration in agriculture', 'Environmental Stewardship, which has three different elements (launched March 2005) will replace the existing agri-environment schemes .  Entry Level Stewardship (ELS) is expected to cover 70 per cent of farmland by 2008.  Some elements of farmer action under ELS, such as the management of grassland with reduced fertilizer inputs and the establishment of unfertilized grass margins will assist in reducing emissions and increasing sequestration, though the scale of the benefit may be quite small.  In 2007, there will be a review of progress for ELS and, in particular, consideration will be given to adding an explicit scheme objective for climate change mitigation and adaptation.  <br />There are three tiers of agri-environment schemes in Wales.  The Assembly Government will be carrying out a review of the schemes as part of its axis II review later in 2007 and this will be an opportunity to increase the focus on addressing climate change &ndash; both mitigation and adaptation &ndash; through the schemes.<br />The Organic ELS should have a positive effect on climate change mitigation, by encouraging more widespread use of organic farming, which does not use energy-intensive artificial fertilizers. Higher Level Stewardship, along with the existing Countryside Stewardship (CSS) and Environmentally Sensitive Areas (ESAs) should have a significant local effect by promoting less intensive farming, with lower fertilizer inputs and reduced stocking rates. These effects are likely to be most marked in the current ESA areas where uptake of such agreements is already high.  At a national scale however, it is unlikely that such agreements will cover more than about 20 per cent of farmland in the near future.', '2005', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'GB subMM19_03_07, p.35', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(257, 'UK-AGR-12', NULL, '66', 'Integrated Pollution Prevention and Control (IPPC)', 'Reduction of emissions from agriculture', 'The UK must implement the Integrated Pollution Prevention and Control Directive between 1999 and 2007 . This will extend the pollution control regime to intensive pig and poultry units.  Existing intensive livestock units above a certain threshold are required to apply for a permit between November 2006 and January 2007.  The guidance notes governing the permitting process for such installations focus on, amongst other things, delivering improvements in energy efficiency and reductions in diffuse nitrogen emissions. Requirements for better nutrient management should give rise to a reduction in nitrous oxide losses. The guidance can be revised over time and as knowledge improves, specific recommendations for controlling nitrous oxide could be developed.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'GB subMM19_03_07, p.39', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(258, 'UK-AGR-13', NULL, '67', 'Catchment Sensitive Farming (CSF)', 'Promote the more efficient use of chemical and organic fertilizers leading to a reduction in overall inputs', 'The Government is promoting catchment-sensitive farming  as a response to the challenge of diffuse water pollution from agriculture (DWPA). This will promote the more efficient use of chemical and organic fertilizers leading to a reduction in overall inputs, and also contributing to a reduction in the level of nitrous oxide emissions.  However, given current uncertainties over the scale and nature of the DWPA in England, and the success of measures that might be employed to tackle it, it is difficult at this stage to determine the extent to which it will impact on nitrous oxide emissions.<br />Under the Nitrates Directive, which requires EU Member States to ensure farmers follow an Action Programme of measures to reduce nitrate pollution.  The UK Government has designated 55 per cent of England as a Nitrate Vulnerable Zone (NVZ) and has introduced an Action Programme of measures to control the use of fertilizers and livestock manures in this area.  By requiring that these substances be applied to land at times, and in amounts, most likely to maximize plant nitrogen uptake and reduce nitrate leaching, these measures are expected to reduce nitrous oxides emissions to the atmosphere and the use of energy-intensive artificial fertilizer in some areas.  The scale of change and impact on nitrous oxide emissions has not yet been quantified.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'GB subMM19_03_07, p.39/40', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(259, 'UK-WAM-01', NULL, '68', 'Waste management', 'Reduce emissions from waste', 'Landfill methane emissions in the UK are falling, mainly because of increased collection of landfill gas for energy recovery and environmental control. There are also a number of Government policies aimed at reducing land filling of biodegradable waste. For example, the landfill tax was raised &pound;21 per tonne of active waste for the year 2006/07 to encourage more sustainable management of waste that would otherwise be land filled. The UK Government announced in 2003 that the tax would increase by at least &pound;3 per tonne of active waste per year from 2005-06 until it reached a level of &pound;35 per tonne. The Chancellor&#39;s 2006 Pre-Budget Report announced that the Government will consider whether the standard rate of landfill tax needs to increase more steeply from 2008 onwards, or go beyond &pound;35 per tonne. In addition, the Waste Strategy 2000 for England (currently under review following a consultation document in 2006) and the corresponding strategies for Scotland, Wales and Northern Ireland set out a range of other policies designed to reduce waste production and recover value from waste that is produced through reuse, recycling/composting and energy recovery. The Wales Waste Strategy  is in place and is being reviewed this year. <br />The implementation of the European Community&rsquo;s Landfill Directive  will have a significant effect on emissions because it imposes strict engineering requirements on landfills.  It also requires landfill gas (methane) to be collected from all landfills receiving biodegradable waste and the landfill gas to be treated and used.  If the gas collected cannot be used to produce energy, it must be flared.  The Landfill Directive further imposes limits on the amount of biodegradable municipal waste (BMW) that can be land filled.The Landfill Directive further imposes limits on the amount of biodegradable municipal waste (BMW) that can be land filled. The reduction targets (based on the amount of waste produced in 1995) are challenging; they are: <br />&bull; By 2010 to reduce the amount of BMW going to landfill to 75 per cent of that produced in 1995;<br />&bull; By 2010 to reduce the amount of BMW going to landfill to 50 per cent of that produced in 1995; and<br />&bull; By 2020 to reduce the amount of BMW going to landfill to 35 per cent of that produced in 1995<br />These targets are legally binding and the UK is committed to meeting them. England is making good progress towards meeting the 2010 targets.  <br />In England, the Government introduced on 1 April 2005 a Landfill Allowances Trading Scheme (LATS)  that restricts the amount of biodegradable municipal waste that can be land filled by local authorities. In the first year of LATS (2005/06), an estimated 12.4 million tones of biodegradable municipal waste was land filled in England.  This is 83 per cent of the total amount land filled in 1995.  The limit in 2010 is 11.5 million tones. The devolved administrations have introduced their own permit schemes with Scotland planning to join the LATS trading element from 2008.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'GB subMM19_03_07, p.15/16', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(260, 'CZ-CRS-806a', NULL, '1', 'National Programme to Abate the Climate Change Impacts in the CR', 'Reduction of greenhouse gas emissions and ensuring of meeting the obligations resulting from Kyoto protocol', 'Framework document defining tasks for individual ministries in order to reach targets of Kyoto protocol', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '&quot;No Measures&quot;', 'Framework measure', NULL, 'N/A', 'All', NULL, 'CZ Submission 07', 'Reduced energy consumption', NULL, NULL, 'N/A', NULL, NULL),
(261, 'CZ-CRS-01', NULL, '2', 'Clean air act', 'Reducing emissions from air pollutants', 'Complex law covering protection of air from pollutants, ozone layer protection and protection of the climate system. The law introduces National programme for abatement of climate change of Earth. The law sets among other things emission bounds and reduction targets and deadlines for substances influencing the climate system. There is also an obligation of operators of large plants above 5 MW to keep emission bounds and to submit data on substances influencing climate system.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '&quot;No Measures&quot;', 'Framework measure', NULL, 'N/A', '07.01.2008', NULL, 'CZ Submission 07', 'Reduced energy consumption', NULL, NULL, 'N/A', NULL, NULL),
(262, 'CZ-ENS-01', NULL, '3', 'Energy act', 'The law establishes the obligation of electricity distributors to buy electricity from combined heat and power plants and from renewable energy sources. It also opens the market with electricity.', 'The Act No. 258/2000 Coll. lays down the right of operators of installations for combined production of electricity and heat and installations for use of renewable energy sources and waste combustion to preferential access to the distribution networks. If the basic technical conditions are met, the operators of the distribution networks are obliged to purchase electricity and heat energy originating from renewable energy sources and combined production of heat and electricity.', '2001', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '&quot;No Measures&quot;', 'Framework measure', NULL, 'N/A', '07.01.2008', NULL, 'CZ Submission 07', 'Reduced energy consumption', NULL, NULL, 'N/A', NULL, NULL),
(263, 'CZ-ENS-02', NULL, '4', 'Energy management act', 'Basic law defining rules for efficient production and use of energy.', 'This law covers more topics: 1. Sets the obligation for regional authorities to elaborate Regional energy concept which should define rules for efficient use of energe and for introduction of RES. 2. Establishes the National programme for effective use of energy and utilisation of renewable and secondary energy sources. 3. Defines minimal efficiencies for electricity and heat production, maximum losses for energy transmission and distribution and sets minimal technical requirements for buildings and appliances. 4. Defines measures for support of RES. 5. Introduces labeling of appliances. 6. Sets obligation to perform energy audits of defined categories of buildings.', '2001', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '&quot;No Measures&quot;', 'Defines minimal efficiencies for power and heat production', NULL, 'N/A', '07.01.2008', NULL, 'CZ Submission 07', 'Reduced energy consumption', NULL, NULL, 'N/A', NULL, NULL),
(264, 'CZ-CRS-02', NULL, '5', 'Joint Implementation', 'Realisation of Kyoto Protocol Mechanisms', 'Reduction of CO2 emission using flexible mechanisms within Kyoto protocol', NULL, NULL, '1071', NULL, '1562', NULL, '1684', NULL, NULL, NULL, '7195', '&quot;No Measures&quot;', 'Foreign investments', NULL, 'From list of approved actions.', '4', NULL, 'CZ Submission 07', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, 'N/A', NULL, NULL),
(265, 'CZ-CRS-03', NULL, '6', 'National programme for effective use of energy and utilisation of renewable and secondary energy sources', 'Decrease energy consumption and increase use of RES', 'National Programme is a document expressing targets of energy consumption decrease and RES and secondary energy sources utilisation consistently with economic and social needs, sustainable development and environment protection.The National Programme is oriented to state and municipal sphere, enterprises, households and non-governmental organisations. It represents a framework for the State programme for support of energy savings and use of renewable energy sources.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '&quot;No Measures&quot;', 'Framework measure', NULL, 'N/A', '07.04.2008', NULL, 'CZ Submission 07', 'Reduced energy consumption', NULL, NULL, 'N/A', NULL, NULL),
(266, 'CZ-CRS-806b', NULL, '7', 'Integrated national programme for emission reduction in the Czech Republic', 'Complex programme aimed at meeting of national emission bounds of SO2, NOX, VOC and ammonia in 2010.', 'The main targets of the programme are: 1. meeting of national emission bounds of SO2, NOX, VOC and ammonia in 2010, 2. decrease emissions of pollutants (including ozone precursors) for which imission limits are exceeded, 3. keeping low emission levels for pollutants for which imission limits are not excceded, 4. reaching targets for acidification, human health and vegetation by year 2020.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '&quot;No Measures&quot;', 'Framework measure', NULL, 'N/A', '07.01.2008', NULL, 'CZ Submission 07', 'Reduced energy consumption, measures aimed directly at lower emissions', NULL, NULL, 'N/A', NULL, NULL),
(267, 'CZ-ENC-03', NULL, '8', 'State programme for support of energy savings and use of renewable energy sources - Part A', 'Decreasing the energy intensity of the economy, savings in energy production materials and minimization of the burdening of the environment by emissions and decreasing emissions of greenhouse gases', 'The support covers mainyl: 1. Energy efficiency projects in public and living buildings, 2. RES and secondary energy projects, 3.Combined heat and power generation, 4. Energy audits, 5. Energy performance contracting projects, 6. Use of modern technologies and materials for improved energy efficiency, 7. Projects of modernisation of energy producingg and distributing facilities, 8. Elaboration of energy concepts of cities, municipalities and living agglomerations, 9. Energy savings in industry, transport and agriculture, 10. Projects decreasing emissions of GHG, 11. Consulting, education and advertisment for efficient energy use.', '1999', NULL, '143', NULL, '198', NULL, '200', NULL, NULL, NULL, '901,67', '&quot;No Measures&quot;', 'Investment subsidies, education, information', NULL, 'Annual evaluations of the programme', '07.04.2008', NULL, 'CZ Submission 07', 'Reduced energy consumption', NULL, NULL, 'Investment subsidies', NULL, NULL),
(268, 'CZ-ENC-04', NULL, '9', 'State programme for support of energy savings and use of renewable energy sources - Part B', 'Decreasing the energy intensity of the economy, savings in energy production materials and minimization of the burdening of the environment by emissions and decreasing emissions of greenhouse gases', 'The renewable energy segment (RES) has been supported by the State Environmental Fund since 1999 on the basis of the anually announced &ldquo;State programme in support of the energy savings and utilisation of renewable energy sources &ndash; part B&rdquo;. Aid is provided, depending on the available financial resources, mainly for projects aimed at the construction of heating and water warming systems via RES, in community buildings, in the objects of a tertiary sphere and family houses, further for the demonstration installations of photothermic and photovoltaic systems in schools, as well as for projects of non-investment character (publications, seminars etc.). For reasons of the perpetually declining financial resources, the perspective is that in future, aid will be provided for the projects that are less financially demanding. In the case of bigger projects, aid will be possible to be drawn from some of the European structural funds that are currently under preparation.', '1999', NULL, '128', NULL, '101', NULL, '100', NULL, NULL, NULL, '548,33', '&quot;No Measures&quot;', 'Investment subsidies, education, information', NULL, 'Annual evaluations of the programme', '07.04.2008', NULL, 'CZ Submission 07', 'Reduced energy consumption', NULL, NULL, 'Investment subsidies', NULL, NULL),
(269, 'CZ-ENS-400', NULL, '10', 'Support from the State Environmental Fund in the field of air protection', 'This programme aims primarily at air protection and covers fuel switch at small and medium plants, combined heat and power production and development of energy infrastructure of small municipalities.', 'The air protection segment is focused on reductions in the emissions of pollutants and greenhouse gases, resulting mainly from the replacement of fuels in combustion sources, and from energy-saving solutions. The emphasis is on providing aid for the preparation of local programmes for emissions and ground level pollutant reductions in areas with worsened air quality. As regards investment projects having direct impact on the air quality, aid is primarily granted to measures linked up with the facilities in operation under community services.', NULL, NULL, '617', NULL, '1000', NULL, '1000', NULL, NULL, NULL, '4361,67', '&quot;No Measures&quot;', 'Investment subsidies, education, information', NULL, 'Annual evaluations of the programme', '07.04.2008', NULL, 'CZ Submission 07', 'Reduced energy consumption, measures aimed directly at lower emissions', NULL, NULL, 'Investment subsidies', NULL, NULL),
(270, 'CZ-ENC-01', NULL, '11', 'GEF Efficient lighting initiative', 'Support of  accelerated introduction of energy efficient lighting to newly established markets.', 'Reduction of GHG emissions by accelerated introduction of energy efficient technologies to newly established markets. The activities were oriented to public sestor, housholds and public lighting.', NULL, NULL, '425', NULL, '425', NULL, '425', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2125', '&quot;No Measures&quot;', 'Finatial support, information, education', NULL, 'Ex ante evaluation of the programme', '06.04.2008', NULL, 'CZ Submission 07', 'Reduction of electricity consumption', NULL, NULL, 'Investment subsidies', NULL, NULL),
(271, 'CZ-ENC-02', NULL, '12', 'Programme for support of reconstruction and revitalisation of pannel houses', 'Support to reconstruction, revitalisation and modernisation of pannel buildings. From 2007 the support will be obtained from the Integrated Operational Programm.', 'The program aims at retrofit, reconstruction and modernisation of more than 1.1 million pannel houses.The program offers direct subsidies, contributions to loan interest and bank guarantees of loans. The underdevelopped regions and regions with damaged environment are preferred. The support covers thermal insulation of buildings, heating systems, heat and hot water distribution and introduction of RES.', '2000', NULL, '18,2', NULL, '27,5', NULL, '30,7', NULL, NULL, NULL, '127,33', '&quot;No Measures&quot;', 'Subsidies of credit interest,  bank guaramtees for credits for buildings renovation', NULL, 'Estimated from number of renovated houses', '06.04.2008', NULL, 'CZ Submission 07', 'Reduction of energy consumption', NULL, NULL, 'Credit interest subsidies, bank guarantees', NULL, NULL),
(272, 'CZ-ENC-06', NULL, '13', 'Credits obtained by municipalities for support of reconstruction and modernisation of living houses', 'The main aim of the measure is to improve technical status of municipal houses, which leads also to energy and consequently CO2 emission savings', 'Long-term (10 years) low-interest (3 %) credits which municipalities can obtain in order to improve status of municipal living houses', NULL, NULL, '18,2', NULL, '43,2', NULL, '62,2', NULL, NULL, NULL, '206', '&quot;No Measures&quot;', 'Lon-term cheap credits for buildings renovation.', NULL, 'Estimated from number of renovated houses', '06.04.2008', NULL, 'CZ Submission 07', 'Reduction of energy consumption', NULL, NULL, 'Credit interest subsidies', NULL, NULL),
(273, 'CZ-TRA-05', NULL, '14', 'Portfolio of measures in the transport sector', 'Decrease of air pollutants', 'Continually reslised measures aimed mainly at decrease of air pollutions. The key measures in transport are: 1. Development and introduction of transport means and transport fuels for road, rail, water and air transport fulfilling european emission standards, 2. State programme for support of energy savings and use of renewable energy sources, 3. Programme of support to renewal of vehicles in public city transport and 4. Programme MARCO POLO dealing with reduction of traffic jams.', NULL, NULL, '9,3', NULL, '29,3', NULL, '41,8', NULL, NULL, NULL, '134', '&quot;No Measures&quot;', 'Increased energy efficiency, introduction of RES, preference of public transport modes, more fluent transport', NULL, 'Evaluation performed by the Ministry of trransport', '2', NULL, 'CZ Submission 07', 'Reduction of energy consumption', NULL, NULL, 'Investment subsidies', NULL, NULL),
(274, 'CZ-IND-01', NULL, '15', 'Act on IPPC', 'Preventing all kinds of pollution', 'The law aims at prevention of all kinds of pollution. It covers more than 850 enterprises with 1400 facilities. Implementation of the EU directive 96/61/EC on Integrated Pollution Prevention and Control', '2003', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '&quot;No Measures&quot;', 'Improved energy efficiency', NULL, 'N/A', '4', NULL, 'CZ Submission 07', 'Reduced energy consumption, measures aimed directly at lower emissions', NULL, NULL, 'N/A', NULL, NULL),
(275, 'CZ-LUC-01', NULL, '16', 'Support for aforrestation of non-utilised agricultural areas', 'The objective of the measure is to decrease CH4 and N2O emissions from non-utilised agricultural soils an do increase absorption of CO2 in forest areas.', 'State support to conversion of non-utilised agricultural and other areas into forests. The increase of forrest arreas is from 1990 permanently higher than decrease due tu changes of forests into other areas.', NULL, NULL, '84', NULL, '84', NULL, '84', NULL, NULL, NULL, '420', '&quot;No Measures&quot;', 'Increased stock of bliving biomass.', NULL, 'Evaluation performed by the Ministry of agriculture', 'N/A', NULL, 'CZ Submission 07', 'neutral impact', NULL, NULL, 'Investment subsidies', NULL, NULL),
(276, 'CZ-WAM-01', NULL, '17', 'Act on packaging and wastes', 'Harmonisation of the Czech legislation with the EU legislation - (1) increase share of recycled wastes to 55 % of all produced wastes  in 2012 and increase utilisation of munisipal wastes to 50 % in 2010 relative to 2000; (2) decrease the mass share of landfilled wastes by 20 % in 2010 relative to 2000 with an outlook of further gradual decrease; (3) decrease the share of landfilled biodegradable municipal wastes to 75 % in 2010, 50 % in 2013 and 35 % in 2020 relative to amount of biodegradable wastes produced in 1995.', 'The law harmonises the Czech legislation with EU directive 99/31/ES. It defines targets for waste recycling and for use of biodegradable wastes.', '2002', NULL, NULL, NULL, '258', NULL, '886', NULL, NULL, NULL, '1906,67', '&quot;No Measures&quot;', 'Reduced amount of biologically degradable wastes disposed to landfills', NULL, 'Calculation from waste generation projection using IPCC methodology', '10', NULL, 'CZ Submission 07', 'neutral impact', NULL, NULL, 'N/A', NULL, NULL),
(277, 'CZ-WAM-02', NULL, '18', 'Utilisation of sewage gas and landfill gas', 'Decreasing emissions of methane from landfills and waste water treatment plants', 'Realisation of projects for energy use of sewage gas and landfill gas. The program is concerned with the use of methane formed in waste landfills and in decomposition of waste water treatment plant sludges. In Article 11, Decree No. 383/2001 Coll., on details of waste management, as amended, stipulates the technical requirements on waste landfills and the conditions for operation and closing of landfills. These conditions are considered to be fulfilled if they correspond to the technical standards specified in this Article. Technical standard CSN 83 8034, Waste Landfilling &ndash; Degasification of Landfills, stipulates the thresholds according to the mean methane concentration, above which it is necessary to utilize or remove landfill gases.', '1998', NULL, '69', NULL, '76', NULL, '80', NULL, NULL, NULL, '375', '&quot;No Measures&quot;', 'Replacement of fossil fuels using methane for energy production', NULL, 'Estimate from number of landfills and sewage plants.', '10', NULL, 'CZ Submission 07', 'neutral impact', NULL, NULL, 'N/A', NULL, NULL),
(278, 'CZ-CRS-802', NULL, '19', 'National allocation plan', 'Realisation of the EU directive 2003/87/EC on system of emission trading in the period 2005 - 2007.', 'The national allocation plan for years 2005 - 2007  covers 436 industrial facilities and the limit amounts 97,6 Gg CO2 per year.', '2005', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '&quot;No Measures&quot;', 'Economically enforced limit of emissions', NULL, 'Calculation using EFOM/ENV model', '4, 7', NULL, 'CZ Submission 07', 'Reduction of energy consumption', NULL, NULL, 'N/A', NULL, NULL),
(279, 'CZ-CRS-803', NULL, '20', 'National allocation plan II', 'Realisation of the EU directive 2003/87/EC on system of emission trading in the period 2008 - 2012', 'The asked allocation of permits for years 2008 - 2012   amounts 101,9 Gg CO2 per year. The final value is likely to be lower.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2523', NULL, '1642', NULL, NULL, NULL, '6941,67', '&quot;With Measures&quot;', 'Economically enforced limit of emissions', NULL, 'Calculation using EFOM/ENV model', '4, 7', NULL, 'CZ Submission 07', 'Reduction of energy consumption', NULL, NULL, 'N/A', NULL, NULL),
(280, 'CZ-ENS-05', NULL, '21', 'Preferential feed-in tariffs for electricity produced from renewable energy sources', 'Increase use of RES in power generation', 'This is the principal measure for support of RES use in power generation. The law defines minimal feed-in tariffs for electricity produced from RES and garantees its long-term validity. The Act on support of utilisation of RES sets preferential feed-in tariffs for electricity produced from RES and garantees their  validity for 15 years.', '2000', NULL, NULL, NULL, '985', NULL, '1350', NULL, NULL, NULL, '3891,67', '&quot;No Measures&quot;', 'Long-term guarantee for preferential feed-in electricity tariffs', NULL, 'Calculation using EFOM/ENV model', '4, 7', NULL, 'CZ Submission 07', 'Decreased use of fossil fuels, however use of biomass can lead to increase of non GHGs', NULL, NULL, 'N/A', NULL, NULL),
(281, 'CZ-ENS-803', NULL, '22', 'Ecological tax reform', 'Support for environmentally sound fuels and means of producing electricity and, on the other hand, putting at a disadvantage fuels and means of producing electricity that are significant sources of emissions of greenhouse gases and other pollutants.', 'Implementation of the EU directive 2003/96/ES on minimal excise tax of energy products and electricity. The final figure of this measure is not yet clear. The most likely variant is to adopt minimal requirements of the EU directove followed by stepwise increase of the ecological taxes, which will be compensated by decrease of income taxes for enetrprises.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1083', NULL, '2538', NULL, NULL, NULL, '6035', '&quot;With Measures&quot;', 'A kind of carbon tax.', NULL, 'Calculation using EFOM/ENV model', '4, 7', NULL, 'CZ Submission 07', 'Reduction of energy consumption', NULL, NULL, 'Fiscally neutral', NULL, NULL),
(282, 'CZ-ENC-05', NULL, '23', 'Directive on energy performance of buildings', 'Increase of energy efficiency of relevant buildings by 10 - 20 % is expected tu the year 2020.', 'Implementation of EU directive 2002/91/ES on energy performance of buildings. The directive defines methodology of calculation of energy efficiency of buildings, minimal requirements for new buildings, minimal requirements for larger existing buildings under reconstruction, energy certificates of buildings and obligatory inspections of boilers and heating and cooling systems. An increase of energy efficiency of relevant buildings by 10 - 20 % is expected tu the year 2020.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '305', NULL, '586', NULL, NULL, NULL, '1485', '&quot;No Measures&quot;', 'Minimal technical requirements for buildings, certification of buildings, regular inspections of boilers and air conditioning.', NULL, 'Estimation from number of houses and expected energy saving.', '06.04.2008', NULL, 'CZ Submission 07', 'Reduction of energy consumption', NULL, NULL, 'N/A', NULL, NULL),
(283, 'CZ-ENS-07', NULL, '24', 'Implementation of directive on co-generation', 'The measure increases energy efficiency and supply security by support of efficient combined heat and power generation', 'Implementation of the EU directive 2004/8/EC on co-generation.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '106', NULL, '301', NULL, NULL, NULL, '678,33', '&quot;No Measures&quot;', 'Long-term guarantee for preferential feed-in electricity tariffs', NULL, 'Calculation using EFOM/ENV model', '4, 7', NULL, 'CZ Submission 07', 'Reduced fuel consumption for power &amp; heat generation', NULL, NULL, 'N/A', NULL, NULL),
(284, 'CZ-IND-01a', NULL, '25', 'Operational programme industry and enterprise', 'Increase energy efficiency and use of renewable energy sources in industry', 'Operational Programme Industry and Enterprise is one of programmes for funding from EU structural funds. It is designed mainly for SMEs.As regards climate protection, the Measure 2.3 &quot;Decrease of energy intensity and higher utilisation of RES&quot; is important. The measure 2.3 contains two programmes - Energy savings and Renewable energy sources.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '185', NULL, '185', NULL, NULL, NULL, '616,67', '&quot;No Measures&quot;', 'Investment subsidies into energy efficiency and RES introduction', NULL, 'Evaluation of the programme', '4, 7', NULL, 'CZ Submission 07', 'Decrease of energy consumption, introduction of RES', NULL, NULL, 'Investment subsidies', NULL, NULL),
(285, 'CZ-IND-05', NULL, '26', 'Operational Programme Enterprise amd Innovation', 'Increased energy efficiency and higher share of renewable energy sources', 'Programme funded from EU structural funds aimed at increased energy efficiency and higher share of renewable energy sources. As regards climate protection, the Measure 3.1 &quot;Energy savings and renewable enrgy sources&quot; is important. The expected budget is 14 M&euro;.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '&quot;With Measures&quot;', 'Investment subsidies into energy efficiency and RES introduction', NULL, 'Optimal allocation of investments using EFOM/ENV model', '4, 7', NULL, 'CZ Submission 07', 'Decrease of energy consumption, introduction of RES', NULL, NULL, 'Investment subsidies', NULL, NULL),
(286, 'CZ-CRS-806', NULL, '27', 'Operational programme infrastructure', 'Reduction of the amount of emitted pollutants, improving pollution levels in the affected locations, improvement of the state of health of the population and condition of vegetation, reduction of GHG emissions', 'Programme financed from European Regional Development Fund. This programme aims at  protection and improvement of environment and improvement of transport infrastructure. <br />The most important is the Measure 3.3 - Improvement of air protection infrastructure wchich should lead to  decrease of pollutions, improvement of imission situation of exposed localities, improvement of health of population and of vegetation status, decrease of GHG emissions. The budget amounted 142 M&euro;.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '154', NULL, '154', NULL, NULL, NULL, '513,33', '&quot;No Measures&quot;', 'Investment subsidies into energy efficiency and RES introduction', NULL, 'Estimation from types number of projects.', '4, 7', NULL, 'CZ Submission 07', 'Reduction of energy consumption', NULL, NULL, 'Investment subsidies', NULL, NULL),
(287, 'CZ-CRS-807', NULL, '28', 'Operational programme environment', 'Improvement of environment and health of inhabitants', 'Programme funded from EU structural funds aimed at improvement of environment and health of inhabitants. Relevant priority axes are (2) - Air quality and decrease of emissions, (3) - Sustainable utilisation of enery and (4) - Improved waste management. The expected budget of CO2 emission related actions amounts about 860 M&euro;.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1506', NULL, '2323', NULL, NULL, NULL, '6381,67', '&quot;With Measures&quot;', 'Investment subsidies into energy efficiency and RES introduction', NULL, 'Optimal allocation of investments using EFOM/ENV model', '4, 7', NULL, 'CZ Submission 07', 'Reduction of energy consumption', NULL, NULL, 'Investment subsidies', NULL, NULL),
(288, 'CZ-TRA-06', NULL, '29', 'Operational Programme Transport', 'Overall improvement of transport infrastructure', 'Almost all programme tasks comtribute indirectly to saving of CO2 emissions increasing fluency of transport and increasing atractivity of public transport modes.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '849', NULL, '1600', NULL, NULL, NULL, '4081,67', '&quot;With Measures&quot;', 'Investment subsidies into transport infrastructure', NULL, 'Optimal allocation of investments using EFOM/ENV model', '4, 7', NULL, 'CZ Submission 07', 'Reduction of energy consumption', NULL, NULL, 'Investment subsidies', NULL, NULL),
