(346, 'DK-IND-04', NULL, 'BU-5', 'Enterprise sheme on HFCs', 'To reduce use and thus emissions of HFCs in the refrigeration sector', 'A general enterprise scheme will be administeret by the Danish Environmental Protection Agency. The total budget for the period 2004-2007 is DKK 144 mill. where the budget for 2005 amount to DKK 26.3 mill. The general objective of the enterprise scheme is to promote better conditions for environmental improvements in enterprises. In the general enterprise scheme is included a budget share of DKK 12 mill. 2005-2007 for projects with the development of alternatives to HFCs in the refrigerating business and the establishment of a knowledge center for HFC-free cooling as the objectives.', '2005', '2007', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'DenmarksUpdateOnPAMsAndProjections-15march 2007, p.65', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(347, 'DK-ENC-02', NULL, 'DO-1', 'Energy labelling of small and large buildings (incl. public sector and business)', 'Promotion of energy saving', 'Sales of small buildings (under 1500 m2 ) shall be accompanied with energy labels recommending the buyer how to achieve cost effective energy saving measures. The requirement for larger buildings is the establishment of an energy management plan containing an annual review of the building and its energy consumption and potential energy savings.', '1997', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'DenmarksUpdateOnPAMsAndProjections-15march 2007, p.80', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(348, 'DK-ENC-05', NULL, 'BU-7', 'Electricity Saving Trust &ndash; campaigns and A club to promote energy efficient appliances', 'Electricity savings, technology development and market promotion of energy efficient products and appliances.', 'The task of the Electricity Saving Trust includes th promotion of efficient electric appliances etc. and electric heating conversion in households and the public sector. The Trust are making use of measures such as national campaigns, efforts to influence the market, voluntary agreements and efforts to raise awareness on the consumption. The budget is approx. DKK 90-100 mill. annually.', '1996', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'DenmarksUpdateOnPAMsAndProjections-15march 2007, p.67', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(349, 'DK-ENC-06', NULL, 'DO-2', 'Energy labelling of electric appliances', 'To promote development and use of energy efficient appliances with the purpose of reducing energy consumption and CO2 emissions.', 'The EU energy labelling directives on household appliances are mandatory and all products under these directives must be labelled. The energy consumption of the appliances have to be shown in a scale from A to G, where A represent the lowest energy consumption.', '1992', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'DenmarksUpdateOnPAMsAndProjections-15march 2007, p.81', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(350, 'DK-ENC-07', NULL, 'BU-2', 'Savings activities by elec. grid, gas and district heating companies (incl. for the domestic and public sectors)', 'Energy savings and efficiency', 'The grid, district heating and natural gas distribution companies are required to promote energy savings within their supply areas, and they are carrying out a number of campaigns, information activities, advisory work, etc. These activities are funded via the companies&#39; tariffs.', '2000', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'DenmarksUpdateOnPAMsAndProjections-15march 2007, p.62', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(351, 'DK-ENC-16', NULL, 'BU-6', 'Circular on energy-efficiency in state institutions', 'To limit central authorities&#39; consumption of energy and water through promotion of energy efficient purchase and energy efficient behaviour in state institutions and to operate and maintain buildings owned or rented by the state in an energy efficient manner.', 'The circular requires state institutions to:<br />&middot; Focus on energy efficiency in their behaviour<br />&middot; Buy energy efficient products<br />&middot; Oprerate state buildings in an energy efficient manner<br />&middot; Report on, and make public, figures on consumption of energy and water and energy labelling of buildings', '2005', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'DenmarksUpdateOnPAMsAndProjections-15march 2007, p.66', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(352, 'DK-ENC-17', NULL, 'BU-1', 'Agreements on energy efficiency with business', 'Energy efficiency at energy-intensive enterprises and to reduce the effect of the CO2 tax on energy intensive industries&#39; competitiveness.', 'In connection with the implementation of the CO2 tax also a subsidy for CO2 tax discount for energy intensive industries was introduced. However, a condition for getting the CO2 tax discount is an agreement on improvements in energy efficiency. Industries under the CO2 allowance scheme are no longer covered by this arrangement. The aggrement scheme was significantly revised in 1996.', '1993', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'DenmarksUpdateOnPAMsAndProjections-15march 2007, p.61', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(353, 'DK-CRS-06', NULL, 'EN-1', 'EU-CO2-allowances for electricity and district heat production and certain industrial processes (incl. Business)', 'CO2-reduction', 'On 1 January 2005 the EU Emission Trading scheme (EU ETS) replaced Denmark&rsquo;s national allowance scheme. Denmark&rsquo;s national allowance<br />scheme only included the major producers of electricity in the energy sector. Via the national allocation plan, the present allowance regulation in Denmark includes individual emission limits 2005-2007 for CO2 emissions from 377 Danish production facilities within several sectors, which together produce approx. half of Denmark&rsquo;s total greenhouse gas emissions. These are still, primarily, energy producers and energyintensive businesses and industries.', '2004', NULL, '6000', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'DenmarksUpdateOnPAMsAndProjections-15march 2007, p.34', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(354, 'DK-ENS-02', NULL, 'EN-2', 'Biomass Agreement', 'R&amp;D, demonstration, CO2 reduction', 'In 1993 it was agreed to increase the use of biomass in the energy supply. The agreement has been adjusted several times. Today, the target is to reach an amount of 1.4 mill. tonnes of biomass in energy supply by 2005. The incentive for producers of electricity is a garanteed minimum sales price for electricity at DKK 0.4 per kWh through a subsidy adjusted in accordance with the market price on electricity. In addition, certain plants for production of heat and power can obtain a subsidy per tonnes of biomass combusted - but for no longer than 10 years.I', '1993', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'DenmarksUpdateOnPAMsAndProjections-15march 2007, p.35', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(355, 'DK-ENS-09', NULL, 'EN-6', 'Energy research', 'The main objective of the EFP is to support the governments energy policy target, which is a cost effective, environmentally friendly and stable energy supply, and to support the competitiveness of Danish compagnies in the energy area', 'The Energy Research Programme (EFP), under the responsability of the Danish Energy Authority, support energy research, development and pilot projects.', '1976', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'DenmarksUpdateOnPAMsAndProjections-15march 2007, p.39', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(356, 'DK-ENS-14', NULL, 'EN-3', 'Price supplement for suppliers of environmental friendly electricity', 'Promotion of renewable energy sources', 'Since 1 January 2005, all environmentally friendly electricity from wind turbines and other plants based on renewable energy and from decentralised CHP plants, has been sold on market terms. The previous subsidy for environmentally friendly electricity, where consumers were allowed only to buy electricity at a fixed price, has changed into a financial subsidy adjusted relatively to the market price and to a<br />price supplement to the market price. The main principle is that existing plants can receive the susidy in 20 years, with 15 years as the minimum from 2004. New plants based on renewable energy kan receive the subsidy for 20 years.', '2004', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'DenmarksUpdateOnPAMsAndProjections-15march 2007, p.36', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(357, 'DK-ENS-18', NULL, 'EN-4', 'Tender for off-shore wind turbines', 'Promote technology development and aiming for making electricity production with wind turbines competitive to conventionally produced electricity. Reduction of the electricity production&#39;s impact on the environment, including CO2 emissions.', 'In the agreements of 29 March 2004 it was agreed to establish 2 offshore wind turbine facilities, each wih a size of 200 MW. One of the facilities should be located at Horns Rev (&quot;Horns Rev II&quot;) and the other at R&oslash;dsand (&quot;R&oslash;dsand II&quot;). Both should be build on the basis of tenders.', '2004', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'DenmarksUpdateOnPAMsAndProjections-15march 2007, p.37', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(358, 'DK-ENS-19', NULL, 'AF-6', 'Biogas plant', 'Reduced CO2 and CH4 and better exploitation of manure', 'The politically fixed supplement on the price of power production based on biogas has been adjusted several times during the last five years &ndash; most recently by the Energy Policy Agreement of 29 March 2004, which provides for support to biogas through a supplement on the price of electricity for biogas plants established before the end of 2008.', '1987', NULL, NULL, NULL, '500', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'DenmarksUpdateOnPAMsAndProjections-15march 2007, p.77', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(359, 'DK-ENS-20', NULL, 'EN-5', 'Scrapping sheme for old wind turbines', 'Promote technology development and aiming for making electricity production with wind turbines competitive to conventionally produced electricity. Reduction of the electricity production&#39;s impact on the environment, including CO2 emissions.', 'The scrapping scheme will support taking down old and unfavourable placed wind turbines and will support expansion of wind power - aiming at 350 MW new capacity within 5 years. It will only be possible to issue scrapping certificates within a total of 175 MW', '2004', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'DenmarksUpdateOnPAMsAndProjections-15march 2007, p.38', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(360, 'DK-WAM-01', NULL, 'WA-1', 'Obligation to send combustibel waste for incineration', 'Reduce CH4 emissions from landfills', 'An administrative regulation in the form of a ban against landfilling comubstible waste, effective from 1997. Savings occur in energy consumption as well as energy production.', '1997', NULL, NULL, NULL, '333', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'DenmarksUpdateOnPAMsAndProjections-15march 2007, p.82', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(361, 'DK-WAM-02', NULL, 'WA-2', 'Waste tax', 'Greater recycling and least possible landfilling.', 'The tax is differentiated to reflect the prioritisation of the different forms of treatment. It thus costs most to deposit waste, less to incinerate it and nothing in tax to recycle it. The size of the tax thus provides an incentive to recycle as much of the waste produced as possible and to use non-recyclable, combustible waste as fuel in energy production instead of depositing it at a landfill site.', '1987', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'DenmarksUpdateOnPAMsAndProjections-15march 2007, p.83', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(362, 'DK-WAM-03', NULL, 'WA-3', 'Weight and volume based packaging taxes', 'The objectives of both weight and volume -based packaging taxes are to reduce the amount of packaging waste and its impacts on the environment. The taxes provide for economic incentives to behave in accordance with these objectives.', 'Weight-based taxes (e.g. on various packaging, carrier bags and PVC, film) encourage a reduction in packaging consumption and thus the quantities of waste.The weight-based tax is based on an index that reflects the environmental burden of the materials used.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'DenmarksUpdateOnPAMsAndProjections-15march 2007, p.84', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(363, 'DK-WAM-05', NULL, 'WA-5', 'Increased recycling of waste plastic packaging', 'Increase the recycling of plastic packaging waste to a level of 22.5% i 2008.', 'As a result of the EU Packaging Directive, collection of plastic packaging waste for recycling is to be increased to 22.5%, corresponding to an increase in recycling of about 11,000 tonnes plastic per year from 2008. This will be done through an amendment to the Statutory Order on Waste, which will require municipalities to improve the possibilities of people and enterprises to separate and deliver plastic packaging waste for recycling.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '5', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'DenmarksUpdateOnPAMsAndProjections-15march 2007, p.86', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(364, 'DK-WAM-06', NULL, 'WA-6', 'Implementation of the EU landfill directive', 'To introduce more rigorous demands for landfilling of waste and to lower the amount of waste going to landfills', 'On the basis of the EU Landfill Directive, demands on the arrangement and running of landfills have been tightened with Statutory Order No. 650 of 29 June 2001 on landfills. According to the new regulations, wastegas in landfills for mixed waste must be monitored. Gas from landfills where not insignificant amounts of biodegradable waste are landfilled must be managed in an environmentallysound way or be used to produce electricity or for heating purposes.', '2001', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'DenmarksUpdateOnPAMsAndProjections-15march 2007, p.87', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(365, 'DK-WAM-08', NULL, 'WA-4', 'Subsidy programme &ndash; Enterprise Scheme (special scheme for businesses)', 'Reduce environmental impacts from waste', 'In 2005 the Programme for Cleaner Products etc. was replaced by the Enterprise Scheme which refunds CO2 taxes to business. The waste part of the new programme is aimed exclusively at enterprises. A total of DKK 33 mill. for the four-year period from 2004 to 2007 has been earmarked for the waste part of the scheme. The subsidies are to be used to reduce the environmental impact of waste.', '2004', '2007', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'DenmarksUpdateOnPAMsAndProjections-15march 2007, p.85', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(366, 'DK-TRA-01', 'CL-DK-TRA-01', 'TD-6', 'Green owner tax on motor vehicles', 'Improving efficiency of energy consumption, CO2 reduction', 'The Green Owner&rsquo;s Tax is calculated on the basis of the fuel consumption of a car, and there is thus a direct connection between the tax and the petrol or diesel consumption of a vehicle.', '1997', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CL-DK-TRA-01', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'DenmarksUpdateOnPAMsAndProjections-15march 2007, p.32', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(367, 'DK-TRA-02', 'CL-DK-TRA-01', 'TR-1', 'Information campaign on new cars&#39; fuel consumption', 'Improving efficiency of energy consumption, CO2 reduction', 'The Road Safety and Transport Agency has published the folder, Hvor langt p&aring; literen (How far per litre?),containing information on the fuel consumption of all new private cars. An agreement has also been made with the Danish automobile sector that sales materials must contain information on fuel consumption. Duration of campaign: 2 years.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CL-DK-TRA-01', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'DenmarksUpdateOnPAMsAndProjections-15march 2007, p.54', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(368, 'DK-TRA-03', 'CL-DK-TRA-01', 'TR-2', 'Energy correct driving techniques', 'Improving efficiency of energy consumption, CO2 reduction', 'Part of training for driving license', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CL-DK-TRA-01', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'DenmarksUpdateOnPAMsAndProjections-15march 2007, p.55', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(369, 'DK-TRA-04', NULL, 'TR-3', 'Initiative on enforcing speed limits', 'Improving efficiency of energy consumption, CO2 reduction', 'Action for compliance with current speed limits', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'DenmarksUpdateOnPAMsAndProjections-15march 2007, p.56', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(370, 'DK-TRA-05', NULL, 'TR-4', 'Establishment of intermodal installations', 'Improving efficiency of transport, CO2 reduction', 'Establishment of intermodal installations', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'DenmarksUpdateOnPAMsAndProjections-15march 2007, p.57', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(371, 'DK-TRA-08', NULL, 'TR-5', 'Promotion of environment-friendly freight transport', 'Improving efficiency of transport, CO2 reduction', 'Promotion of environment-friendly freight transport', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'DenmarksUpdateOnPAMsAndProjections-15march 2007, p.58', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(372, 'DK-TRA-10', 'CL-DK-TRA-01', 'TR-6', 'Reduced travelling time for public transport', 'Improving efficiency of transport, CO2 reduction', 'Reduced travelling time for public transport', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CL-DK-TRA-01', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'DenmarksUpdateOnPAMsAndProjections-15march 2007, p.59', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(373, 'DK-TRA-11', NULL, 'TR-7', 'Spatial planning', 'Reduction of traffic, CO2 reduction', 'The revised regional plan 2001 describes the stopping of urban sprawl to limit increases in city traffic as a national target.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'DenmarksUpdateOnPAMsAndProjections-15march 2007, p.60', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(374, 'CL-DK-TRA-01', 'CL-DK-TRA-01', 'TR-1, TR-2, TD-6, TR-6', 'Quantification of various transport measures', 'Reducing emissions from transport', 'The effects related to improvement of energy efficiency of cars, both on individual cars and in total, and shown here are from the Effort Analysis where the estimate includes the total effect of EU measures (voluntary agreements with the automobile industry) and national measures (the green owner tax, information campaigns, energy labelling etc.)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '600', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'DenmarksUpdateOnPAMsAndProjections-15march 2007, p.32, 54, 55', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(375, 'DK-CRS-803', NULL, NULL, 'Purchase CO2 credits from JI and CDM projects', 'fullfilling the EU Burden Sharing agreement cost-effectively', 'Since then two Danish purchasing programmes have been launched managed by the Ministry of Foreign Affairs and the Ministry of the Environment. The government set aside DKK 930 million (&euro; 125 mill.) in the period 2003-07 for the purchase of about 3.2 million CO2 credits annually (2008-2012) from Joint Implementation (JI) and Clean Development Mechanism (CDM) projects for use in the period 2008-12. Furthermore, for 2008-9 DKK 200 million (&euro; 27 mill.) have been set aside for the purchase of credits in 2008-2009.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'DenmarksUpdateOnPAMsAndProjections-15march 2007, p.159', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(376, 'DK-AGR-01', NULL, 'AF-1', 'Action Plan for the Aquatic Environment I and II and Action Plan for Sustainable Agriculture', 'Reduction of nitrate pollution to the aquatic environment, i.e. reduction of N runoff from agriculture by 100,000 tonnes N per year.', 'Through reductions in the use of fertiliser, Action Plan for the Aquatic Environment I and II have led to reductions in N2O emissions. The action plans have been implemented as regulations of farmer&#39;s behaviour. The action plans included particular requirements concerning winter-green fields and better utilisation of manure. The action plan II included re-establishment of wetlands, afforestation, agreements on environment-friendly agricultural measures, organic farming on additional 170,000 ha, improved use of fodder, reduced animal density, use of catch crops, reduced fertilization norms and stricter requirements concerning the use of N in manure.', '1991', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'DenmarksUpdateOnPAMsAndProjections-15march 2007, p.68', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(377, 'DK-AGR-02', NULL, 'AF-3', 'Ban on burning of straw on fields', 'Reduced air pollution', 'The ban has resulted in more carbon being returned to the soil and greater use of straw as a fuel. Both uses will result in a net reduction in CO2 emissions. Not burning straw prevents the methane and nitrous oxide emissions associated with the burning. On the other hand, there are some emissions of nitrous oxide in connection with the return of nitrogen to the soil when the straw is mulched. The measure works by regulating behaviour.The measure was implemented in the form of a statutory order under the Environmental Protection Act, and compliance is monitored by the local authorities.', '1989', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'DenmarksUpdateOnPAMsAndProjections-15march 2007, p.70', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(378, 'DK-AGR-03', 'CL-DK-AGR-01', 'AF-4a', 'Ammonia action plan and the new statutory order on manure: Optimisation of manure handling during housing.', 'Protection of the aquatic environment from nitrate pollution.', 'Ammonia action plan and the new statutory order on manure: Optimisation of manure handling during housing for cattle, pigs, poultry and fur animals e.g. cleaning in fur animal houses at least once a week and a maximum time of 6 hours from field application of manure to incorporation and cover requirements etc..', '2001', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CL-DK-AGR-01', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'DenmarksUpdateOnPAMsAndProjections-15march 2007, p.71', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(379, 'DK-AGR-04', NULL, 'AF-2', 'Action Plan for the Aquatic Environment III', 'Protection of the aquatic environment from nitrate and phosphorus pollution.', 'The third action plan contains targets with respect to nitrogen, phosphorus, sensitive natural areas, and slurry odour. This is a 10-year agreement, and in evaluations in 2008 and 2011 initiatives will also be combined with the Water Framework Directive and the Habitats Directive. Special emphasis is on the use of catch crops, stricter requirements for use of manure as well as afforestation and agro-environmental measures.<br />The plan contain several measures, where the most import in relation to greenhouse gas emissions are:<br />Establishment of 4000 ha wetlands in 2004 and 2005.<br />  Making the rules on catch crops more rigorous.<br />  Making the rules on exploitation of N in animal manure more rigorous.<br />  Additional environmentally friendly measures in crop farming.', '2004', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'It is estimated that the general structural development will lead to a reduction of 170 GgCO2eq/year and the effect of the CAP reform will be an additional reduction of 230 GgCO2eq/year.', 'DenmarksUpdateOnPAMsAndProjections-15march 2007, p.69', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(380, 'DK-AGR-05', NULL, 'AF-5', 'Planting of windbreaks', 'Binding of CO2', 'Planting of windbreaks is supported under conditions described in the Statutory Order on subsidies for planting windbreaks and biotope-improving measures (Statutory Order no. 1101 under the EU Rural Districts Programme). Since the end of the 1960s about 1,000 km of tree-lined windbreaks have been planted with government subsidies. It is also estimated that about 30% more has been planted without subsidies.', '1960', NULL, NULL, NULL, '140', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'DenmarksUpdateOnPAMsAndProjections-15march 2007, p.76', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(381, 'DK-AGR-06', 'CL-DK-AGR-01', 'AF-4b', 'Ammonia action plan and the new statutory order on manure: Rules on covering storage facilities.', 'Protection of the aquatic environment from nitrate pollution.', 'Order with rules on covering storage facilities for solid manure (compost layer or another air tight material) and slurry tanks (floating layer, tent or similar).', '2002', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CL-DK-AGR-01', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'DenmarksUpdateOnPAMsAndProjections-15march 2007, p.72', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(382, 'DK-AGR-07', 'CL-DK-AGR-01', 'AF-4c', 'Ammonia action plan and the new statutory order on manure: Ban on surface spreading of manure', 'Protection of the aquatic environment from nitrate pollution.', 'With spreading of manure with towing tubes instead of ordinary broad surface spreading the evaporation of ammonia will be reduced. Also emissions of nitrous oxide will be reduced.', '2002', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CL-DK-AGR-01', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'DenmarksUpdateOnPAMsAndProjections-15march 2007, p.73', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(383, 'DK-AGR-08', 'CL-DK-AGR-01', 'AF-4d', 'Ammonia action plan and the new statutory order on manure: Reduction of the time on field surfaces.', 'Protection of the aquatic environment from nitrate pollution.', 'Manure applied to areas without crops shall be ploughed in within 6 hours.', '2002', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CL-DK-AGR-01', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'DenmarksUpdateOnPAMsAndProjections-15march 2007, p.74', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(384, 'DK-AGR-09', 'CL-DK-AGR-01', 'AF-4e', 'Ammonia action plan and the new statutory order on manure: Ban on ammonia treatment of straw.', 'Protection of the aquatic environment from nitrate pollution.', 'Ban on ammonia treatment of straw.', '2002', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CL-DK-AGR-01', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'DenmarksUpdateOnPAMsAndProjections-15march 2007, p.75', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(385, 'CL-DK-AGR-01', 'CL-DK-AGR-01', 'AF-4a - AF-4e', 'Ammonia action plan', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '30', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'DenmarksUpdateOnPAMsAndProjections-15march 2007, p.71-75', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(386, 'DK-LUC-01', 'CL-DK-LUC-01', 'AF-7', 'Subsidy scheme for private afforestation on agricultural land', 'Promote private afforestation in achieving the target of an increse in forest area by 450,000-500,000 ha in 100 years.', 'Private owners of agricultural land can get grants for establishment of broadleaves or conifer forests, nursing of these in the first 5 years, establishment of fences, mapping and or accounting of the area as well as income compensation in the first 10 years - if the forest will be established in an area planned for afforestation.', '1997', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CL-DK-LUC-01', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'DenmarksUpdateOnPAMsAndProjections-15march 2007, p.78', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(387, 'DK-LUC-03', 'CL-DK-LUC-01', 'AF-8', 'Public afforestation', 'Public afforestation in achieving the target of an increse in forest area by 450,000- 500,000 ha in 100 years for purposes such as outdoor recreation, groundwater protection and CO2 sequestration.', 'Public afforestation (state, counties and municipalities) in achieving the target of an increse in forest area by 450,000- 500,000 ha in 100 years for purposes such as outdoor recreation, groundwater protection and CO2 sequestration.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CL-DK-LUC-01', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'DenmarksUpdateOnPAMsAndProjections-15march 2007, p.79', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(388, 'CL-DK-LUC-01', 'CL-DK-LUC-01', 'AF-7/AF-8', 'Afforestation', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '262', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'DenmarksUpdateOnPAMsAndProjections-15march 2007, p.78/79', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(389, 'DK-CRS-01', 'CL-DK-CRS-01', 'TD-1', 'Mineral-oil tax act', 'Restructuring of existing acts on oil and gas taxes and later also reduction of consumption of polluting fuels as part of the energy policy', 'Act no. 701 of 28 September 1998 on energy taxes of mineral oil products etc., and amendments.<br />Tax on mineral oil products in Denmark. The tax is: Gas oil and diesel oil used as motor fuel: DKK 2.787 per litre<br />Other gas oil and disel oil: DKK 1.857 per litre Light diesel oil (sulphur content max. 0,05%): DKK 2.687 per litre<br />Diesel, low in sulphur (sulphur content max. 0,005%): DKK 2.507 per litre Diesel, sulphur free (sulphur content max. 0,001%): DKK 2.487 per litre<br />Fuel oil: DKK 2.092 per kilogramme Heating tar: DKK 1.888 per kilogramme Petroleum used as fuel: DKK 2.787 per litre<br />Other petroleum: DKK 1.857 per litre, Petrol, with &quot;lead&quot;: DKK 4.50 per litre<br />Petrol, lead-free: DKK 3.85 per litre Petrol, &quot;with Lead&quot; and vap. recovery: DKK 4.47 per litre<br />Petrol, lead-free and vap. recovery: DKK 3.82 per litre Auto gas (LPG): DKK 1.746 per litre<br />Other liquified gas (LPG), used as motor fuel: DKK 3.21 per kilogramme, Other liquified gas (LPG) (refinery gas): DKK 2.379 per kilogramme,<br />Carburettor liquid: DKK 4.07 per litre', '1993', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CL-DK-CRS-01', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'DenmarksUpdateOnPAMsAndProjections-15march 2007, p.27', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(390, 'DK-CRS-02', 'CL-DK-CRS-01', 'TD-2', 'Gas tax act', 'In order to have a tax level on this fuel which match the tax level on other fuels', 'Tax on consumption of natural gas and town gas in Denmark. The tax amount to: DKK 2.042 per Nm3.', '1996', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CL-DK-CRS-01', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'DenmarksUpdateOnPAMsAndProjections-15march 2007, p.28', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(391, 'DK-CRS-03', 'CL-DK-CRS-01', 'TD-3', 'Coal tax act', 'At its introduction the objective was both fiscal and reductions in energy use. Later, CO2 reduction also became an objective.', 'Tax rated after the calorific value of coal, coke, furnace coke, coke gravel, crude coke, lignite briquettes and lignite, tall oil, wood tar, vegetable pitch etc. The tax amount to DKK 51,9 per GJ', '1982', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CL-DK-CRS-01', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'DenmarksUpdateOnPAMsAndProjections-15march 2007, p.29', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(392, 'DK-CRS-04', 'CL-DK-CRS-01', 'TD-4', 'Electricity tax', 'At its introduction in 1977, the objective was both fiscal and reductions in energy use. Since the beginning of the 1990s, amentments also have had CO2 reduction as an objective.', 'Tax on consumption of elektricity. The tax amount to DKK 0.511 per kWh for electricity consumption over 4000 kWh in buildings heated by electric panels. Tax the on all other consumption of electricity amount to DKK 0,576 &oslash;re per kWh.', '1977', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CL-DK-CRS-01', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'DenmarksUpdateOnPAMsAndProjections-15march 2007, p.30', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(393, 'DK-CRS-05', 'CL-DK-CRS-01', 'TD-5', 'Carbon dioxid tax on energy products', 'Reductions in energy use and related CO2 emissions', 'Act no. 643 of 27 August 1998 on carbondioxide taxes of certain energy products, and amendments.<br />Tax on energy products depending on their contribution to CO2 emissions based an average tax of DKK 90 per tonnes of CO2. The taxes are:<br />Gas oil and diesel oil: DKK 0.243 per litre, Fuel oil: DKK 0.288 per kilogramme<br />Heating tar: DKK 0.252 per kilogramme, Petroleum: DKK 0.243 per litre<br />Coal, coke, furnace coke, coke gravel: DKK 217.8 per tonnes, Crude coke: DKK 290.7 per tonnes<br />Lignite briquettes and lignite: DKK 160.2 per tonnes, Electricity: DKK 0.09 per kWh<br />Auto gas (LPG): DKK 0.144 per kilogramme, Other liquified gas: DKK 0.27 per kilogramme<br />Gas (refinery gas): DKK 0.261 per kilogramme, Natural gas and Town gas: DKK 0 198 per Nm3', '1992', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CL-DK-CRS-01', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'DenmarksUpdateOnPAMsAndProjections-15march 2007, p.31', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(394, 'DK-TRA-12', NULL, 'TD-7', 'Registration tax act', 'Restructuring of existing legislation and reduction in consumption of polluting fuels by introducing incentives to buy more fuel efficient cars.', 'Act no. 977 of 2 December 2002 on registration tax on motor vehicles (act no. 964 of 20 December 1999 on fuel efficient cars).<br />- The Registration Tax for diesel-driven cars driving more than 45 km/litre and for petrol-driven cars driving more than 40 km/litre will in the period 2000-2005 be 4/6 of the normal tax and in the period 2006-2010 be 3/5 of the normal registration tax.<br />- The Registration Tax for diesel-driven cars driving 37.5-45 km/litre and for petrol-driven cars driving 33.3-40 km/litre will in the period 2000-2005 be 3/6 of the normal tax and in the period 2006-2010 be 2/5 of the normal registration tax.<br />- The Registration Tax for diesel-driven cars driving 32.1-37.5 km/litre and for petrol-driven cars driving 28.6-33.3 km/litre will in the period 2000-2005 be 2/6 of the normal tax and in the period 2006-2010 be 1/5 of the normal registration tax.<br />- The Registration Tax for diesel-driven cars driving 28.1-32.1 km/litre and for petrol-driven cars driving 25-28.6 km/litre will in the period 2000-2005 be 1/6 of the normal registration tax.', '2000', NULL, NULL, NULL, '600', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'DenmarksUpdateOnPAMsAndProjections-15march 2007, p.33', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
