(504, 'ES-AGR-07', NULL, '65', 'Improve energy efficiency in irrigation areas, as much in water supply of hydrological resources as in irrigation systems (gravity spray)', 'Improve energy efficiency in irrigation areas.', 'Diesel motors for irrigation comprised 32% of total consumption in 2000 and will comprise 4,44% in 2012 as a consequence of irrigation machinery change to electric motors. Improvements are expected in energy efficiency and an exchange of diesel by electric motors with a consquent emission reduction.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'The effect of this measure cannot be quantified independently of the rest, because of the interrelation of all considered in the projections.', 'Communication of Spain to the European Commission relative to greenhouse gas projections and effects of policies and measures in accordance with Decision 280/2004/EC. Attached template: ES 2007_Spain_Template_Decisions_280-2004_2005-166 (V.3.1)', 'Due to achieved fuel and electricity savings, this measure results in reduction of contaminants generated, like Nox, Sox, TSP, CO,&hellip;', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(505, 'ES-AGR-08', NULL, '66', 'Other actions for emission reduction of agricultural machinery', 'Improve energy efficiency of agricultural machinery and renovation of the same.', 'Beyond the foregone consideration of conserving agriculture other additional measures for emission reduction have been included in the objective scenario. These base on the renovation of the tractor fleet and the improvment of its energy efficiency.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'The effect of this measure cannot be quantified independently of the rest, because of the interrelation of all considered in the projections.', 'Communication of Spain to the European Commission relative to greenhouse gas projections and effects of policies and measures in accordance with Decision 280/2004/EC. Attached template: ES 2007_Spain_Template_Decisions_280-2004_2005-166 (V.3.1)', 'Due to achieved fuel and electricity savings, this measure results in reduction of contaminants generated in motors of agricultural machinery, like Nox, Sox, TSP, CO,&hellip;', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(506, 'ES-TRA-09', NULL, '67', 'Reduction of passenger car mobility', 'Decrease of the mobility of passenger-km in road transport.', 'The emissions of the road transport sector are subject to an increase in mobility, besides other apsects, as anticipated in the transport planning of the base scenario.<br />Therefore, beyond the actions considered in foregone measures in relation to road transport, the present measure intends to reduce emissions on the basis of a revision of car passenger mobility, which might derive from initiatives like transfer to other more efficient modes, promotion of telecommuting or diminishment of the distance between living and work.<br />For this, the medium-covered kilometre allowance  has been reduced for these vehicles. This implies an emission reduction of all contaminants originating from passenger cars in urban, rural and interurban targets. The mobility reduction of private vehicles has been transferred to the railway, which is a more efficient mode of transport.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'The effect of this measure cannot be quantified independently of the rest, because of the interrelation of all considered in the projections.', 'Communication of Spain to the European Commission relative to greenhouse gas projections and effects of policies and measures in accordance with Decision 280/2004/EC. Attached template: ES 2007_Spain_Template_Decisions_280-2004_2005-166 (V.3.1)', 'The fuel saving achieved by mobility reduction of private transport and by more efficency of the railway results in reduction of contaminants like Nox, TSP, COVNM, CO,&hellip;', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(507, 'ES-IND-22', NULL, '68', 'Directive 2004/42/EC on the limitation of COV emissions in the use of organic solvents for determinated paint and varnish and in the use of products for car renovation (RD 227/2006)', 'Reduction of COV emissions in activities that use organic solvents and in products for the finishing renovation of cars. As a consequence, the CO2 emissions of these activities are also affected.', 'The Real Decree transposes Directive 2004/42/EC of 21 April 2004, and intends to limit total COV content in paint, varnish and products for the finishing renvation of cars related to annex I, in order to prevent and reduce atmospheric contamination due to the contribution of COV to the formation of tropospheric ozone.', '2007', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'The effect of this measure cannot be quantified independently of the rest, because of the interrelation of all considered in the projections.', 'Communication of Spain to the European Commission relative to greenhouse gas projections and effects of policies and measures in accordance with Decision 280/2004/EC. Attached template: ES 2007_Spain_Template_Decisions_280-2004_2005-166 (V.3.1)', 'This measure focuses on COV reduction', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(508, 'ES-IND-23', NULL, '69', 'Directive 1999/13/EC relative to the limitation of COV emissions due to the use of organic solvents in determinated activities and installations (RD 117/2003)', 'Reduction of  COV emissions in activities that use organic solvents. As a consequence, CO2 emissions of these activities are also affected.', 'This measure imposes obligations on respective installations, among these the one to not exceed several emission thresholds to be specified, or the one to reduce their emissions by other measures like the use of products with low or no content of solvent.', '2007', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'The effect of this measure cannot be quantified independently of the rest, because of the interrelation of all considered in the projections.', 'Communication of Spain to the European Commission relative to greenhouse gas projections and effects of policies and measures in accordance with Decision 280/2004/EC. Attached template: ES 2007_Spain_Template_Decisions_280-2004_2005-166 (V.3.1)', 'This measure focuses on COV reduction', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(509, 'FI-ENC-01', NULL, '1', 'Energy conservation programme', 'To reduce energy consumption', 'The programme has a variety of different energy conservation measures, but only part of them have yet been implemented. The most significant potential is estimated to come from energy use for heating in the housing sector. Because of the slow turnover of the housing stock, however, the average fuel efficiency of housing is expected to improve relatively slowly. As to the consumption of electricity,the efficiency of electric appliances could be increased by stricter norms, both in households and, more significantly, in different services. One of the most important measures is the Voluntary Agreement Scheme on Energy Efficiency. Motiva has run the scheme since 1997 under the Ministry of Trade and Industry; at present the scheme covers around 85% of the total industrial energy use and over 50% of the building stock of the service sector. It has been estimated that the total effect of VAs would be some 2 Tg CO2 eq. in 2010. When the Energy Conservation Programme was drafted, the total effect of energy conservation measures was estimated to be 3&ndash;4 Tg in 2010. However, allocation of resources has not come true to the extent planned.', '1992', NULL, NULL, 'not quantified', '3500', '3,000-4,000', NULL, 'not quantified', NULL, 'not quantified', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(510, 'FI-ENC-03', NULL, '2', 'Directive 2002/91/EC on the energy performance of buildings', 'Energy efficiency', 'Two new laws are under drafting. Some amendments will be made in the existing Land Use and Building Act.', '2003', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(511, 'FI-ENC-04', NULL, '3', 'Measures to promote energy conservation and use of renewables', 'Reduce energy consumption', 'In the WAM Scenario, total conservation of the energy in 2015 is expected to be about 5% of the consumption of energy in the WM Scenario. Measures to promote energy conservation outside the emissions trading sector include, for example, promotion of low-energy construction, including information guidance and development activity (e.g. support for experimental building of detached house areas).<br />Renovation activity with respect to the existing building stock through grants for improving energy efficiency for blocks of flats and terraced houses be continued. For 2007, such grants for blocks of flats and terraced houses were not continued, having remained in force during 2003 &ndash; 2006.<br />Grants for improving energy efficiency in detached and semi-detached houses were introduced in 2006.<br />The related Government Decree came into force in early 2006 and will remain in force until the end of 2008. During this period, grant-based subsidies will be available for investments in heating equipment, or connection to district heating systems, wherever such investments will help to reduce greenhouse gas emissions. Householders may also deduct the labour costs of a certain level of investment by using credit available for domestic work (a Government Bill is being drafted by the Ministry of Finance).<br />Another assumption for the heating sector is that, in accordance with the Directive on the Energy Performance of Buildings, regulations and operating models for energy certificates and audits will be completed in 2006. Proposals for new legislation on the energy efficiency of buildings were presented by the Finnish Government to Parliament in late 2006. It was proposed that the new legislation include an Act on the energy certification of buildings, an Act on inspections of the energy efficiency of cooling equipment used in buildings&rsquo; air conditioning systems, and amendments to the Land Use and Building Act, which would be expanded to cover energy efficiency requirements and details on how energy efficiency should be calculated.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'not quantified', '1500', '1000-2000', NULL, 'not quantified', NULL, 'not quantified', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'FI subMM15_03_07, p.17/18', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(512, 'FI-ENC-05', NULL, '4', 'Eco Management and audit sheme', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'FI subMM15_03_07, p.23', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(513, 'FI-ENC-06', NULL, '5', 'Energy labelling of household appliances', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'FI subMM15_03_07, p.24', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(514, 'FI-ENS-06', NULL, '6', 'Construction of a new nuclear power unit', 'Increased supply of electricity', 'The construction of a new nuclear reactor is quantitatively the most efficient way to reduce CO2 emissions. Emission reduction due to this measure is estimated to be some 8 Tg, if the same amount of electricity were to be produced with coal condensing power, which is the marginal mode of electricity production in Finland (planned start of operation in 2009). Most of the emissions reduction achieved by energy conservation comes from the emission trading sector and most of the measures to promote renewables lie in the ETS sector and are thus included in the allocation of emission allowances.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'not quantified', '8000', NULL, NULL, 'not quantified', NULL, 'not quantified', NULL, 'Emission reduction due to this measure is estimated to be some 8 Tg, if the same amount of electricity were to be produced with coal condensing power, which is the marginal mode of electricity production in Finland.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(515, 'FI-ENS-07', NULL, '7', 'Action plan for renewable energy', 'Increase share of renewable energy', 'The Action Plan on Renewable Energy Sources (RES) was approved in1999. The target was to increase the use of RES by 30% up to the year 2010 in relation to year 2001. The plan also defined a national target of RES for 2010 as 31.5% of the electricity demand. In 2001, bioenergy without peat covered 20% of the primary energy consumption and 10% of the electricity demand in Finland, which are the highest figures in the industrialised countries. National incentives concerning taxation and subsidies of RES are being updated because of a number of reasons, including GHG emissions trading. The key instruments for promoting the use of RES are investment grants, taxation, subsidies and supporting research.', '1999', NULL, NULL, 'not quantified', '4500', '4,000 - 5,000', NULL, 'not quantified', NULL, 'not quantified', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(516, 'FI-ENS-08', NULL, '8', 'Electricity Market Act', 'Increased Competition', 'The electricity market in Finland operates as a part of the regional Nordic market; all customers have been able to change their supplier since November 1998, but consumers have been quite passive. Market liberalization resulted in situation in which power plants are operated according to their cost-efficiency.<br />In a wet hydrological year in the Nordic countries, the price of electricity is low because of large hydropower production. In a dry hydrological year the price is higher and the marginal mode of production is condensing power. GHG emissions fluctuate according to hydrological conditions, but on the whole, the deregulation of the market seems to have had a positive effect on emission reduction. Consumers are also able to select electricity produced from renewable energy sources. However, &ldquo;green electricity&rdquo; products have not gained a remarkable market share. The consumers do not see electricity as concerning an active buying decision, and the suppliers do not have long experience in an active electricity market.', '1995', NULL, NULL, 'not quantified', NULL, 'not quantified', NULL, 'not quantified', NULL, 'not quantified', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(517, 'FI-WAM-01', NULL, '9', 'Government decision on landiflls', 'reduction of emissions', 'Government decisions on landfills and the collection and recovery of waste paper, the waste tax and the adoption of the National Waste Plan lowered considerably GHG emissions from waste management in the 1990s. The mitigation impacts of individual policies and measures cannot be estimated, particularly because there was no &lsquo;without measures&rsquo; scenario available for waste management', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '100', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(518, 'FI-WAM-02', NULL, '10', 'Waste minimisation, the collection and recovery of waste paper and other waste fractions', 'reduction of emissions', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'The mitigation impacts of individual policies and measures in the waste sector cannot be estimated, particularly because there was no &lsquo;without measures&rsquo; scenario available for waste management.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(519, 'FI-WAM-03', NULL, '11', 'Waste tax', 'reduction of emissions', 'The waste tax is EUR 15.1/t and it is applied to wastes excluding soils disposed to municipal landfills.  The taxes on waste handling at landfills will be tightened stepwise to encourage the use of biodegradable waste as material and energy. In addition, the possibilities of extending waste taxes to cover the incinerable industrial waste will be considered', '1980', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'The mitigation impacts of individual policies and measures in the waste sector cannot be estimated, particularly because there was no &lsquo;without measures&rsquo; scenario available for waste management.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(520, 'FI-WAM-04', NULL, '12', 'Landfill gas recovery and utilization', 'reduction of emissions', 'Furthermore, the handling of biodegradable municipal waste at landfills will be reduced, in accordance to the Waste Directive of the EU, to 75% of the 1995 levels by 2006, 50% by 2009 and 35% by 2016. The collection of methane would be extended to those closed landfills, where emissions are considerable.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '100', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(521, 'FI-WAM-05', NULL, '13', 'Waste minimisation, the utilisation of source-separated waste fractions as material and energy', 'reduction of emissions', 'Preparation of a new National Waste Plan, with targets for 2015, started in 2005. It will be finalised in 2006, and integrated into other relevant plans and programmes.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(522, 'FI-WAM-06', NULL, '14', 'Development of waste taxation', 'reduction of emissions', 'The taxes on waste handling at landfills will be tightened stepwise to encourage the use of biodegradable waste as material and energy. In addition, the possibilities of extending waste taxes to cover the incinerable industrial waste will be considered.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(523, 'FI-WAM-07', NULL, '15', 'Biowaste strategy', 'To reduce CH4 emissions', 'With regard to waste management, the additional measures included in the WAM projection cover the pre-treatment and initial sorting of waste and the impact of the reduction of treatment of waste at landfill in accordance with the implementation of the EC Landfill Directive, and the influence of intensified waste prevention and collection of landfill gas. The projection restricts the treatment of biodegradable waste at landfills and the growth of the volume of waste and promotes the treatment of landfill gases.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '130', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'FI subMM15_03_07, p.19', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(524, 'FI-TRA-02', 'CL-FI-TRA-02', '16', 'Act on biofuels', 'Increased use of biofuels in transport', 'At the beginning of 2007, the Finnish Parliament passed the Act on Biofuels under the Directive on the Promotion of the Use of Biofuels or Other Renewable Fuels for Transport (2003/30/EC). This Act will increase the share of renewable fuels in the transport sector to 5.75 per cent in 2010, and will enter into force at the beginning of 2008.', '2007', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CL-FI-TRA-02', NULL, 'CL-FI-TRA-02', NULL, 'CL-FI-TRA-02', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'FI subMM15_03_07, p.18', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(525, 'FI-IND-01', NULL, '17', 'Regulation on F-gas', 'Reduce emissions from F-gases', 'The WAM projection assesses the impact of the Regulation on F-gases on emissions (Regulation of the European Parliament and of the Council on certain fluorinated greenhouse gases (EY) No. 842/2006).The implementation of the Regulation does not affect the WM projections for electricity distribution equipment and cellular plastics. In the WAM projection, emissions from other sources are changed from those in the WM projection as a result of the measures included in the regulation. The emission reduction achieved by these measures is estimated to be 0.36 Tg in 2010.', '2007', NULL, NULL, NULL, '360', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'FI subMM15_03_07, p.20', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(526, 'FI-IND-02', NULL, '18', 'F-gases from  air conditioning', 'Reduce emissions from F-gases', 'The directive entered into force on 4 July 2006. Member States shall adopt and publish national legislation by 4th January 2008 and apply it on the next day.', '2007', NULL, NULL, NULL, '30', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'FI subMM15_03_07, p.24', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(527, 'FI-TRA-03', 'CL-FI-TRA-01', '19', 'Voluntary agreements with European, Japanese and Korean car industries,', 'Reduction of CO2 emissions from passenger cars: 140/120 g/km by 2008/2010', 'Average energy consumption of petrol fuelled cars should be less than 6 litres in 100 km and that of diesel cars less than 5.5 litres in 100 km. Additional measures will need to be developed to meet the EU target of 120 g/km for new cars by 2010. Instead of decreasing, CO2 emissions increased by approximately  100-200 Gg CO2eq.', '1999', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'not quantified', NULL, 'not quantified', NULL, 'CL-FI-TRA-01', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(528, 'FI-TRA-04', NULL, '20', 'Differentiation of vehicle taxation in conjunction with voluntary energy saving agreements', 'Reduction of passenger car traffic and GHG emissions', 'Fiscal measures with the aim to reform vehicle taxation to encourage purchase of low consumption and energy-saving cars and to promote and subsidize public transport. a working group is at present developing methods for making the annual vehicle tax dependent on CO2 emissions.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(529, 'FI-TRA-05', 'CL-FI-TRA-01', '21', 'Promotion of public and non-motorised transport', 'Increasing share of public and non-motorised transport', 'Regulatory measures with the aim to guide development of new agglomerations with the help of public tarnsporttation system plans and intention agreements in such a way that agglomerations are connected with well-functioning public and non-motorised facilities. In August 2005, the Government decided to allow tax deductions for employer-paid public transport tickets from the beginning of 2006. This is estimated to lead to increasing use of public transport in commuter traffic if employers become encouraged by the tax deduction to start buying tickets for their employees.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'not quantified', NULL, 'not quantified', NULL, 'not quantified', NULL, 'CL-FI-TRA-01', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(530, 'FI-TRA-06', 'CL-FI-TRA-01', '22', 'Eco-driving', 'Adoption of ecoefficient driving skills and habits', 'Information, education and motivation, such as eco-driving, campaigns aiming at awareness raising and changing behaviour. Campaign has the aim to train 1500 professionals HDV drivers and 1000 passenger car drivers', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'not quantified', NULL, 'not quantified', NULL, 'not quantified', NULL, 'CL-FI-TRA-01', NULL, 'premanent decrease in energy consumption is expected to be around 5-10%', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(531, 'FI-TRA-07', 'CL-FI-TRA-01', '23', 'Energy-saving agreements', 'Adoption of energy saving agreements between administration and transport operators 5% energy saving by year 2010 compared to 2003', 'Voluntary energy saving agreements with the transport carriers. New porgramme covers 2005-2010. 5% energy saving in 2010 compared to 2003, around 1% reduction per year in 2020.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CL-FI-TRA-01', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(532, 'CL-FI-TRA-01', 'CL-FI-TRA-01', '19, 21, 22, 23', 'Cluster of measures (WM) in transport (voluntray agreement, promotion public and non-motorized transport, eco-driving, energy saving agreements)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'not quantified', NULL, 'not quantified', NULL, 'not quantified', '1000', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(533, 'FI-TRA-08', 'CL-FI-TRA-02', '24', 'Additional measures to maintain urban structure', 'Concentrating and Maintaining compact urban structure', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'not quantified', NULL, 'CL-FI-TRA-02', NULL, 'CL-FI-TRA-02', NULL, 'CL-FI-TRA-02', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(534, 'FI-TRA-09', 'CL-FI-TRA-02', '25', 'Increase of fuel taxation', 'To reduce traffic volume and GHG emissions', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'not quantified', NULL, 'CL-FI-TRA-02', NULL, 'CL-FI-TRA-02', NULL, 'CL-FI-TRA-02', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(535, 'FI-TRA-13', NULL, '26', 'Tax deduction for employer paid public transport tickets', 'Increase use of public transport', 'Employers should be encouraged by the tax deduction to start buying tickets for their employees. This should lead to an increasing use of public transport in commuter traffic.', '2006', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(536, 'FI-TRA-14', 'CL-FI-TRA-02', '27', 'Differentiation of vehicle taxation in conjunction with voluntary energy saving agreements of the car industry', 'Promotion of purchase and use of energy efficient vehicles', 'The introduction of differentiation of vehicle taxation in accordance with energy consumption and in conjunction with the voluntary energy saving agreements between the European Commission and car manufacturing industry (ACEA-JAMA-KAMA) should reduce transport-related CO2 emissions in Finland. Expected to lead to an annual reduction of around 1.5% in CO2 emissions if differentiation will lead to consumer behaviour changes.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CL-FI-TRA-02', NULL, 'CL-FI-TRA-02', NULL, 'CL-FI-TRA-02', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(537, 'FI-TRA-15', NULL, '28', 'Railway act', NULL, NULL, '2003', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'FI subMM15_03_07, p.23', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(538, 'CL-FI-TRA-02', 'CL-FI-TRA-02', '24, 25, 27, 16', 'Cluster: effect of additional policies and measures in transport sector (Diffferentiation of vehicle taxation, increase fuel taxation, biofuels, urban structure)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'not quantified', '500', NULL, '500', NULL, '500', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'FI subMM31_05_07, p.18', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(539, 'FI-CRS-01', NULL, '29', 'Use of Kyoto Mechanisms', 'Raising the assigend amount', 'In order to fulfil its climate commitments, Finland is using the Kyoto mechanisms to acquire emission units in accordance with the policies of the National Climate Strategy, whereby Finland&rsquo;s assigned amount will rise by 10 million tonnes during 2008&ndash;2012. Furthermore, Finland will acquire approximately 2 million tonnes&rsquo; worth of emission units from the CDM/JI pilot programme (Clean Development Mechanism/Joint Implementation). Finland has already allocated a total of 70 million euros to the acquisition of emission units in its state budgets for 2005-2007. The budget for the CDM/JI pilot programme, which started in 1999, was approximately 20 million euros.<br />Several reports examining the use of the mechanisms were compiled in January-February 2006, on the basis of which the interministerial supervisory group on the Kyoto mechanisms prepared strategic policies for the use of the Kyoto mechanisms during 2006&ndash;2012. In addition, the Ministry of Foreign Affairs drafted its own action plan for CDM acquisitions. The Ministry of the Environment has compiled an executive strategy for joint implementation projects (JI) and international emissions trading for the years 2006&ndash;2012. These documents were approved by the Ministerial working group on Climate and Energy Policy in August 2006.', '1999', '2006', NULL, 'not quantified', '2000', NULL, NULL, 'not quantified', NULL, 'not quantified', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'FI subMM15_03_07, p.19', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(540, 'FI-CRS-501', NULL, '30', 'EU Emission Trading Scheme - Allocation 2005-2007', 'Reduced CO2 emissions from industry', 'The EU ETS covers almost the whole energy sector, with only small district heating plants and space heating outside its scope. So the allocation of emission allowances under the EU&rsquo;s Emission Trading Directive is the main additional measure in the energy sector. The reduction of emissions due to the ETS is estimated to be 0.8 Tg per year in the 2005&ndash;2007 period.', '2005', '2007', '800', NULL, NULL, 'not quantified', NULL, 'not quantified', NULL, 'not quantified', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(541, 'FI-CRS-502', NULL, '31', 'EU Emission Trading Scheme  - Allocation 2008-2012', 'Reduced CO2 emissions from industry', 'In the second ETS-period, 2008&ndash;2012, the reduction is estimated to be 8.7 Tg per year. This is the deficit between the WM-scenario and the amount of emission allowances allocated under EU ETS. Installations may either reduce this amount by doing domestic measures or buy emission allowances under EU ETS.', '2008', NULL, NULL, 'not quantified', '8700', NULL, NULL, 'not quantified', NULL, 'not quantified', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'FI-subMM31_05_07', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(542, 'FI-CRS-801', NULL, '32', 'Finnish CDM/JI Pilot Programme', 'Develop capacity for project based mechanisms', 'The Finnish CDM/JI Pilot Programme was launched in 1999 in order to develop Finland&rsquo;s capacity to apply the project-based mechanisms.  Overall, the activities of the Pilot Programme are estimated to generate some 2 Tg of Kyoto compatible credits (ERUs, AAUs and CERs) under the first commitment period of 2008&ndash;2012.', '1999', NULL, NULL, 'not quantified', '400', NULL, NULL, 'not quantified', NULL, 'not quantified', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(543, 'FI-CRS-90', NULL, '33', 'Energy taxation', 'To reduce energy consumption and to improve competitiveness of renewables. Duty on certain fuels and products.', 'Finland was the first country to introduce a CO2 tax in 1990. This tax was based on the carbon content of fuels. Since its introduction the tax system has been modified and tax rates adjusted several times in the 1990s. The present energy taxation consists of three tax components: A basic excise tax is levied on transport and heating fuels, an additional CO2-based excise tax is levied on fossil fuels and peat and an additional differentiated (industrial and other use) excise tax is levied on electricity consumption. <br />The energy taxation is regulated by the Act on Excise Duty on Electricity and Certain Fuels (1260/1996) and the Act on Excise Duty on Liquid Fuels (1472/1994). The energy tax divides into basic tax and surtax. The basic tax is fiscal by nature and it is collected on oil products only. The basic tax on petrol and diesel oil is graded according to their quality and environmental characteristics. Surtax is collected on oil products, other fossil fuels and electricity. The surtax on fuels is determined according to their carbon content.<br />Electricity is taxed at its consumption stage. The tax on electricity is divided into two classes, of which the lower, Class II, tax is paid by industry and professional greenhouse cultivation. Other consumers pay the higher, Class I, tax. The energy taxation scheme also includes various subsidies. Of these, the most important ones in terms of energy policy are tax subsidies paid for power production based on renewable energy sources.', '1997', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(544, 'FI-AGR-02', NULL, '34', 'Agenda 2000, including Agri-environmental support measures<br />Horizontal Rural Development Programme in Continental Finland (2000-2006)', 'Promotion of sustainable development in agriculture: Decrease nutrient load.', 'In 2000 a new agricultural policy, Agenda 2000, became fully effective in Finland as the five-year EU transitional period came to an end in 1999. One part of the programme is the agri-environmental support for 2000&ndash;2006 based on the Council Regulation (1257/1999).The main focus is not to reduce greenhouse gas emissions, but the support together with the structural change in Finnish agriculture have enabled a significant reduction of greenhouse gas emissions from agriculture; they decreased from 7.1 Tg CO2 eq. in 1990 to 5.7 Tg CO2 eq. in 2003.', '2000', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(545, 'FI-AGR-03', NULL, '35', 'Nitrate Statute', 'To reduce N2O emissions', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(546, 'FI-LUC-01', NULL, '36', 'National Forest Programme', 'Promotion of sustainable forest management, increase the forst industry&#39;s annual use of roundwood by 5-10 million cubic metres by 2010, increase the annual use of wood for energy production by 5 million m3, raise forest improvement investments to EUR 250 million per year, in particular for forest planning and advising and training of forest owners', 'The main idea of the National Forest Programme (NFP) is that a competitive forest cluster combined with the fact that forests are a renewable resource, provides an excellent foundation for sustainable development. The programme recognises the economic, ecological, social, and cultural aspects of sustainable forest management. It also sets the objectives for the forest sector.', '1999', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(547, 'FI-LUC-02', NULL, '37', 'Promotion of use of  wood products', 'Campaign for the promotion of use of wood products', 'The government and different stakeholders have jointly carried out<br />an initiative &ldquo;Time for Wood&rdquo; from 1996 to 2000. The purpose of this<br />campaign was to facilitate the increased use of wood, improve employment<br />in the woodworking industry and improve education and<br />training in the woodworking branch. A similar kind of campaign was carried out in 2001&ndash;2005.', '1996', '2005', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(548, 'FI-LUC-04', NULL, '38', 'Environment Programme for Forestry', 'Forest conservation on privately owned land for 1996-2007', 'The Environmental Programme for Forestry in Finland (1994) includes a strategy for sustainable forestry, together with targets for the year 2005.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(549, 'FI-LUC-03', NULL, '39', 'Forest Certification', 'Improve consumer awareness about sustainable forest management, promote use of wood', 'At the end of 2000 about 95% of the Finnish forests. Altogether about 22 million hectares were certified pusuant to the Finnish Forest Certification System', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(550, 'FR-CRS-01', NULL, '1', 'Information campaign- &quot;Faison vite ca chauffe&quot;', 'Awareness rising of public', 'Awareness rising for measures regarding GHG emissions reduction', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Not mentioned in Rapport France 2007', '4th NC Chap.4 p. 30', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(551, 'FR-CRS-02', NULL, '2', 'Section &quot;Climat-&eacute;nergie&quot; in contracts of the project &quot;State-Regions 2007-2012&quot;', 'Coordination of actions', 'Coordination of actions for the development of renewable energies and energy efficiency and the territorial climate plans between the national government and the regions.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 30', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(552, 'FR-CRS-03', NULL, '3', 'European Emission trading, National Allocation Plan', 'Limitation of CO2 emissions of installations by a market based mechanism', '28% of total emissions of France are affected by EU-ETS (156,5 Mt CO2/year). Decree from 29. July 2005 established verification modalities and monitoring of emissions. This text also fixes obligations for monitoring for GHGs. The NAP was delivered in 2006.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3200', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 30 and p. 16', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(553, 'FR-CRS-04', NULL, '4', 'Certificates for energy savings', 'Commitment for suppliers', 'Commitment for suppliers of electricity, gas and fuel oil to realise energy savings. The law for orientation of energy policy from 2005 stipulates an obligation for energy savings for energy suppliers. The amount is fixed at 54 TWh of energy savings for three years calculated for the life-time of the product or the equipment concerned with a rate of repayment of 4%. Suppliers obliged to join this project have been published 2006 together with their saving objectives. They are allowed to buy certificates from other suppliers or to realise energy savings in their own company or from their customer to get saving certificates. Costs of saving actions are estimated to be10 &euro;/MWh. Penalty costs for not fulfilling the saving commitment is 0,02&euro;/kWh. http://www.industrie.gouv.fr/portail/ministre/comm.php?comm_id=7009', '2006', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2400', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'France provides two different estimates for the certificates on energy savings, 2,400 Gg CO2eq as part of cross-cutting measures and it is again included in a more general estimate under WAM in the energy sector.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 30 and p. 13', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(554, 'FR-CRS-05', NULL, '5', 'Wood energy plan', 'Development of substitution of fossil fuel by energy from wood.', 'Energy from wood is the most promising renewable resource in France. A programme called  &quot;wood energy 2000-2006&quot; was started by ADEME for developing urban and industrial wood-fueled boiler houses and modernisation of conditions of use on the market for domestic applicances. Nearly 6 million households already use wood heating boilers. The purchase of such installations increased because of increased oil prices and tax credits which started in 2005 for purchase of efficient and low-polluting combustion equipments. It can be observed that the installed boilers became  more efficient but they are often used as additional heating units. Wood use remained constant at about 7,5 Mtoe/year. About 1000 urban or collective boiler houses were built which use wood as main energy source. ADEME subsidises investments for collective boiler houses (up to 50%) and promotes a label for efficient and user-friendly installations (Green flame) and a label for fuel wood (NF). Public costs of this programme are 65 M&euro; for six years, in the first 5 years a reduction of 0,5 MtCO2/year has been obtained. Total objective for emission reduction is 1,4 MtCO2eq.', '2000', NULL, NULL, NULL, '1400', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 30 and p. 8-9', NULL, NULL, '108333333333333', 'Public costs of this program are estimated to be 65 M&euro;, for 6 years of programm', NULL, NULL),
(555, 'FR-CRS-06', NULL, '6', 'Research program for new energy technologies', 'Development of new energy technologies', 'Request for projects started in April 2005. Research programs regarding hydrogen (PAN-H), bio-energy (wood, bio-carbonates), CCS, PV and energy efficient buildings (PREBAT). Financed by ANR and AII.', '2005', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 30 and p. 13', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(556, 'FR-ENS-01', NULL, '8', '&quot;Wind energy&quot; Plan', 'Development of wind energy', 'Wind power is the most developed renewable electricity generating technology with highest potential in France (66 TWh of technical potentail for land-based and 90 TWh for sea-based installation). The wind energy plan 1996-2000 called  &quot;windpower 2005&quot; had the objective to initialise a wind power capacity between 250 and 500 MW in 2005, a  capacity of 360 MW had been achieved.', '1996', '2000', NULL, NULL, '40', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 30 and p. 10', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(557, 'FR-ENS-02', NULL, '9', '&quot;Solar energy&quot; Plan', 'Development of solar energy', 'Development of thermal and photovoltaic solar energy for substitution of fossil fuels. Objective: 110.000 m2 of new solar panels in 2006. Subventions are given by ADEME and eventually additional local subsidies. Labelling of installations, capacity building of installers (6000 at the end of 2004) and garanteed solar results. In 2003 88.000 m2 of solar panels were installed.', '2000', '2006', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 30 and p. 9', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(558, 'FR-ENS-03', NULL, '10', 'Contracts for cogeneration and exemption &quot;TICGN&quot;', 'Promotion of cogeneration', 'From the year 1993 on cogeneration installations are profiting from an exemption of the consumption tax for natural gas, the tax on petrol products for 5 years and of a purchase obligation with EDF.', '1993', '2006', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 30, Rapport France 2007 p.22', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(559, 'FR-ENC-01', NULL, '11', 'Labelling of electric household applicances', 'Labelling for energy efficiency improvement of electric household applicances', 'Labelling  of electric household applicances for market evolution towards energy efficient products. Specific consumption decreased but total household consumption nevertheless increased.', '1992', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 30 and p. 11', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(560, 'FR-ENC-02', NULL, '12', 'FACE (Fonds d&#39;amortissement des charges d&#39;&eacute;lectrification)', 'Decrease of energy consumption and development of renewable energies', 'Special fund provides financial support for CDM and JI projects for local communities.', '1995', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 30 and p. 11', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(561, 'FR-ENC-03', NULL, '13', 'Energy audits', 'Energy advice', 'Subsidies from ADEME are given for realisation of energy audits, which are the most important measure in energy sector for CO2 reduction. From the year 2000 on 60 M&euro; have been invested in this measure, 3200 audits have been subsidised.', '2000', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'n.e.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 31 and p. 14', NULL, NULL, '12000', 'Amount of subsidies for audits which have been given 2000-2005 is 60 M&euro;.', NULL, NULL),
(562, 'FR-ENS-5', NULL, '91', 'Extension of nuclear electricity generation', 'CO2 reduction because of nuclear electricity generation', 'Last connections of three nuclear reactors ith 1500MW to the grid have been undertaken in 2001. France had 59 nuclear reactors with a net production of 428 TWh in 2004.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th NC Chap. 4 p.8', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(563, 'FR-ENS-14', NULL, '92', 'Technology change for nuclear enrichment', 'Lower electricity consumption for nuclear enrichment', 'After a public discussion organised in 2004 Eurodif, the enrichment factory, part of the company AREVA, will change the enrichment technology used to ultracentrifugation up to 2015. This will reduce electricity consumption in the range of 16 TWh.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th NC Chap. 4 p.8', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(564, 'FR-ENS-16', NULL, '94', 'Use of geothermal energy', 'Development of renewable use for heating purposes', 'In the regions &quot;Ile de France&quot; and around Bordeaux France has 65 geothermal active sources which are heating 0.2 Mio. households since about 1980. For maintenance and extension of pipelines ADEME extended the &quot;Long-term garantee&quot; to 25 years and gives subsidies of 400 &euro; per tCO2 avoided.', '1980', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th NC Chap. 4 p.9', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(565, 'FR-ENS-6', NULL, '95', 'Renewable electricty generation', 'Development of renewable use for electricity generation', 'Actual production of electricity from renewables is 70 TWh, 13% of total generation in 2004. The annual increase of 2,5 TWh additional production is largely compensated by consumption growth. High dependency on hydro generation therewith from perpetuation. The transposition of the EC Directive 2001/77/CE requires an increase of at least additional 33 TWh in 2010, (21% of total generation ). Subsidies for electricity from renewables are given by an purchase obligation for electricity distributers following an assessment base reglemented and financed totally from a contribution of public service for electricity generation. Purchase tariffs for electricity generated from wind power have been adapted to installation size.  Wind power installations have induced costs of 30 M&euro;. There is a highly controversial discussion about wind power, a national wind power committee will be established to start a dialogue.', '2001', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th NC Chap. 4 p.9-10', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(566, 'FR-ENC-22', NULL, '96', 'Funds like FIDEME, FOGIME', 'Financial instruments for encouragement of investments', 'Funds for investments for environmental measures or measures that reduce consumption for small and medium sized enterprises. FOGIME gives additional securities (70%), financed by ADEME, in 2001 4,5 Mio &euro;. FIDEME is a fund for financing of important projects of companies for proven technologies in the sector of renewable energies but also in recycling and valorisation of waste (30 MIo &euro; from bancs and 15 Mio &euro; from ADEME). It has to be repaid with nearly normal market interests.', '2001', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th NC Chap. 4 p.11', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(567, 'FR-ENS-04', NULL, '15', 'Possibility of nuclear option (EPR Flamanville)', 'Possibility of nuclear option (EPR Flamanville)', 'Installation of an EPR demonstration reactor with 1600 MW in or about 2012, stipulated by the law for orientation of energy politics from 2005. Replacement of existing nuclear plants in 2020 (oldest plants will be about 40 years in operation) is necessary - the nuclear option is not excluded.', '2005', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 30 and p. 12', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
