(568, 'FR-ENS-09', 'CL-FR-ENC-01', '16', 'Certificates for energy saving (electricity part)', 'Commitment for suppliers', 'see P&amp;M-No. 4 Commitment for suppliers of electricity, gas and fuel oil to realise energy savings.  The law for orientation of energy policy from 2005 stipulates an obligation for energy savings for energy suppliers. The amount is fixed at 54 TWh of energy savings for three years calculated for the life-time of the product or the equipment concerned with a rate of repayment of 4%.  Suppliers obliged to join this project have been published 2006 together with their saving objectives. They are allowed to buy certificates from other suppliers or to realise energy savings in their own company or from their customer to get saving certificates. Costs of saving actions are estimated to be10 &euro;/MWh. Penalty costs for not fulfilling the saving commitment is 0,02&euro;/kWh.  http://www.industrie.gouv.fr/portail/ministre/comm.php?comm_id=7009', '2006', '2009', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CL-FR-ENC-01', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 30 and p. 13', NULL, NULL, '180000000', '54 TWh shall be saved in three years, costs of 10&euro;/MWh are assumed.', NULL, NULL),
(569, 'FR-ENC-05', 'CL-FR-ENC-01', '17', 'Ecodesign Directive and general energy efficiency labelling', 'Reduction of energy consumption', 'Market evolution towards energy efficient products.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CL-FR-ENC-01', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 30 and p. 14', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(570, 'FR-ENC-06', 'CL-FR-ENC-01', '18', 'Sustainable air conditioning', 'Rational use of climatisation', 'The Climate Plan stipulates to establish a regulation which allows the use of air conditioning units only above certain temperatures and autorises the integration of climatisation into the calculation of thermal regulation only in limited cases, especially in the regions C&ocirc;te-d&#39;Azur-Provence-Alpes. In other cases respecting the rules for  conceptual design shall assure sufficient comfort in summer season.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CL-FR-ENC-01', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 30 and p. 14', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(571, 'CL-FR-ENC-01', 'CL-FR-ENC-01', '16+17+18', NULL, NULL, 'Certicates for energy savings (electricity part), Ecodesign Directive, Sustainable air-conditioning and new thermal regulation', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3000', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(572, 'FR-ENS-10', 'CL-FR-ENS-10', '20', 'Feed-in tariffs and purchase obligation', 'Development of renewable energies', 'Substitution of fossil fuels for electricity generation by renewable energies. Purchase tariffs from electricity generated from biomass and photovoltaic generation will be increased.', '2006', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CL-FR-ENS-10', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 30 and p. 13', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(573, 'FR-ENS-11', 'CL-FR-ENS-10', '21', 'Tender for multi-year investment (wind and biomass)', 'Development of renewable energies', 'Wind power and biomass tender from PPI - (Programmation pluriannuelle d&#39;investissement) - Multiyear investment program. Article 6 from Law 2000-108 regarding modernisation and development of public electricity services stipulates a multiyear program for investments.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CL-FR-ENS-10', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 30, 59, 66', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(574, 'CL-FR-ENS-02', 'CL-FR-ENS-02', '20+21', NULL, NULL, 'Feed-in tariffs and investment programme', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '6225', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(575, 'FR-ENS-12', NULL, '22', 'Green certificates for electricity from renewable energies', 'Development of renewable energies', 'To improve the promotion of electricity from renewable energies a &quot;green certificate&quot; was introduced from an international association &quot;Renewable Energy Certificate System&quot; that guarantees the  origin from renewable sources. 0.6 TWh electricity was certified.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 30 and p. 9-11', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(576, 'FR-ENS-13', NULL, '23', 'Waste plan (Waste incineration with energy recovery)', 'Reduction of waste volume', 'Increase the share of waste incineration for energy purposes', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '500', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 30', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(577, 'FR-ENS-17', NULL, '97', 'Development of the use of renewable thermal energy', 'Development of thermal energy from renewables', 'In 2005 a tax reduction was established with a tax exemption of 40%. A strong increase of installation of solar heating devices (80-100%) was observed as a result. Installation of geothermal heat pumps and water-air systems and wood-fuelled boilers also increased. The national government proposes to increase the tax exemption to 50% for heating appliances based on renewables. An increase of 50% from 2005 to 2010 of thermal energy from renewables is the objective. A program called &quot;Face sud&quot; for solar thermal energy use has the objectiv to install  1 mn m2/year. In 2006 a decree entered into force that obliges construction projects to prepare a feasibility study for renewable thermal energy use. In the framework of Climate Plan 2004-2012 government decided to double credits for thermal use of renewable energies. 200 mn&euro; will be allocated for five years.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 12', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(578, 'FR-IND-01', NULL, '25', 'Wood energy plan (industry)', 'Fossil fuel substitution by wood fuel', NULL, '2000', '2006', NULL, NULL, '400', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 31', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(579, 'FR-IND-03', 'CL-FR-IND-01', '27', 'Regulation of N2O emissions from industrial processes', 'Limits for specific N2O emissions', 'A decree from 1993, strengthened in 1998, limited N2O emissions to 7kg per tonne of nitric acid produced.', '1993', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CL-FR-IND-01', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 31 and p. 14', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(580, 'FR-IND-04', 'CL-FR-IND-01', '28', 'General tax on polluting activities - N2O', 'Internalisation of external costs', 'A law from 1999 completed the regulation of N20  with a general tax on polluting activities which includes N2O emissions (57,17 &euro;/tonne). Because of these two measures (P&amp;M-No. 27+28) specific emissions of nitric acid production have been reduced by 25% after 1990.', '1999', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CL-FR-IND-01', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 31 and p. 14', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(581, 'FR-IND-05', 'CL-FR-IND-01', '29', 'Voluntary agreement AERES: N2O commitment', 'Commitment for reduction of N2O emission in chemical industry', 'AERES (Association of companies for reduction of climate change) has been created in 2002 on voluntary basis by French companies. 33 companies and four business associations (11 activity sectors are represented) are included. The coverage is broader than in EU-ETS because all six GHG are included. The engagement of the industry is defined for two periods: unitl 2007 and until 2012.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CL-FR-IND-01', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 31 and p. 16', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(582, 'CL-FR-IND-01', 'CL-FR-IND-01', '27+28+29', NULL, NULL, 'Measures for N2O reduction in chemical industry (process emissions)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '25700', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(583, 'FR-IND-06', NULL, '30', 'Regulation of installations of HFC &gt;2 kg', 'Limitations of emissions from equipment and maintenance operations', 'Within the framework of the EC Directive  France established  a decree in 1992 with an obligation for recuperation and control of F-gas leakages for installations with charges of more than 2 kg. The implementation was accompaniedby a convention between professionals, ADEME and the Ministry for environment. A control-run started in 2002 by regional directions of industry, research and regional services of Ministries of industry and environment, showed that controls are useful for mobilising professionals. Studies about leak-tightness of cooling composites by initiative from AFCE and financed by ADEME and UNICLIMA led to important findings and to the next imporvement of definition of a French norm which will be proposed to ISO. Projects for refunds in France or taxation at EC level have been abandoned.', '1993', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Not mentioned in Rapport France 2007', '4th NC Chap.4 p. 31 and p. 15', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(584, 'FR-IND-07', NULL, '31', 'Progress commitment AERES', 'Emission reduction from HFC, PFC production', 'Two production sites for PFCs and HFCs in France reduced their emissions by 92% because of the use of an incinerator. AERES (Association of companies for reduction of climate change)  was created in 2002 on a voluntary basis by french industries. 33 companies and four business associations (11 activity sectors are represented) are included.  Engagement of industries is projected in two periods: 2003-2004 and 2005-2007.', '2002', NULL, NULL, NULL, '3300', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 31 and p. 16', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(585, 'FR-IND-08', NULL, '32', 'Sectoral progress commitment 1996 and 1997: glas, iron industry, aluminium, magnesium foundries, AERES', 'Change of industry processes', 'AERES (Association of companies for reduction of climate change) has been created in 2002 on voluntary basis by French companies. 33 companies and four business associations (11 activity sectors are represented) are included. The coverage is broader than in EU-ETS because all six GHG are included. Engagement of industries is projected in two periods: 2003-2004 and 2005-2007. Emissions of members are reduced by 23% in 2004 to 1990. Sectoral progress: -16% (1990-2003) reduction of CO2 for Ammonium production', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '5000', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 31 and p. 16', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(586, 'FR-IND-09', NULL, '33', 'Convention RTE, GIMELEC, ADEME', 'Management of SF6 of electric equipments', 'GIMELEC (Group of industries for electrical equipment of control technology and associated services); management of RTE (Electricity transportation network), MEDD (Ministry of ecology and sustainable development) and ADEME sigend an agreement for the period of 2004-2010, regarding the reduction of SF6 from electric appliances of high and low voltage in 2010 to achieve  the level of emissions from 1995. RTE and GIMELEC will start an action programme, ADEME engages within existing subsidy frameworks.', '2004', NULL, NULL, NULL, '1100', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 31 and p. 15', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(587, 'FR-IND-10', NULL, '34', 'Voluntary agreement WSC', 'Reduction of emissions from F-gases from production of semi-conductors', 'Reduction of emissions from F-gases from production of semi-conductors', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2800', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 31, 102', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(588, 'FR-IND-11', 'CL-FR-Ind-03', '35', 'Application of European recycling Directives DEEE, VHU', 'Obligation for recuperation of refrigerant fluids', 'Application of two European Directives regarding management of waste DEEE (recuperation of electric and electronical waste - directives 2002/95/CE and 2002/96/CE) and VHU (recycling of vehicles 2000-53 CEE) imposed with decrees from 20 June 2005 and 1 August 2003 concern the recuperation of cooling mediums from refrigerators and mobile air conditioning.', '2002', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CL-FR-Ind-03', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Not mentioned in Rapport France 2007', '4th NC Chap.4 p. 31 and p. 17', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(589, 'FR-IND-12', 'CL-FR-Ind-03', '36', 'Reglementation of installations of HFC &lt;2 kg', 'Limitations of emissions from equipment and maintenance operations', 'Limitations of emissions from equipment and maintenance operations', '2007', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CL-FR-Ind-03', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Not mentioned in Rapport France 2007', '4th NC Chap.4 p. 31 and p. 17', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(590, 'FR-IND-13', 'CL-FR-Ind-03', '37', 'Project for European reglulation on F-gases', 'Limitations of emissions from equipment and maintenance operations', 'Limitations of emissions from equipment and maintenance operations', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CL-FR-Ind-03', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Not mentioned in Rapport France 2007', '4th NC Chap.4 p. 31', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(591, 'FR-IND-14', 'CL-FR-Ind-03', '38', 'Project of European Directive on F-gases', 'Limitation of GWP from F-gases in vehicles', 'A project for an European Directive will prohibit F-gases with GWP above 150 for vehicles brought on the market after 2011 and for all vehicles in 2017. Several gases are affected: 17 HFCs, 7 PFCs and SF6.', '2011', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CL-FR-Ind-03', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Not mentioned in Rapport France 2007', '4th NC Chap.4 p. 31 and p. 17', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(592, 'CL-FR-IND-03', 'CL-FR-IND-03', '35-38', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3600', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(593, 'FR-IND-15', NULL, '39', 'European Emission Trading, National Allocation Plan', 'Limitation of CO2 emissions of installations by a market based mechanism', '28% of total emissions of France are affected by EU-ETS (156,5 Mt CO2/year). Decree from 29. July 2005 established verification modalities and monitoring of emissions. The NAP II was approved in May 2007, 132,8 Mt CO2/year have allocated for the period 2008-2012.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1900', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 31 and p. 16; Rapport France 2007 p. 25', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(594, 'FR-IND-16', NULL, '40', 'Inclusion of N2O into the European Emission Trading Scheme', 'Inclusion of N2O into the European Emission Trading Scheme', 'France supports the inclusion of N2O in EU-ETS.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2600', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 31 and p. 16', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(595, 'FR-IND-17', NULL, '98', 'Participation in project-based flexible mechanisms', 'CDM and JI projects', '9 CDM projects have been accepted the Designated National Authority (DNA). 8 of these projects were registered by the CDM Executive Board (incl. a wind parc in Morocco, biogas recovery in Brasil, N2O reduction in Korea and Brasil). 16 MtCO2eq /year will be generated from these  8 projects in the period 2008-2012. Two other projects are in process of registration. In addition France encouraged French companies to participate in JI and CDM projects and estimates this engagement with 16 Mt CO2eq. reduction in 2010. The emission reduction due to the participation in project mechanisms by operators included in the EU ETS is not included in this database as the effect is already included in the reduction effect of the trading scheme.', '2008', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th NC Chap. 4 p. 17', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(596, 'FR-IND-18', NULL, '99', 'Creation of an action group for CO2 reduction', 'Coordination of actions', 'A group of industries created a club with the name &quot;Action group CO2&quot; following the initiative of Medef (Movement of companies in France) for coordination of research actions and encouragement of actions in local communities regarding reduction of GHG emissions. This group wants to coordinate the exchange of information and a promote research and development of mitigation measures in different sectors.', '2005', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th NC Chap. 4 p. 17', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(597, 'FR-TRA-01', NULL, '41', 'Development of TGV network', 'Increase share of railway in long distances', 'Development plan from before 1990 for extension of high speed railway network. Three lines are now planned. Change of transportation mode shall be especially from aviation to rail, with second importance from road to rail.', '1990', NULL, NULL, NULL, '1500', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 31 and p. 18', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(598, 'FR-TRA-02', NULL, '42', 'Promotion for cultivation of energy plants within the PAC', 'Development of production of biomass', 'Actual production of biomass is 1 % of annual carbon consumption (0,34 Mtoe) in 2004. Promotion is done by partial tax exemptions and by subventions of 45 euro/ha for bio energy cultures.', '1991', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Transport C0', NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 31 and p. 18', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(599, 'FR-TRA-03', NULL, '43', 'Voluntary agreement of automobile manufacturers (ACEA, JAM, KAMA)', 'Limitation of specific emissions of passenger cars', 'ACEA agreement at EU level. Average specific consumption in 2005 in France of new cars: 152 gCO2/km. Target: 140 gCO2/km in 2008/2009.', '1998', '2009', NULL, NULL, '9000', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Transport C0', NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 31 and p. 19 and Rapport France p.28', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(600, 'FR-TRA-04', NULL, '44', 'Labelling of fuel consumption and CO2 emissions of cars', 'Evolution of vehicle market towards more efficient vehicles', 'CO2 emissions of cars are included in a label separating 7 classes of CO2 emissions (similar to labelling of household applicances) to improve information of customer. The label is obligatory from 10.May 2006 on.', '1999', NULL, NULL, NULL, '200', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Transport C0', NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 31 and Rapport France p.29', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(601, 'FR-TRA-05', NULL, '45', 'Speed control', 'Reduction of accidents and of actual specific consumption of vehicles', 'Measures will continue to be applied across the entire road system to ensure compliance with speed limits. 450 radars have been installed. The average speed observed on the roads has been reduced by more than 10 km/h (2004), lower fuel consumption can be observed (1-2%).', '2002', NULL, NULL, NULL, '3000', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Transport C0', NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 31 and p. 18', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(602, 'FR-TRA-06', NULL, '46', 'Technical control of low-weight vehicles', 'Better performance', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2500', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 32', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(603, 'FR-TRA-07', NULL, '47', 'Development of TCSP (public transport) and TER (regional express train)', 'Modal shift in road transport', 'Local communities have engaged for additional financial efforts for modernisation of public transport. New circulation policies and urban road charges are only investigated until now. It is thought to use parking fines for financing of public transport.  Government has decided in 2005 to give 100 M&euro;  for  this measure.', '2005', NULL, NULL, NULL, '350', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 32', NULL, NULL, NULL, '100 M&euro; for TCSP from financing agency of transport infrastructure (AFTIF)', NULL, NULL),
(604, 'FR-TRA-08', NULL, '48', 'Plan for freight transport with rail', 'Modal shift in road transport', 'Financing of infrastructure other than roads is prioritized since 2003. Freight transport by rail is competitive for distances above 500 km but two thirds of the transport is below 300 km.  A plan for freight rail transport was implemented with a budget of 1,5 Mrd &euro;  during three years (800 mn &euro; paid by the state). The fund is used for investments in railway networks and subsidies of combined transport.', '2003', NULL, NULL, NULL, '100', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Transport D0', NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 32 and p. 20', NULL, NULL, '500000000', 'Plan for rail-bound freight transport with 1,5 Mds&euro; for three years', NULL, NULL),
(605, 'FR-TRA-09', NULL, '49', 'Establishment of AFITF: readjustment on financing for public transport', 'Modal shift from road transport', 'Prioritisation of financing of transport infrastructure other than road with particular emphasis on rail and navigation.', '2003', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Transport D1', NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 32 and p. 20', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(606, 'FR-TRA-18', NULL, '100', 'Privilege of non-road transport infrastructure', 'Modal-shift', 'At the level of the national interministerial committee for rural development, assembled at 18.december 2003, financing of transport infrastructure other than roads is privileged. An agency for financing transport infrastructure in France has been established in 2005 (AFITF). CIADT will approve plans for transport infrastructure for the horizon up to 2025 and a program for infrastructure realisation up to 2012. Public transport has not increased like it was planned.', '2003', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 19', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(607, 'FR-TRA-11', 'CL-FR-TRA-2', '50', 'Consumption tax exemption for biofuels - enhancement of use of biofuels', '7% share of biofuels in 2010', 'France has agreed to produce 7% of liquid fuels from biomass in 2010 and 10% in 2015.  3-3.5 Mha will be used for biomass production in 2015. For ecological reasons (water availability, monocultures) subsidies are necessary.  In 2006 259 mn &euro; have been approved. For 800,000 t biofuels which are foreseen in 2007 320 mn &euro; are estimated. The objective is to install 500-600 green gas stations in 2007 and 1800 in 2008.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CL-FR-TRA-2', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Transport C0', NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 32 and p. 21', NULL, NULL, '400000000', '2006: 259 M&euro; approved; 2007: 320 M&euro;  estimated, 2Mrd&euro; are preprogramed until 2010.', NULL, NULL),
(608, 'FR-TRA-12', 'CL-FR-TRA-2', '51', 'TGAP  (General tax for polluting activities) biofuels', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CL-FR-TRA-2', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Transport C0', NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 32', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(609, 'CL-FR-TRA-2', 'CL-FR-TRA-2', '50+51', NULL, NULL, 'Promotion of biofuels', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '9400', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(610, 'FR-TRA-13', NULL, '52', 'Tax incentives for clean vehicles', 'Evolution of vehicle market towards more efficient vehicles', 'Tax incentives for clean vehicles', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'n.e.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Transport C0', NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 32', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(611, 'FR-TRA-14', NULL, '53', 'Registration tax based on CO2 emissions', 'Evolution of vehicle market towards more efficient vehicles', 'Regsitration costs of vehicles are based on CO2 emissions : above 200 g CO2/km there is a supplementary costs of  2&euro;  per additional gram, above 250 g CO2/km 4&euro; per additional gram.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '100', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Transport C0', NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 32 and p. 22', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(612, 'FR-TRA-15', NULL, '54', 'Assistance for relocation plans of companies, carbon balance for logistic', 'Information about emission reduction potentials', 'Assistance for relocation plans of companies, carbon balance for logistic', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'n.e.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 32', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(613, 'FR-TRA-16', NULL, '55', 'Ecodriving', 'Sensibilization of drivers for energy savings', 'Awareness rising for fuel consumption related to driving behaviour', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '600', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Transport C0', NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 32', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(614, 'FR-TRA-17', NULL, '56', 'Enhancement of agreements of ACEA, JAMA, KAMA', 'Limitation of specific emissions of passenger cars', 'France supports in the European objective to achive average emissions of 120 g CO2/km until 2012 for new cars. There is a research programme for clean cars which is supported with 100 mn &euro; for designing a car with high market penetration which uses less than 3,5 l/100 km (90 g CO2/km).', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Transport C0', NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 32 and p. 21', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Research program with 100 M&euro;', NULL, NULL),
(615, 'FR-ENC-08', 'CL-FR-ENC-03', '57', 'Subsides for energy audits of buildings', 'Reduction of energy consumption of buildings through by energy consultants', 'From  the year 2000 on  ADEME subsidies energy audits for buildings. Between 2000 and 2004 35.000 buildings have been analysed. In 55% of all cases recommendations have been realised. Mitigated emissions have been estimated at approx. 0,07 Mt CO2 in 2004.', '2000', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CL-FR-ENC-03', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 32 and p. 23', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(616, 'FR-ENC-09', 'CL-FR-ENC-03', '58', 'Energy information points', 'Reduction of energy consumption', 'Following Climate Plan 2004-2012 umber of info-points for individual energy advices will be doubled until 2010.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CL-FR-ENC-03', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 32 and Rapport France p.41', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(617, 'CL-FR-ENC-03', 'CL-FR-ENC-03', '57+58', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '100', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(618, 'FR-ENC-10', NULL, '59', 'Thermal Regulation RT 2000', 'Energy consumption reduction of new buildings', 'The thermal building code 2000 which entered into force on 1June 2001 requires a reduced heating demand of  -10 to -20% for new residential buildings and -15 to -25% for the tertiary sector. Realisation of savings are very dependent on type of construction and used energyform.', '2001', '2020', NULL, NULL, '600', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 32 and p. 22', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(619, 'FR-ENC-11', NULL, '60', 'Energy label (HPE, THPE) and environment label (HQE)', 'Labelling and scheme for energy efficient products', 'Thermal regulation act is accompaigned with the initiation of volontary labels : HPE for at least 8% reduction additional to the required level and THPE for at least 15% ; Environment Quality initiatives and quality schemes have been introduced like the HQE for green buildings.', '2001', NULL, NULL, NULL, '500', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 32 and p. 23', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(620, 'FR-ENC-12', NULL, '61', 'Recued VAT rate of  5,5% for energy saving equipment', 'Incentives for redevelopment of existing buildings', 'In September 1999, the government lowered  the VAT rate for energy improvements of existing buildings  by 15 points (from 20.6% to  5.5%). Companies get a special early depreciation rate for certain equipments for energy saving or energy generation by renewables.', '1999', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 32 and p. 22', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(621, 'FR-ENC-13', NULL, '62', 'Efficiency requirements for new hot-water boilers', 'Limitation of specific emissions', 'The European Directive has been transposed into national law: a minimum efficiency has been prescribed for new warm water heating boilers with liquid or gaseous fuels. Condensing boilers now have a market share of about 5%.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '300', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 32 and p. 23', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(622, 'FR-ENC-14', NULL, '63', 'Subsidies for thermal energy from renewables (tax credits, subsidies from Solar Plan and Wood Plan)', 'Substitution of fossil fuels by renewables', 'See PAM tax credits for renewables, solar plan and subsidies for biomass as fuel', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '600', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 32', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(623, 'FR-ENC-22', NULL, '89', 'Operation program for technical and energetic improvement', 'Lowering energy consumption of buildings', 'Ministry of Buildings and ADEME have started a new procedure in 2002 for energetic enhancement of buildings for a whole district. 16 communities have been selected for participation.', '2002', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 23', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(624, 'FR-ENC-23', NULL, '90', 'ANAH (National Agency for improvement of living conditions)', 'Award of renewable heating systems', 'Following the decision of the administration council from 2002 the National Agency for improvement of living conditions (ANAH Agence nationale d&#39;am&eacute;lioration de l&#39;habitat) gives financial awards for wood heating systems, thermodynamic systems and solar energy systems for certain efficient equipments (3,8 mn &euro; in 2003). The Agency determines thresholds for special performances.', '2002', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 23', NULL, NULL, NULL, '3,8 M&euro; in 2003', NULL, NULL),
(625, 'FR-ENC-15', NULL, '65', 'New Thermal Regulation RT 2005 and follwing RT 2010, RT 2015', 'Reduction of energy consumption of new buildings', 'The thermal building code 2000  will be intensified in 3 successive steps every 5 years with additional requirements of -10 to -15% as foreseen by the Energy Law of 2005. In 2020 the reduction of thermal energy demand will be 40%.  In 2006 a decree is coming into force to requiring a 15% reduction of thermal energy demand.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '600', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 32 and p. 22', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(626, 'FR-ENC-16', NULL, '66', 'Directive for energy efficiency of buidings (DPE, inspection of central heating boilers, existing regulation)', 'Reduction of energy consumption of new buildings', 'Application of the European Directive started before 2007 and comprises for the first time an energy regulation for retrofitting existing buildings following similar requirements as RT2000 and a regulation for marginal rehabilitations. From 2006 on periodic inspections of central heating boilers is obligatory.  Boilers with more than 100 kW have to be inspected every two years, boilers which are older than 15 years have to be inspected. Thermal diagnostic of buildings shall be available for each new purchaser or lodger. On the energy label CO2 and primary energy is indicated, the label is obligatory for purchase of ancient buildings and appartments from 1.1.2006 on and for all locations and new buildings from 1.1.2007 on.', '2006', NULL, NULL, NULL, '600', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 32 and p. 24 and Rapport France 2007 p. 39', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(627, 'FR-ENC-17', NULL, '67', 'Modernazation subsidies by ANAH are bound to energy efficiency improvements', 'Energy consumption reduction of existing buildings', 'Modernisation subsidies by ANAH are directed at energy efficiency improvements', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 32', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(628, 'FR-ENC-18', NULL, '68', 'Renovation ANRU (Agence national pour la r&eacute;novation urbaine)', 'Renovation of sensible quarters', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '300', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 32', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(629, 'FR-ENC-19', 'CL-FR-ENC-04', '69', 'Enhancement of tax reductions for renewable energies', 'Initialisation of markets for renewable energies', 'Tax reduction with the aim of sustainable development and energy savings. To enhance energy efficiency of buildings the government proposed to increase tax reductions by 40-50% for renewable energy installations and heat pumps.  Bank credits are given with an interest of 1.5% for investment in energy savings and &quot;White certificates&quot; may be used to finance certain works.', '2005', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CL-FR-ENC-04', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 32 and p. 24', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(630, 'FR-ENC-20', 'CL-FR-ENC-04', '70', 'Enhancement of tax reductions for central heating boilers and insolation', 'Evolution of  market towards more efficient products', 'Tax reduction with the aim of sustainable development and energy saving. Tax credits are : 15% for low-temperature boilers; 25% for condensing boilers, insolation material and equipment for heating regulation, 40% for installations for the use of renewable energies and heat pumps which are used mainly for heating pruposes. For enhancement of energy efficiency of buildings government proposed to increase tax credits: 40-50% for REN installations and heat pumps, 25-40% for condensing boiilers and insulation material under the condition that they are installed in buildings which have been completed before 1977 and that the installation is done at least two years after purchase of the building. It is discussed if tax credits of 25% will be given for equipment for the use of district heating if heat is generated from renewables or from cogeneration. Local collectives are allowed to renounce temporarily the local rates for buildings with significant energy efficient renovation. Bank credits are given with an interest of 1,5 % for investment in energy savings and &quot;White certificates&quot; may be useful to finance certain works.', '2005', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CL-FR-ENC-04', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 32 and p. 24 and Rapport France 2007 p. 40', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Tax credits have been 400 M&euro; in 2005 and 900 M&euro; in 2006.', NULL, NULL),
(631, 'CL-FR-ENC-04', 'CL-FR-ENC-04', '69+70', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '900', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 32', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(632, 'FR-ENC-21', NULL, '71', 'Certificates for energy economy (part &quot;heating&quot;)', 'Commitment for suppliers', 'Commitment for suppliers of electricity, gas and fuel oil to realise energy savings. See P&amp;M- No. 4', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1000', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 32 and p. 13', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(633, 'FR-AGR-01', NULL, '72', '1st campaign for fine-tuning of tractors and agriculture engines', 'Reduction of energy consumption', 'Reduce fuel consumption by an average of 10% by systematic fine-tuning of engines and advices for fuel-efficient driving. In 2002-2003 about 3,000 tractors have been fine-tuned from a parc of 1,250,000 engines.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 33 and p. 26 and Rapport France p. 44', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(634, 'FR-AGR-02', NULL, '73', 'Information programme on energy consumption', 'Reduction of energy consumption', 'A technical journal (RAD-Solagro-ADEME) provides advice on energy economics, energy efficiency, energy generation by renewables and reduction of GHGs. Destinators are the chamber of agriculture, agricultural services and regional associations. A certain number of concrete actions were undertaken and it is planned to itensify these actions.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 33 and p. 26', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(635, 'FR-AGR-03', NULL, '74', 'Improved application of nitrogen fertiliser', 'Reduction of nitrate pollution to groundwater', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 33', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(636, 'FR-AGR-04', NULL, '75', 'Agreement for environmental wood construction', 'Material substitution by wood', 'For construction with timber products low energy input is necessary, besides is captures carbon for about 30 years. An agreement was signed in 2001 for the promotion of the use of wood for construction.  The substitution of material can avoid 0,9 Mt CO2 eq/year. 4 mn m3 of supplementary wood is predicted to be used in constructions which could avoid 7 Mt CO2 eq/year.', '2001', NULL, NULL, NULL, '900', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 33 and p. 26', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(637, 'FR-AGR-05', NULL, '76', 'Decree for obligatory minimum share of wood use in construction', 'Material substitution by wood', 'A decree imposed a construction labelling indicating the percentage of timber which was used in the construction in new buildings. The decree published on 26.December 2005 prescribes a minimum percentage of wooden materials  that has to be used in new constructions; this rate is assessed to be to small.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 33', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(638, 'FR-AGR-06', NULL, '77', 'Additional campaign for fine-tuning of tractors and agriculture engines', 'Reduction of carbon consumption', 'Additional programme for fine-tuning of tractors. 30.000 adjustments per year for about 1,2 Mio engines.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '500', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 33 and p. 27', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(639, 'FR-AGR-07', NULL, '78', 'Encouragement for biogas recovery', 'Reduction of methane emisisons and energy valorisation', 'Encouragement for biogas recovery', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '900', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 33', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(640, 'FR-AGR-08', NULL, '79', 'Improved use of nitrogen fertilisers and additional cultivation areas for biomass and biofuels', 'Impact of cultivating new areas for the production of biomass', 'Improved use of nitrogen fertilisers and additional cultivation areas for biomass and biofuels', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '-100', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 33', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(641, 'FR-AGR-10', NULL, '86', 'Integration of sequestration capacity of forests and agricultural soils', 'Integration of sinks', 'This measure will thoroughly stabilise the methodology for the inventory estimation in the LULUCF sector. It will be used for the complete inventory produced at the end of 2007. Studies about effects of climate change on forests and definition of future management of metropolitain forests have been commissioned.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th NC p.83 and Rapport France 2007 p. 46', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(642, 'FR-AGR-11', NULL, '87', 'Anaerobic treatment of manure', 'Reduction of CH4', 'ADEME started several experimental projects in the whole country. The decree from 10.July 2006 determines higher tariffs for electricity purchase from biogas-fueled installations. An increase of the number of methane-using installations is expected because of new domestic projects.', '2005', '2010', NULL, NULL, '500', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th NC p.83 and Rapport Framce 2007 p. 46', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(643, 'FR-AGR-12', NULL, '88', 'Energetic valorisation of biomass', 'Intensified use of biomass', 'There are ideas to introduce an obligation for public projects above 1000 m2 to use biomass energy (Either through a heat fund or the legal framework). Following the &quot;Orientations of energy policy&quot;, the use of heat from renewables should increase by 50% and electricity from renewables by 21%. A multi-year investment programme for heat was established. Energetic valorisation of biomass will also be promoted by several other measures which supports the use of thermal heat by renewables. This measure started like it was planned but should be more dynamic regarding the availability of recycled wood. Following certain studies the potential of unused and waste wood is one third of French production.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3000', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th NC p.83-84', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(644, 'FR-WAM-01', 'Cl-FR-WAM-01', '80', 'Limitation of waste landfilling', 'Reduction of waste volume', 'Limitation of waste landfilling', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Cl-FR-WAM-01', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 33', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(645, 'FR-WAM-02', 'Cl-FR-WAM-01', '81', 'Obligation to capture methane from landfills', 'Reduction of CH4 emissions', 'Obligation to capture methane from landfills', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Cl-FR-WAM-01', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 33', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(646, 'Cl-FR-WAM-01', 'Cl-FR-WAM-01', '80+81', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '14400', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(647, 'FR-WAM-03', NULL, '84', 'Waste plan', 'Reduction of waste volume', 'This plan, announced in 2004 by the French government, is a national plan for waste reduction until 2008 (trend is an increase of 1% per year). Recycling will be developed for cost reductions but also for better acceptance of waste management.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '100', NULL, NULL, NULL, '1600', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th NC Chap.4 p. 33 and 61', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(648, 'FR-ENS-18', NULL, '101', 'Electricity generation by windpower', 'Development of renewable energies', 'A decree from 22 June 2001 introduces feed-in tariffs for electricity generated by windfarms. The law POPE from 13. July 2005 has canceled the threshold for windfarms with installed capacity lower than 12 MW but establishes development zones for windfarms selected by communities and autorised by the prefect.  Due to a highly controversial discussion about wind power, mainly because of landscape questions, a national wind power committee has been established to start a new dialogue. On 1.1.2007 1500 MW wind power have been installed with an increase from 0.6 TWh in 2004 to 1.0 TWh in 2005.', '2001', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Rapport France 2007 p. 16', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(649, 'FR-ENS-19', NULL, '102', 'VAT of 5.5% for energy from wood', 'Development of renewable energies', 'The agricultural steering law from 5. January 2006 has reduced VAT for wood energy for non domestic use to 5.5%. The national housing action law from 16. July 2006 also reduced VAT to 5.5% for district heating using at least 60% of renewable energy (biomass, geothermal), energy recovery or thermal energy from waste incineration.', '2006', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Rapport France 2007 p. 19', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(650, 'FR-ENS-20', NULL, '103', 'Tax on CO2', 'Internalisation of external costs', 'In the framework of Climate Plan 2004-2012 the government decided to introduce an environmental tax to cover the external environment and health costs. This tax is included in the supplementary budget from 2006. The decree is under elaboration.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Rapport France 2007 p. 20', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(651, 'FR-TRA-19', NULL, '104', 'Extension of energy label CO2', 'Information about actual car effciencies', 'Following the Climate Plan 2004-2012 the spread of energy labels for existing and used cars shall be increased. A simplified label to be attached on windscreens of vehicles is under evaluation; labelling will be extended for used cars in professional selling places .', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Rapport France 2007 p. 34', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(652, 'FR-ENC-24', NULL, '105', 'Savings for sustainable development for loans for renovation works in existing buildings', 'INformation about credits for energy saving works in existing buildings', 'Following the Climate Plan 2004-2012  savings CODEVI and LDD for sustainable development have been developed to mobilise bank agencies to promote profitable credit offers for works which which increase energy efficiency in existing buildings. The legislation allows from 1.1.2007 to increase the personal limit for savings from 4,400 to 6,000&euro;. Collection of these tax exempted savings are estimated to be 10 bn &euro; and will be immediamently disposable. 40 bn &euro; are estimated for credits destinated to finance works for energy savings on existing buildings', '2007', NULL, NULL, NULL, '700', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Rapport France 2007 p. 41', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'more than 40 MRD &euro; will be available', NULL, NULL),
(653, 'FR-ENC-25', NULL, '106', 'Credit for energy performance of branch office', 'Financing of energy saving investments', 'The main financing agency for social housing issues credits with 2.45% for additionsal investments which save energy for new social buildings to get the THPE label (20% above regulation requirements).', '2006', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Rapport France 2007 p. 41', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(654, 'FR-AGR-13', NULL, '107', 'Structuring of supply with fuel wood', 'Development of use of wood as fuel', 'Supply infrastructure has been one of the challenging points of the wood energy -lan 2000-2006 from ADEME, especially regarding the production line and the supply of boilers with forest pellets. Commercial production in 2005 has increased to 181,724 m3.', '2000', '2006', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Rapport France 2007 p. 44', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
