(1281, 'GR-ENS-01', NULL, '13', 'Natural gas in electricity generation', 'Fuel Switch in power plants', 'The introduction of natural gas in the national energy system is one of the largest investments ever carried out in Greece and it constitutes a major priority of the national energy policy. An important part of the infrastructure, mainly the high pressure transmission system and the medium<br />pressure network, which is necessary for the transport of natural gas to the main regions of consumption, has been completed, while the networks&rsquo; development in the cities is ongoing, financed in the framework of the Operational Program Competitiveness (OPC).<br />National target for 2010: 3496 MW installed power of plants using natural gas as fuel', NULL, NULL, '5964', NULL, '4855', NULL, '4935', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Total installed power of plants using natural gas as fuel', NULL, 'Climate Change - Emissions Projections Policies And Measures, May 2008 (Greece&#39;s submission under Decision 280/2004/EC), p.11,16,23', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1279, 'GR-ENS-350', NULL, '11', 'Natural gas in residential/tertiary sector', 'Promotion of natural gas for thermal uses', 'Tax exemption for end-user purchase and installation of systems using natural gas.The Value Added Tax (VAT) is fixed at 9%, while the consumption of natural gas is exempted from any excise tax up to 1 Jan 2014. The penetration of natural gas in the residential and the tertiary sector (roughly 163 ktoe in 2005) remains considerably behind from the initial planning because of delays in the development of networks within the cities. However important increase in the penetration of natural gas in these sectors is observed for 2005, as well as for the first semester of 2006 mainly because international prices of oil increased significantly.<br />National target for 2010: Total annual consumption of natural gas in the residential / tertiary sector: 858 ktoe', NULL, NULL, '483', NULL, '1215', NULL, '1581', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Total annual consumption of natural gas in the residential / tertiary sector (ktoe)', NULL, 'Climate Change - Emissions Projections Policies And Measures, May 2008 (Greece&#39;s submission under Decision 280/2004/EC), p.11,17,23', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1278, 'GR-ENC-501', NULL, '10', 'Energy conservation interventions', 'Energy efficiency of thermal and electric energy uses', 'Miscellaneous interventions for energy savings in the industry sector, pursued to be supported by OPC, the Development Assistance Act and also the operation of the EU-ETS. The reduction of energy intensity in the Greek industry is continuous during the last fifteen years and it is projected that the decrease will be continued in the next years, while the energy conservation in the small to medium-sized industrial units should constitute an additional target. National target for 2010: Heat energy savings: 26 ktoe; Electrical energy savings 14 ktoe', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '282', NULL, '296', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Heat energy savings (ktoe), Electrical energy savings (ktoe)', NULL, 'Climate Change - Emissions Projections Policies And Measures, May 2008 (Greece&#39;s submission under Decision 280/2004/EC), p.13,19,24', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
