(712, 'HU-ENS-01', NULL, '1', 'Act on Electricity (VET)', 'Regulation of the electricity market', 'A 10-year energy efficiency loan construction established within the frame of European Union&#39;s Phare programme, but this facility was stopped with the expiry of the Phare programme in 2006.', '2001', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'HU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.6', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(713, 'HU-ENS-02', NULL, '2', 'New Act on Electricity (VET)', 'Regulation of the electricity market', 'Due to the necessity of creating the legal framework for the liberalisation of energy market, the Government initiated that a new Act on Electric Energy would be passed. The draft of the new Act was submitted to the Parliament with urgency on 21st May, 2007. According to the text of the draft, the new Act also lists among its main objectives the promotion of energy efficiency and energy saving in order to serve sustainable development. It also states that in order to protect the environment and nature, the utilisation of renewable energies, waste as fuel and combined heat and power generation must be promoted.<br />The protection of the environment and energy efficiency appear as criteria in several aspects, such as the operation of transmission systems, construction of new capacities. The draft also stipulates that proper information must be provided for the consumers about the environmental impacts of the power sold.<br />It also codifies demand side management as a tool for reducing primary energy use. It also authorizes the Hungarian Energy Office to safeguard the implementation of the principles of energy efficiency and least cost.<br />In general the draft can be considered as maintaining the framework and basis for further GHG mitigation actions and the related lower-level legislation.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'HU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.6f', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(714, 'HU-ENS-03', NULL, '3', 'Limitation of SO2 emissions from power plants', 'Reduce air pollution', 'The Decree 22/1998 (VI.26) KTM and a sequel Decree of the Minister for Environment and Water 10/2003. (VII.11.) KvVM which is replacing it have set more strict emission limits than those in force earlier and offered two alternatives for the operators of the emission sources: either provisions are made to reduce emissions below the limit (e.g. FGD units are installed) or the operation has to be stopped. The deadline for the measures for large power stations was January 1st, 2005, for other plants it is (mainly industrial) 31st December, 2008.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '980', NULL, '980', NULL, '980', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'HU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.11, 36', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(715, 'HU-ENS-04', NULL, '4', 'Support of CHP', 'Promotion of CHP', 'This policy promotes combined heat and power (CHP) by<br />&bull; stipulating the mandatory purchase of co-generated electric power<br />&bull; providing financial support for the operators of CHP plants in the form of regulated and subsidised feed-in tariff.<br />Funds for the subsidies are provided by a small earmarked fraction of the regulated end-user electricity prices.<br />This safe market generated rapid growth of -  primarily small-scale - CHP. This growth of small scale CHP capacities created problems in the control of the national power system, therefore the legislation was changed in order to shift the focus from quantity to quality and limit further growth. In the past two years further limitations were introduced:<br />&bull; limitations of subsidy to strictly distinct heating-coupled CHP plants below 6 MW capacity<br />&bull; 10% reduction of subsidies for plants commissioned after the year 2006.<br />The following GHG-emission reduction benefits of the policy are still retained:<br />&bull; The new natural gas fired CHP units replace some of the fossil (coal and oil) power generation capacity of the Hungarian power system, as well as some of the heat-only thermal plants.<br />&bull; The overall efficiency - especially with the new efficiency criteria - of the CHP plants is higher than the combined efficiency of conventional power generation and heat only plant, resulting in net fuel saving and hence emission reduction.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '698', NULL, '776', NULL, '750', NULL, NULL, 'The emission reduction can be calculated by comparing the energy production data to a baseline scenario, where the same amount of electricity is generated in the Hungarian Power system and the heat in gas fired heat only plants.<br />The forecast of the quantitative effects follows the monitoring method. As to the baseline values for power generation, they are based on the values and methods developed by the Ministry of Environment and Water for the calculation of reference CO2 emission factors used for baseline calculations of JI projects . As these values are developed for 2008-2012 only, using their linear trends between 2008-2010, and 2010-2012, extrapolations are made to 2020.<br />In the forecast it is assumed that due to the limitations built in the regulations the growth of CHP capacities will be slower than in the recent years. The forecast also assumes a slight increase in overall equipment efficiencies with regard to technological development. Instead data of the previous report based on the forecast of the capacity plan of MAVIR, the actual figures of Cogen Hungary, including both gas engine and turbine technology are used and a modest growth with decreasing rate is assumed.', NULL, NULL, 'HU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.12', 'Monitoring is implemented through the yearly energy production and fuel use data of the individual CHP plants. These data are mandatorily provided to the Hungarian Energy Office on a monthly and to MAVIR on a yearly basis.', NULL, 'HU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.11ff, 36', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(716, 'HU-ENS-05', NULL, '5', 'Support of renewable- based power generation', 'Promote renewables in order to meet EU targets', 'The support described in the previous report is maintained with some changes that serve the protection of forests and the safeguarding of the Hungarian power system&rsquo;s stability. Similarly to CHP, power generation from renewable energy sources is supported by mandatory purchase of such power subsidised feed-in tariffs.<br />The primary objective is to ensure that Hungary comply with its international commitments as a part of the general GHG mitigation policy of the European Union. Hungary&rsquo;s original commitments were to increase the share of renewable based power generation to 3.6%, and the share of overall renewable energy to 5% by 2010, this target was already surpassed in 2005.<br />In order to ensure the stability of the national power system first a 3-zone tariff system was introduced , then this was refined and differentiated by generation technology in order to offset the disadvantages of some weather-dependent technologies, such as wind or hydro.<br />The new VET plans to limit or deny subsidy from power plants fuelled by forestry-originated biomass in order to protect sustainable forest management.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2668', NULL, '4425', NULL, '5284', NULL, NULL, 'The emission reduction can be calculated by comparing the energy production data to a baseline scenario, where the same amount of electricity is generated in the Hungarian Power system. The specific CO2 emission of the JI projects referred to earlier can be used as a basis.', NULL, NULL, 'HU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.14', 'Monitoring is through the yearly energy production and fuel use (where applicable, such as biomass plants) data of individual plants. These data are provided mandatory to the Hungarian Energy Office on a monthly and to MAVIR on a yearly basis.', NULL, 'HU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.13ff, 36', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(717, 'HU-ENS-06', NULL, '6', 'Land-based support for energy crops and forests', 'Assist growing plant for energy use', 'In line with the priorities of National Rural Development Plan, Decree 28/2005. FVM provides for financial support for various agricultural activities that are entitled for support from the European Agricultural Orientation and Guarantee Fund. For these purposes additional national support may be obtained. The decree allocates EUR 946 000 for the production of energy crops (both wood and herbaceous plants). The detailed regulation of the support is codified by 74/2005. (VIII. 22.) FVM. The latter decree defines which plant classifies ad energy crop, maximises the area that can obtain financial support and the obtainable finance: for wheat, corn, rape and sunflower together it is 16 000 ha and EUR 27/ha, for energy grass 10 000 ha and 32 EUR/ha and for energy forest 2 500 ha and 194.13 EUR/ha.', '2005', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Although the energy crops act as short-term carbon sinks, due to the short rotation it is not considered as GHG mitigation effect. The major impact of the measure is that all plants grown on the supported lands will be used either directly as fuel (energy grass, wood) or indirectly as raw material for automotive fuel or biogas.', NULL, NULL, 'HU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.18', 'Implementation is monitored via the support system managed by MVH. All supports are allocated via a regulated application process, that provides enough data about the lands and planned energy plants for the monitoring of the impact of the measure. Thus the main indicators of monitoring are of land, type of energy crop, expected yield.', 'Mitigation effects included in forecasts for other measures', 'HU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.18, 36', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(718, 'HU-ENS-07', NULL, '7', 'Additional land-based support for energy crops and forests', 'Assist growing plant for energy use', 'Decree 33/2007. (IV. 26.) FVM of the Minister of Agriculture and Rural Development provides for additional land-based support for energy plant/crop production, in accordance with 1973/2004/EC. Strict criteria are set (the producer must have valid sales contract with respectable market player(s), financial deposit is made, etc.) and the maximum value of the support is 45 EUR/ha.', '2007', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Although the energy crops act as short-term carbon sinks, due to the short rotation it is not considered as GHG mitigation effect. The major impact of the measure is that all plants grown on the supported lands will be used either directly as fuel (energy grass, wood) or indirectly as raw material for automotive fuel or biogas.', NULL, NULL, 'HU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.19', 'Implementation is monitored via the support system managed by MVH. All supports are allocated via a regulated application process, that provides enough data about the lands and planned energy plants for the monitoring of the impact of the measure. Thus the main indicators of monitoring are of land, type of energy crop, expected yield.', 'Mitigation effects included in forecasts for other measures', 'HU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.19, 36', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(719, 'HU-ENS-08', NULL, '8', 'Life extension of the Paks nuclear plant', 'Extend nuclear-based power generation for at least 20 years', 'In the Resolution 85/2005 (XI.23) OGy. of the Parliament, the life extension and capacity increase of the Paks nuclear power plant was approved.The four units of the Paks plant were commissioned between 1982-87. Currently the total capacity of the four units is 1866 MW. The Paks plant is the base power station of the Hungarian power system supplying about 40% of the total power production at low costs with no GHG emissions. The planned technical lifetime of the units ends between 2012-17,  but all investigations show that the operation can safely be extended by at least 20 years. In the framework of the retrofits needed for the life-extension, the capacity of the plant will be increased by same 150 MW, chiefly through the improvement of control systems and use of upgraded fuel cells.', '2005', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1477', NULL, '1477', NULL, NULL, 'All the generated power of the individual units will substitute power that should be generated in other (fossil) power plants or imported, if the life extension did not take place.<br />It is very difficult to establish a baseline for calculation the actual emission reduction as there is practically no alternative to the life extension If the life extension did not happen, 50% of the so missing power would be covered by fossil plants, partly utilising some existing reserve capacities (e.g. in the Dunamenti plant) partly from new fossil, most likely natural gas fired CCGT  lants.<br />The average specific CO2 emission is assumed as 0.4 kg/kWh, on the basis of the average value of the most modern capacities of the Hungarian power system. &bull; The other 50% of the power would come mostly from imports and a much smaller share from renewable sources.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'The amount of generated power', NULL, 'HU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.19f, 36', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(720, 'HU-ENS-09', NULL, '9', 'Support for end-user renewable energy', 'Larger share of renewables', 'Promoting the use of renewable energies is one of the priorities of the ESEEAP. Two of its sub-programmes address this area:<br />&bull; Promoting alternative (primarily biomass fuelled) firing systems and<br />&bull; Increasing the utilisation of renewables in general.<br />This objective is still reflected in the existing support system.<br />On a much larger scale the Environment and Energy Operational Programme (KEOP), whose application possibilities will be finalised in September 2007, also addresses the problem on the end-user side, too. Among the planned project types of KEOP the following end-user type projects are present:<br />&bull; Supporting the instalment of the most up-to-date heat pump systems for heating and cooling purposes. <br />&bull; Supporting the establishment of solar power utilization systems: provided partially or entirely for the energy utilization of consumers. Operating photovoltaic systems will reduce the use of fossil fuels in generating electric energy; and operating solar collector systems can diminish the fossil fuel usage in the production of hot water and heating energy.<br />&bull; Supporting energy conscious architectural solutions, passive solar energy', '2007', NULL, NULL, NULL, '53', NULL, '95', NULL, '139', NULL, NULL, 'The related CO2 emission reduction is calculated differently for the two basic project types:<br />&bull; For power generation type projects those specific reference CO2 emission factors are used that were developed for baseline calculations of JI projects. It is noted, however, that the indicated savings are primary energy savings, therefore &ndash; although the projects in question are end-user projects &ndash; the factors of the generation type projects are used, disregarding distribution losses.  In order to calculate the electricity generation related to the given primary energy uses, the forecast average plant efficiencies of the big power plants (without the Paks nuclear) is used.<br />&bull; For the fossil heat replacement type projects (heat generation and solar) the emission reduction is calculated with the fuel mix of the residential and communal sector.', NULL, NULL, 'HU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.31', 'Achieved energy saving', NULL, 'HU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.30f, 38', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(721, 'HU-ENC-01', NULL, '10', 'Energy Saving and Energy Efficiency Action Programme (ESEEAP)', 'Strategy document for energy efficiency', 'Strategy document for energy efficiency, from legal point of view, the Energy Saving and Energy Efficiency Action Programme (ESEEAP) adopted by the resolution of the Government 1107/1999.(X.8.) Korm. is still in force and effective, although many of its targets and tools have become outdated since 1999. ESEEAP came into effect in 2000 and is to run until 2010. The Action Programme also includes initiatives related to renewable energy sources. The Action Programme lists 15 specific policy measures. The overall goals of the Action Programme are: 3,5%/year reduction of energy intensity; the saving of 75 PJ/year of primary energy use; reduction of 50 kt/year of SO2 and 5 Mt/year of CO2 emissions, increase of renewable energy production.', '2000', '2010', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'HU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.10', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(722, 'HU-ENC-02', NULL, '11', 'National Energy Efficiency Action Plan for 2007-2009', 'Strategy document for energy efficiency', 'The objective of the Action Plan is to ensure the compliance with the directive 2006/32/EC of the European Parliament, which prescribes an overall national indicative energy savings target of 9% for the ninth year of application of the Directive. The Action Plan includes the reinforcement of some already operative programmes and introduces new measures. Special attention is paid to labelling of household and office appliances, speed limit for cars, state subsidy or tax reduction for the procurement of efficient appliances, P+R systems to promote public transportation.', '2007', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'HU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.10', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(723, 'HU-ENC-03', NULL, '12', 'Energy tax and environmental levy', 'Incentives for energy saving, funding for nature conservation', 'A high level regulation (Act LXXXVIII of 2003) introduced the energy tax on the sales and imports of electric power and natural gas. Sales to residential consumer are exempt for the duty of paying the tax. The amount of the tax currently is HUF 186/MWh of electricity, and HUF 56/GJ of natural gas.<br />Act. LXXXIX of 2003 introduced the environmental levies in order to reduce the burden of the environment, protect nature, promote environmental awareness, and &ndash; not least - to provide funds for nature conservation. The objectives also include the use of best available technologies.', '2003', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'In order to compare how strong the incentive for improving energy efficiency is, it is useful to compare the amount of energy tax to average energy prices (see the following table). Even so the actual GHG mitigation effect is not possible to quantify, since any mitigation may be the result of several incentives and policies together.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'The effects of the measure are monitored directly through the amount of tax and levy, and/or the actual quantity of energy sales/pollutants the tax and levies are based on.', 'Mitigation effects not directly quantifiable, but included in the overall emission forecasts', 'HU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.21f, 37', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(724, 'HU-ENC-04', NULL, '13', 'Energy audits in industry and the communal sector', 'Identify energy saving opportunities; increase energy awareness', 'It is widely recognised that demand side energy efficiency actions can only be effective if they are preceded by energy audits that can identify the most efficient course of action. Therefore energy audits have been supported by various programmes in the past, such as the Energy Saving and Energy Efficiency Action Programme (ESEEAP), UNDP-GEF Municipal Energy Efficiency Programme and Sz&eacute;chenyi Plan, and they were also encouraged by including them as a precondition of several financial support mechanisms for energy efficiency projects (e.g. Energy Efficiency Credit Fund, Phare Co-financed Loan Programme). <br />The original resolution (ESEEAP) was the basis for all these measures, it is in still in effect until 2010. The main tools of its implementation were the annually revised energy efficiency programmes (see the previous report), but in the most recent support framework (NEP 2007) there is no provision for energy audits, mainly due to lack of funds. The UNDP-GEF programme would also support energy audits (in the municipal sector) but the support is also suspended temporarily from January, 2007.<br />Still, ESEEAP is effective and it is expected that energy audits will receive further support before 2010, when the resources of the New Hungary Development Plan will be available and possibly onwards.', '2000', '2010', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'As to the future, it is not possible to make reliable forecasts as to the achievable GHG mitigation because:<br />&bull; savings depend on how much of the audits&rsquo; recommendations are actually implemented;<br />&bull; the future of available supports is uncertain, especially after 2010;<br />&bull; much of the industrial audits do not use the available support but are financed directly by the industry owners.', NULL, NULL, 'HU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.22f', 'Number of energy audits conducted; energy saving potential identified', 'Mitigation effects not directly quantifiable, but included in the overall emission forecasts', 'HU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.22f, 37', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `pam` (`id`, `pam_identifier`, `cluster`, `pam_no`, `name_pam`, `objective_of_measure`, `description_pam`, `start`, `ende`, `red_2005_val`, `red_2005_text`, `red_2010_val`, `red_2010_text`, `red_2015_val`, `red_2015_text`, `red_2020_val`, `red_2020_text`, `cumulative_2008_2012`, `explanation_basis_of_mitigation_estimates`, `factors_resulting_in_emission_reduction`, `include_common_reduction`, `documention_source`, `indicator_monitor_implementation`, `general_comment`, `reference`, `description_impact_on_non_ghg`, `costs_per_tonne`, `costs_per_year`, `costs_description`, `costs_documention_source`, `remarks`) VALUES
(725, 'HU-ENC-05', NULL, '14', 'New legislation for the energy efficiency of buildings', 'Reduced energy consumption for space heating', 'The regulation introduced new standards for the energy performance of buildings. Both the methodology of evaluation (thermal calculations) and some key parameters (e.g. U-values and normalised heat loss) are prescribed. Meeting with these prescribed values are the precondition for the issuance of licences for construction or major refurbishment of buildings. The objective is to achieve considerable savings through stricter performance requirements.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '303', NULL, '681', NULL, '1059', NULL, NULL, 'The emission reduction can only be estimated, using the average number of homes constructed annually (40,000) and the difference of allowed heat loss for an average home. It is also noted that when the achieved savings are to be determined in a specific year, the accumulated saving shall be taken into account since the policy was effective, as all those homes generate savings that were constructed/reconstructed up to the specific year.', NULL, NULL, 'HU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.25', 'Number of issued Building Energy Certificates, number / heated volume of new or reconstructed housing', NULL, 'HU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.24f, 37', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(726, 'HU-ENC-06', NULL, '15', 'Improving energy awareness', 'Increased energy awareness of the public leading to concrete savings', 'One important action of the ESEEAP is to assist reaching its overall objectives by providing state-of-the-art information and training via the educational system and the organisation and operation of advisory networks and consumer offices, as well as via advertisements, media, etc. Another specific point of action is the promotion of the use of energy efficiency labels. The relevant legislation set an overall 10 PJ energy saving until 2010 via energy awareness raising tools.', '2000', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Number of project applications, information outreach indicators.', 'Mitigation effects not directly quantifiable, but included in the overall emission forecasts', 'HU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.25f, 37', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(727, 'HU-ENC-07', NULL, '16', 'Support for the improvement of industrial energy efficiency', 'Reduced energy consumption in industy', 'One of the actions of the ESEEAP was aimed at reducing industrial energy consumption. The objectives of the action were <br />&bull; modernisation of energy processes of industrial production, <br />&bull; improving thermal insulation, <br />&bull; improving the efficiency of energy consuming equipment and <br />&bull; improving the efficiency of energy generating equipment.<br />The form of support foreseen was preferential loans, but no particular amount was allocated. The expected target reduction of industrial energy use was 8.5 PJ until 2010. Similarly to other actions of the ESEEAP the primary tools of implementation were the annually revised energy efficiency programs and some other existing support schemes. NEP2007, however does not include industrial energy efficiency components.', '2000', '2010', NULL, NULL, '63', NULL, '73', NULL, '32', NULL, NULL, 'The forecast emission reduction achieved by these sources, however is maintained as the technical lifetime of the already implemented projects is more than 10 years, therefore the generated savings will still appear in 2010 and 2015. In 2020, however, the savings achieved by the projects implemented up to 2004 are assumed to diminish.', NULL, NULL, 'HU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.29', 'Achieved energy saving.', NULL, 'HU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.28f, 38', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(728, 'HU-ENC-08', NULL, '17', 'Support for the improvement of residential/communal energy efficiency', 'Reduced energy consumption in the residential and communal sector', 'Similarly to industrial energy efficiency improvement and other actions of the ESEEAP the primary tools of implementation were the annually revised energy efficiency programs (SZT-EN, NEP), but similarly important was that residential/communal energy efficiency projects were included in other existing support schemes, such as the Energy Saving Loan Fund (EHA) or the Phare Co-financed Loan Programme. <br />A recent development and new feature of these programmes is that the emphasis is shifted from the sheer subsidy to loan programmes. A good example is NEP-2007, which provides HUF 2.6 billion for <br />&bull; improvement of thermal performance of buildings (insulation, window replacement, heating system and DHW system modernisation) and<br />&bull; utilisation of renewables in the residential sector.<br />While NEP-2007 provides subsidy for maximum 15% of the investment it is supplemented by max 85% preferential loan provided form the &ldquo;For a Successful Hungary&rdquo; Residential Energy Saving Loan. The budget of the Loan is HUF 16 billion.', '2000', '2010', NULL, NULL, '222', NULL, '377', NULL, '459', NULL, NULL, 'The foreseen energy savings achieved by the past two years&rsquo; NEP supports are the followings:<br />NEP 2006: 95 TJ/year<br />NEP 2007: 518 TJ/year<br />Experience with NEP 2007 so far, however, show that the lower level of subsidy considerably reduced the attractiveness of the programme. (Only one third of the expected number of applications arrived until May, 2007). Therefore the forecasted savings may be considered optimistic, so in the emission reduction forecast a more conservative approach is adopted.', NULL, NULL, 'HU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.30', 'Achieved energy saving.', NULL, 'HU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.29f, 38', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(729, 'HU-ENC-10', NULL, '18', 'Modernising district heating systems', 'Improved efficiency in district heating', 'Similarly to the other ESEEAP actions, the support was provided through the SZT-EN and NEP programmes and the EHA and Phare funds. By today only the EHA remained as active source of support, but it is expected that district heating will be among the priorities of the future National Energy Efficiency Action Plan for 2007-2009.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '122', NULL, '139', NULL, '160', NULL, NULL, 'The forecast of further emission reduction is based on similar assumptions to those of the residential energy efficiency programmes. However, a stronger degradation of subsidy intensity is assumed, due to the low number of DH schemes, and the replicability of projects is lower.', NULL, NULL, 'HU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.32', 'Achieved energy saving.', NULL, 'HU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.31f, 38', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(730, 'HU-ENC-11', NULL, '19', 'UNDP-GEF energy efficiency programme for Municipal Energy Conservation', 'Mitigate the initial barriers of energy efficiency investments', 'The goal of the UNDP/GEF funded financial tool is to mitigate the initial barriers of energy efficiency investments. To achieve this, the fund supports the preparation of energy audits and feasibility studies.<br />Energy audit is the starting element of the energy efficiency project development process. The right direction of the process can not be ensured without an audit. Experiences show that the cost of the audit is refunded from the recommended no-cost and low-cost measures. Despite this there is little willingness among the municipalities to finance the project preparation solely from own resources without external financial support.<br />The reasons of this are partly financial and partly originate from the lack of knowledge. The financial barriers can be overcome by external support. This support is given by the government and the GEF/UNDP municipal project in the form of direct subsidies (grant) and interest free loan.<br />The results of the program so far have been the followings:<br />&bull; Trainings with altogether 2000 participants.<br />&bull; Publication of a &ldquo;Good practice&rdquo; booklet series, and a book entitled &ldquo;For municipalities about energy&rdquo;.<br />&bull; Support for more than 1000 energy audits/feasibility studies in 235 municipal institutions.<br />&bull; Based on these audits and studies 22 projects were implemented with 22,000 t/year CO2 foreseen reduction.<br />&bull; Contribution to the establishment of the Association of Energy Efficient Municipalities', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Number of projects, energy savings achieved.', NULL, 'HU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.32f, 38', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(731, 'HU-ENC-12', NULL, '20', 'EHA - Energy Saving Loan Fund (German Coal Aid)', 'Reduction of energy losses of energy generation, distribution and use', 'The EHA is still in place and would provide aid for the reduction of energy losses of energy generation, distribution and use; procurement and use of modern, lower energy consumption process equipment; heat recovery and the utilisation of renewable energies; cogeneration; thermal insulation projects; better space heating control, especially in district heating. <br />The aid is provided in the form of preferential loan with an interest rate of base rate / 3 + 2.5%.<br />Due to the strict conditions of the loan and the much lower base rate than at the time when the facility was designed, EHA has lost much of its attractiveness, and no applications have been submitted recently.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Number of projects, energy savings achieved.', NULL, 'HU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.33, 38', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(732, 'HU-ENC-13', NULL, '21', 'Phare Co-Financed Energy Efficiency Loan Construction', 'Energy efficiency', 'A 10-year energy efficiency loan construction established within the frame of European Union&#39;s Phare programme, but this facility was stopped with the expiry of the Phare programme in 2006.', NULL, '2006', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Number of projects, energy savings achieved.', NULL, 'HU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.33, 38', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(733, 'HU-ENC-14', NULL, '22', 'National Energy Saving Programme (SZT-EN, NEP)', 'Energy efficiency', 'The Programme is the sequel of the Energy Chapter of the Sz&eacute;chenyi Plan, which started in 2001. The priorities and conditions of support and the budget are reviewed annually according to changing emphases in the energy policy. <br />In 2005 due to the disproportion between the demand for support and the size of available funds the NEP was temporarily suspended but is was continued in 2006 and 2007. <br />In 2006 NEP provided subsidy for residential energy efficiency projects i.e. for the improvement of thermal performance of buildings (insulation, window replacement, heating system and DHW system modernisation) from a budget of HUF 880 million. The subsidy was maximum 30% of the total project cost.<br />In 2007 the budget was substantially raised to HUF 2.6 billion, but its maximum was reduced to 15% of the project costs. Utilisation of renewables in the residential sector was added to the priorities and the offered resources were supplemented by a preferential loan facility.', '2001', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Number of projects, energy savings achieved.', NULL, 'HU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.34, 38', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(734, 'HU-ENC-15', NULL, '23', 'KIOP-2004-1.7.0.f (Operative Programme for the Environment and Infrastructure Environmental friendly development of energy management for 2004-2006)', 'Energy efficiency and increased use of Renewables', 'KIOP was one of the five operative programmes of the National Development Plan. The key objectives of the action are: <br />&bull; increased utilisation of renewable energies,<br />&bull; improved energy efficiency .<br />The programme was closed in 2006. Altogether 106 applications were submitted and 43 of these were successful. Thy typical supported project types were the followings:<br />&bull; modernisation of district heating systems<br />&bull; combined heat and power projects<br />&bull; energy efficiency improvements of municipal institutions<br />&bull; windpower projects<br />&bull; biomass projects<br />&bull; geothermal energy utilisation, heat pumps<br />&bull; small-scale hydro<br />&bull; solar collectors<br />From 2007 onwards KIOP will be replaced by KEOP, whose support facilities will be created by late 2007.', NULL, '2006', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Number of projects, energy savings achieved.', NULL, 'HU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.34, 38', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(735, 'HU-ENC-16', NULL, '24', 'Support for the energy efficient reconstruction or modernisation of pre-fab technology buildings (&ldquo;Panel Plus Programme&rdquo;)', 'Energy efficiency in old buildings', 'Due to their large number, age and the technology used in their construction, the buildings constructed from pre-fabricated concrete elements between the end of the 1960s and 1990s (&ldquo;panel&rdquo; buildings) represent large potential in residential energy saving. The same applies to the &ldquo;mass-produced&rdquo; housing constructed with some other technologies. In order to realise some of this saving potential support was provided for the energy efficient reconstruction or modernisation of such buildings in the framework of the so-called &ldquo;Panel Programme&rdquo;.  <br />As a part of the &ldquo;For a Successful Hungary&rdquo; Residential Energy Saving Loan this support is continued under the name of &ldquo;Panel Plus Programme&rdquo;. The Panel Plus is managed by the Hungarian Development Bank.<br /> The supported measures are: <br />&bull; reconstruction, refurbishment resulting in energy saving;<br />&bull; modernisation of building services systems (heating, hot water supply, ventilation, etc.)<br />&bull; improvement of the direct environment (playgrounds, pavements, etc.).<br />Maximum 66% or 75% of the total project cost or 800,000-900,000 HUF/home can be provided in the form of loan. The interest rate of the max. 15-year loan is the 3-month EURIBOR + 2,5-3,5%/year.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Number of projects, energy savings achieved.', NULL, 'HU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.34f, 38', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(736, 'HU-ENC-17', NULL, '25', '&ldquo;Szem&uuml;nk F&eacute;nye&rdquo; Program for the energy efficiency of educational institutions [NEW]', 'Energy efficiency in educational institutions', 'The Programme, which started in 2006,  is a third party financing (ESCO) scheme financed by loans from OTP Bank, Hungary&rsquo;s leading bank. The loan budget provided by OTP is HUF 50 billion. The programme offers energy improvement projects (heating, lighting, controls) for educational institutions. The programme starts with an energy audit that is free of charge for the institution, then a contract is signed for the implementation. The institutions borrow and operate the equipment installed.', '2006', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Number of projects, energy savings achieved.', 'Mitigation effects included in the forecasts for related measures', 'HU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.35, 38', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(737, 'HU-TRA-01', NULL, '26', 'New priorities in the Transport Operative Programme of the NHDP', 'Improvement of urban and suburban public transport', 'As far as network development is concerned, the primary objective is the modernisation of permanent-track transport ensuring the transportation of large amounts of people in an environmentally sound manner (in Budapest: the underground and trams, in provincial cities as Debrecen, Miskolc and Szeged: trams) and the implementation of other developments to improve the conditions and safety of urban transport (for example, the creation of intermodal junctions, of P+R (Park &amp; Ride) and B+R (Bike&amp;Ride) parking lots, traffic calming, traffic regulation and traffic control). On the most intensive traffic routes, the task is to link up permanent-track networks and to establish mode-switching solutions to minimise the number of transfers. For the routes leading to the junctions from regional directions, the objective is to achieve full intermodality, including quick transfer options, integrated tariff systems, achieving adequate services and service frequency and the coordination of  timetables of the various modes of transport. The establishment and development of intermodal junctions is required and justified primarily in the immediate neighbourhood of heavy traffic railway and underground stations and their meeting points. Important elements of the development of urban transport include the construction of intelligent transport systems, the improvement of passenger information and comfort and ensuring clear access. <br />In Budapest, the completion and modernisation of the suburban rail service based on the existing railway infrastructure is of outstanding importance. The start of the modernisation of the 14 suburban railway lines extending into Budapest (including 11 M&Aacute;V and 3 H&Eacute;V lines) will facilitate the commuting of the population of Budapest agglomeration. The development also including railway terminals will enable that modern, comfortable, regularly scheduled and environmentally sound rail transport gain prominence over individual automotive transport causing congestion, traffic jams and considerable environmental pollution. The possibility of solutions using the rail and permanent-track urban infrastructure without changing between transport vehicles should also be considered for suburban railway developments. The construction of a third and fourth track may become necessary on the TEN elements leading to Budapest in order to ensure undisturbed passenger traffic, isolated from goods transport. <br />The possibilities of linking up local and non-local public transport systems should also be considered for major provincial cities. This can be done by the establishment of intermodal centres or by extending the tram lines toward nearby settlements (operating trams as suburban trains). The horizontal objectives of environmental protection and equal opportunities must be given increased priority on drawing up and implementing the developments defined. <br />As a result of these developments the new underground line considerably improving the traversability of the capital will be completed and the modernisation of the suburban train service will commence. The modernisation of passenger trains is part of the development of the suburban rail transport. The public transport infrastructure and the service quality will also improve substantially in provincial cities, which will presumably have the effect that fewer people will choose individual transport, which will reduce the congestion of roads and environmental pollution and improve transport safety and habitability.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'The impacts of the planned actions being rather indirect, it is not possible to forecast the emission reductions achieved by these. Some sort of forecast will be possible only for some of the individual actions when the concrete targets will be clear and input data according to the monitoring indicators are available.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Not defined in the relevant document, however the following indicators are well applicable:<br />&bull; share of local and interurban public transport within modes of transport;<br />&bull; changes in passenger-km of local and interurban public transport;<br />&bull; changes in the length of local and interurban public transport network detailing the transport modes (railway, road);<br />&bull; occupancy indicators of local and interurban public transport;<br />&bull; share of bicycle transport within modes of transport;<br />&bull; changes in the length of bicycle paths', NULL, 'HU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.39f', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(738, 'HU-TRA-02', NULL, '27', 'Transport related policies and measures in NEP-II', 'Reduction of pollution emission from transport', '&bull; An important specific and operative objective within the Action Programme of Urban Environmental Quality is the reduction of urban environmental problems that are due to the traffic, particularly in densely populated areas of towns. <br />&bull; The Action Programme of Climate Change also includes a transport related operative objective, i.e. the reduction of pollution emission from transport, that is to be achieved by:<br />o Accelerating the modernization rate of the vehicle stock<br />o Moderation of the environmental impact of freight transportation: supporting the propagation of environmentally friendly transportation ways, shifting freight transportation from trucks to railway<br />o Support for environmentally sustainable means of transport.<br />The target emission reduction to be achieved by the measures of the Action Programme is the following:<br />CO2  15 %<br />NOx  70 %<br />CO    60 %<br />CH    50 %<br />Particles 70 %', '2003', '2008', NULL, NULL, '925', NULL, '2118', NULL, '5279', NULL, NULL, 'Similarly to K&Ouml;ZOP, due to their indirect nature it is not possible to forecast the emission reductions achieved by these actions. Still, in the course of modelling and forecasting Hungary&rsquo;s GHG emissions some assumptions were made with all the planned measures in mind and with respect to expected growth rate of the economy, the forecast increase of the road network system, the average distance travelled by the different vehicles (primarily lorries and heavy transport vehicles), the price elasticity of automotive fuels and the expected growth of vehicle stock.', NULL, NULL, 'HU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.41', '&bull; share of local and interurban public transport within modes of transport;<br />&bull; changes in passenger-km of local and interurban public transport;<br />&bull; changes in the length of local and interurban public transport network detailing the transport modes (railway, road);<br />&bull; occupancy indicators of local and interurban public transport;<br />&bull; share of bicycle transport within modes of transport;<br />&bull; changes in the length of bicycle paths', NULL, 'HU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.40f', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(739, 'HU-TRA-03', NULL, '28', 'National targets and support for renewable automotive fuels', 'Support for renewable automotive fuels', 'Further to the relevant policy and targets of the European Parliament and the European Commission Hungary also set targets regarding the share of renewable fuels (bio-diesel and ETBE produced from bio-ethanol). According to the earlier legislation (Governmental Decree 2233/2004. (IX. 22.) Korm.) its value shall reach 2% within the total automotive fuel consumption by 2010. This decree was amended by Governmental Decree 2058/2006 (III. 27.) Korm. which adopted the EU targets, i.e. stipulated that the share of renewable fuels shall reach 5.75% by 2010 . Earlier the main tool for achieving the target was an excise-duty refund system planned to stay in place until 2010. The new legislation also stipulates that proper financial incentives shall be used to facilitate the reaching the set goals. These financial incentives are planned to include the replacement of the excide duty replacement by  differentiated (reduced) tax content of fuel prices that contain renewable components.', NULL, '2010', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'According to the study the achievable GHG reduction ranges from 0,3 to 1,8 kg CO2 eq. depending on the feedstock and the fuels used. The wide range well shows that it would be irresponsible to make any statements regarding Hungary&rsquo;s emission reductions as yet, since the construction of the production capacities are in the preparation phase. Still, just to illustrate the order of magnitude, using the above range, it is calculated that the use of the expected quantity of biofuels in 2010 may result in saving of 0,04-0,26 kt per year.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Quantity of bio-fuels sold/used. The Government Decree 42/2005. (III. 10.) Korm makes it obligatory for all traders of bio-fuels to make a detailed report every year for the ministry responsible for transport.', NULL, 'HU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.42ff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(740, 'HU-AGR-01', 'CL-HU-AGR-01', '29', 'National Agri-Envrionmental Programme (NAEP)', 'Support of agricultural production methods that are environmentally friendly', 'The NAEP, a sub-programme of the National Environmental Programme, approved by the Government Resolution 2253/1999 (X.7.) Korm, includes several horizontal and zonal targets. One of them is to increase the territorial proportion of semi-natural forest management. NAEP also looks at afforestation as a tool of implementing some of its measures, such a forest plantation on flood areas in order to protect wetland habitat. The NAEP objectives were integrated into the agri-environmental measures of the National Rural Development Plan (NRDP) in 2004.', '1999', NULL, NULL, 'CL-HU-AGR-01', NULL, 'CL-HU-AGR-01', NULL, 'CL-HU-AGR-01', NULL, 'CL-HU-AGR-01', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Number of projects supported; Number of events; Fund spent on projects', NULL, 'HU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.46', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(741, 'HU-AGR-02', 'CL-HU-AGR-01', '30', 'The SAPARD Plan of Hungary (2000 &ndash; 2006)', 'Reducing the negative impacts of agriculture on the environment', 'Decree No. 53/2001. (VIII. 17.) FVM identified Hungary&rsquo;s priorities in agriculture and rural development in order to prepare for the optimum use of the EU&rsquo;s SAPARD funds. This decree (SAPARD Plan for short) was based on, among others the NAEP. Reducing the negative impacts of agriculture on the environment is listed among the SAPARD Plan&rsquo;s specific objectives and the emphasis on environmental considerations is an integral part of the proposed strategy. The latter is planned to be put into practice by promoting natural farming methods.', '2000', '2006', NULL, 'CL-HU-AGR-01', NULL, 'CL-HU-AGR-01', NULL, 'CL-HU-AGR-01', NULL, 'CL-HU-AGR-01', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Number of projects supported; Number of events; Fund spent on projects', NULL, 'HU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.46', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(742, 'HU-AGR-03', 'CL-HU-AGR-01', '31', 'Nitrate Action Programme', 'Protection of waters against pollution caused by nitrates from agricultural sources.', 'Government Decree 49/2001. (IV. 3.) Korm on protection against the nitrate contamination of waters from agricultural sources (Nitrate Decree for short) contains provisions in line with Council Directive 91/676/EEC of 12 December 1991 concerning the protection of waters against pollution caused by nitrates from agricultural sources. In a manner similar to the directive, the Nitrate Decree, which came into effect in 2001, contains the list of settlements in nitrate sensitive areas, the rules of &ldquo;Good Farming Practice in manuring&rdquo; that farmers are obliged to keep and the time-schedule of implementation in the form of an action plan.', '2001', '2006', NULL, 'CL-HU-AGR-01', NULL, 'CL-HU-AGR-01', NULL, 'CL-HU-AGR-01', NULL, 'CL-HU-AGR-01', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Number of projects supported; Number of events; Fund spent on projects', NULL, 'HU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.46', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(743, 'HU-AGR-04', 'CL-HU-AGR-01', '32', 'New Nitrate Action Programme', 'Protection of waters against pollution caused by nitrates from agricultural sources.', 'The earlier Government Decree 49/2001. (IV. 3.) Korm on protection against the nitrate contamination of waters from agricultural sources (Nitrate Decree for short) referred to in the previous report was replaced and partly superseded by Government Decree 27/2006. (II. 7.) Korm., amended by Government Decree 81/2007. (IV.25.) Korm.<br />The new decree also identifies the nitrate sensitive areas, contains an extended list of settlements in these areas (67 settlements were deleted from the list, 320 added), states the general rules of protection against nitrate pollution and prescribes an overall, coherent, nation-wide action plan. The annex of the earlier decree on the rules of &ldquo;Good Farming Practice in manuring&rdquo; remained in effect, until this new action programme, conform with Directive 2003/35/EC, is ready. The new decree also extends some of the earlier deadlines such that for the isolation of manure storages.<br />In order to fund the Action Programme, a project was launched, including a detailed study published in September, 2006. The project&rsquo;s aim was to establish the conditions for developing environmentally conscious and competitive agricultural practice and technology for protecting groundwater against nitrate pollution. Vulnerable zones will be reconsidered taking into account the opportunities of developing environmentally sound agricultural practice without reducing agricultural competitiveness. The project was to develop a GIS to be tested in pilot areas. At the level of agricultural producers the aim of the project was to ensure the availability of information at local level, to improve opportunities for obtaining subsidies, the technological-financial elaboration of environmentally sound agricultural / animal husbandry / plant growing models by investigations in pilot areas, the development of the complex professional consultancy system, and the elaboration of project preparation manuals.', '2006', NULL, NULL, 'CL-HU-AGR-01', NULL, 'CL-HU-AGR-01', NULL, 'CL-HU-AGR-01', NULL, 'CL-HU-AGR-01', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Number of projects supported; Number of events; Fund spent on projects', NULL, 'HU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.46f', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(744, 'HU-AGR-05', 'CL-HU-AGR-01', '33', 'Agriculture and Rural Development Operative Programme (AVOP)', 'Environmentally friendly agriculture and the rational use of land; Environment-conscious and sustainable land use; Improvement of the status of the environment; Increasing afforestation.', 'AVOP is the part of the National Development Plan, which identifies the environmentally friendly agriculture and the rational use of land among the general objectives of rural development', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CL-HU-AGR-01', NULL, 'CL-HU-AGR-01', NULL, 'CL-HU-AGR-01', NULL, 'CL-HU-AGR-01', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Number of projects supported; Number of events; Fund spent on projects', NULL, 'HU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.47', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(745, 'HU-AGR-06', 'CL-HU-AGR-01', '34', 'New Hungary Rural Development Strategic Plan', 'Competitiveness of agriculture, forestry and food industry; Improvement of the condition of the environment; Quality of life in rural areas', 'The Plan is the sequel of AVOP. Its actions are grouped into three different sets:<br />- Set 1: Competitiveness of agriculture, forestry and food industry<br />- Set 2: Improvement of the condition of the environment.<br />- Set 3: Quality of life in rural areas<br />The three sets are supplemented by a Technical Assistance package.<br />GHG mitigation efforts are chiefly in Set 2. The most important objectives are in line with the following Community priorities:<br />- Biodiversity, traditional landscapes,<br />- Water management<br />- Climate change<br />The national priorities, stemming from the above are:<br />- Protection of Natura 2000 areas and other natural values<br />- Less Favoured Areas<br />- High Quality Water Management<br />- Increasing the forestry resources and their sustainable management<br />- Utilisation of biomass for energy generation<br />- Protection of soils<br />Quantitative targets of the GHG related actions of the New Hungary Rural Development Strategic Plan are:<br />1. Increase of energy crop production:  +4%<br />2. Renewable energy production from <br />agriculture and forestry 800 ktoe<br />3. Agricultural area for biomass production 300 th ha<br />4. Area of energy forests 60 th ha<br />5. Energy intensity of agriculture -2.5 TJ/billion HUF<br />6. Integrated farming area 600 th ha', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CL-HU-AGR-01', NULL, 'CL-HU-AGR-01', NULL, 'CL-HU-AGR-01', NULL, 'CL-HU-AGR-01', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Number of projects supported; Number of events; Fund spent on projects', NULL, 'HU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.47', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(746, 'HU-AGR-06', 'CL-HU-AGR-01', '35', 'Second National Environmental Programme - Thematic Action Programme of Climate Change', 'Broad environmental objectives', 'The Climate Change Operative Programme of the NEP-II: The action programme is aimed at the reduction of greenhouse gas emission, its contribution to anthropogenic climate change and at the same time at improvement of local and regional air quality. In addition, it contributes to the dissemination of environmentally friendly consumption habits and improvement of the quality of settlement environment. Promoting the reduction of atmospheric emissions from energy management activities, Development and dissemination of technologies related to the utilization of renewable energy sources (to subsidize investments), Reduction of pollution emission from transport, Reduction of greenhouse gases from agriculture and waste by strengthening carbon dioxide sink capacities, Research-development, horizontal measures.', '2003', '2008', NULL, 'CL-HU-AGR-01', NULL, 'CL-HU-AGR-01', NULL, 'CL-HU-AGR-01', NULL, 'CL-HU-AGR-01', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'HU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.48', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(747, 'HU-AGR-07', 'CL-HU-AGR-01', '36', 'Land-based support for energy crops and forests', 'To promote environment-friendly development of agriculture; rationalisation of land use and to assist to the realignment of rural areas.', 'In line with the priorities of National Rural Development Plan, Decree 28/2005. FVM provides for financial support for various agricultural activities that are entitled for support from the European Agricultural Orientation and Guarantee Fund. For these purposes additional national support may be obtained. The decree allocates EUR 946 000 for the production of energy crops (both wood and herbaceous plants). The detailed regulation of the support is codified by 74/2005. (VIII. 22.) FVM. The latter decree defines which plant classifies ad energy crop, maximises the area that can obtain financial support and the obtainable finance: for wheat, corn, rape and sunflower together it is 16 000 ha and EUR 27/ha, for energy grass 10 000 ha and 32 EUR/ha and for energy forest 2 500 ha and 194.13 EUR/ha.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CL-HU-AGR-01', NULL, 'CL-HU-AGR-01', NULL, 'CL-HU-AGR-01', NULL, 'CL-HU-AGR-01', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'HU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.46', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(748, 'HU-AGR-07', 'CL-HU-AGR-01', '37', 'Entry Level Scheme (ELSs)', 'Promote environmentally friendly farm management in each land use type to provide broad scale opportunity to farmers to enter commitments to reach environmental achievements in their farming practice', 'Elements of the ELS have already been introduced in Hungary in 2002-2003 under Government Resolution 2253/1999 (X. 7.) on the introduction of the National Agri-environment Programme. ELSs are designed to encourage farmers to use farming methods adapted to the local environmental and agricultural conditions, to target production systems suitable to soil and climate conditions and natural environment, with special attention to relevant environmental protection aspects.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CL-HU-AGR-01', NULL, 'CL-HU-AGR-01', NULL, 'CL-HU-AGR-01', NULL, 'CL-HU-AGR-01', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'HU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.46', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(749, 'HU-AGR-08', 'CL-HU-AGR-01', '38', 'Organic Farming Scheme', 'Encourage farmers using conventional farming methods to convert their production systems to organic production', 'Conversion to organic farming systems provides gains in terms of soil health and fertility, benefits for bio-diversity and wider landscape benefits through the use of organic soil cultivation, crop rotation and the absence of synthetic pesticides, herbicides and fertilisers. Besides organic farming contributes to reduced GHG emissions through the use of manure as fertiliser and the limited energy use.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CL-HU-AGR-01', NULL, 'CL-HU-AGR-01', NULL, 'CL-HU-AGR-01', NULL, 'CL-HU-AGR-01', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'HU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.46', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(750, 'HU-AGR-09', 'CL-HU-AGR-01', '39', 'Integrated Crop Management System (ICMS)', 'Environmentally beneficial extensification, especially the reduced, optimised use of fertilisers and pesticides, the considered (limited) application of dangerous substances and other accompanying benefits for the environment', 'The ICMS is designed to encourage farmers to use integrated farming methods of production in compliance with higher environmental standards, to optimise the use of fertilisers and pesticides and to apply all available means (equipment and know how) of sound farming. The application of integrated farming systems provides benefits in terms of soil conservation, water protection and bio diversity through the use of environmentally friendly crop patterns, cultivation techniques, nutrient management, crop rotations, as well as the optimised, limited use of synthetic pesticides, herbicides and fertilisers', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CL-HU-AGR-01', NULL, 'CL-HU-AGR-01', NULL, 'CL-HU-AGR-01', NULL, 'CL-HU-AGR-01', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'HU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.46', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(751, 'HU-AGR-10', 'CL-HU-AGR-01', '40', 'Support for meeting standards', 'Ensure that the requirements of the valid standards animal husbandry are met.', 'Within the support a separate &ldquo;sub-measure&rdquo; covers the area of environmental protection. The aim of this type of support is to ensure the adequate on-site placement and management of the organic manure and the storage in line with the environmental requirements. The form of support is provided by providing subsidy for the investment costs. In the framework of this support mechanism assistance is also provided for compliance with provisions concerning keeping and foddering technology, although reduction of enteric fermentation is not identified as a target.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CL-HU-AGR-01', NULL, 'CL-HU-AGR-01', NULL, 'CL-HU-AGR-01', NULL, 'CL-HU-AGR-01', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'HU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.46', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(752, 'CL-HU-AGR-01', 'CL-HU-AGR-01', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '57', NULL, '123', NULL, '206', NULL, NULL, 'The above discussed measures obviously have GHG mitigation effects, although, due to either their indirect nature or the lack of adequate data the impacts are very difficult to quantify. The more so because the overall GHG emissions of agriculture are much more influenced by other, stronger factors, such as the market mechanisms and demand for animals of organic products. There are other adverse effects, too. For example, considerable decrease in the use of fertilisers is highly unlikely, as in the past years the problem of Hungarian soils is not the excess of fertilisers, but rather &ndash; due to the negative balance of nutritive elements - the degradation of soil quality.', NULL, NULL, 'HU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.48', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(753, 'HU-LUC-01', 'CL-HU-LUC-01', '41', 'National Forest Programme 2006-2015', 'Increasing forest area', 'The National Forest Programme 2006-2015 sets the following strategy objectives:<br />- At least maintaining the current level of forestation but preferably its increase must be ensured. Neither the quantity nor the quality and value of the forests must not decrease.<br />- Use of wood in the society, as an environmentally friendly raw material, shall be encouraged.<br />- The Forest management shall ensure that the increased demands for wood would be met, without endangering sustainability.<br />- Knowledge and information on forests shall be increased in the society.<br />The key elements of implementing the strategic goals are the followings:<br />1. Protection of forests, of natural processes in the forests. Perseverance of biological and genetic values. Natural forest management.<br />2. Utilisation of forests. The competitiveness of forestry products shall be increased. Utilisation areas may be widened, with respect to industrial and energy-purpose utilisation of wood.<br />3. Development. Increase of forests with respect, however, to biodiversity, landscape, and erosion protection.<br />These elements are to be implemented through the following specialised targeted programs / support schemes:<br />1. Development of state owned forests<br />2. Development of private forests<br />3. Rural development, forestation, forest restructuring<br />4. Nature conservation in the forests<br />5. Modern forest protection<br />6. Rational utilisation of wood<br />7. Forestry management<br />8. Research, education, product development<br />9. Communication about the forests in order to improve the forest-human relationship', '2006', '2015', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CL-HU-LUC-01', NULL, 'CL-HU-LUC-01', NULL, 'CL-HU-LUC-01', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Increase of afforested area; type of forests (CO2 sequestration capability)', NULL, 'HU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.49f', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(754, 'HU-LUC-02', 'CL-HU-LUC-01', '42', 'New Hungary Rural Development Strategic Plan', 'Increasing forest area', 'Afforestation is among the top priorities and measures of the NHRDSP. The quantitative targets of the forestry related actions of the New Hungary Rural Development Strategic Plan are the followings:<br />1. Increase of the average area of private forests  +2.5 ha<br />2. Increase of the productivity of forests +0.5 m3/yr/ha<br />3. Ratio of forests in the total area 20%<br />4. Primary forestation +70 th ha<br />5. Area of forests in the environmental <br />protection programme 160 th ha', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CL-HU-LUC-01', NULL, 'CL-HU-LUC-01', NULL, 'CL-HU-LUC-01', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Increase of afforested area; type of forests (CO2 sequestration capability)', NULL, 'HU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.50f', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(755, 'HU-LUC-03', 'CL-HU-LUC-01', '43', 'National Agri-environment Programme', 'Increasing forest area', 'The NAEP, a sub-programme of the National Environmental Programme, approved by the Government Resolution 2253/1999 (X.7.) Korm, includes several horizontal and zonal targets. One of them is to increase the territorial proportion of semi-natural forest management. NAEP also looks at afforestation as a tool of implementing some of its measures, such as a forest plantation on flood areas in order to protect wetland habitat.', '1999', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CL-HU-LUC-01', NULL, 'CL-HU-LUC-01', NULL, 'CL-HU-LUC-01', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Increase of afforested area; type of forests (CO2 sequestration capability)', NULL, 'HU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.51', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(756, 'HU-LUC-04', 'CL-HU-LUC-01', '44', 'Act LIV of 1996 on the forests and their protection', 'Increasing the area of forests', 'Hungary has a very elaborate legislative framework for the protection of the forests, that ensures that forestry would be sustainable. The legislative framework is based upon the Act LIV of 1996 and the Decree 29/1997. (IV.30) FM on its implementation. Forestry activities are conducted in accordance with a regularly updated 10-year plan that is broken down into individual one-year operative plans. Both types of planning are approved by independent bodies.<br />The following afforestation schedule is set: in 2005: 10 000 ha, in 2006: 11 000 ha, and then this value is predicted to rise to 15000 hectare/year between 2007-2013. These forests are predicted to be planted on low and medium quality arable lands, as most of the grasses are under protection', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CL-HU-LUC-01', NULL, 'CL-HU-LUC-01', NULL, 'CL-HU-LUC-01', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Increase of afforested area; type of forests (CO2 sequestration capability)', NULL, 'HU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.51', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(757, 'CL-HU-LUC-01', 'CL-HU-LUC-01', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '630', NULL, '1857', NULL, '3524', NULL, NULL, '&ldquo;With measures&rdquo; scenario: it is assumed that  average afforestation rates in the past several years (~8,000 ha/year) are maintained until 2050', NULL, NULL, 'HU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.51', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(758, 'HU-WAM-01', NULL, '45', 'Act XLIII of 2000 on waste management', 'Create a framework for waste management that serve a reduction of energy and raw materials consumption by improving efficiency and reducing the volume of waste.', 'The Act put on emphasis on preventing the production of wastes, on recycling and the environmentally friendly treatment of wastes, and adopts the &ldquo;polluter pays&rdquo; principle. It codifies the rights and duties of manufacturers (producers), traders and consumers, identifies who is responsible for the treatment, collection, transport, recycling and treatment of wastes and the basic principles of all these activities.', '2000', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Quantity of wastes, number of projects, budgets used for financing.', 'The quantitative impacts on the GHG emissions are incorporated in the national projections of greenhouse gas emissions and removal.', 'HU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.52ff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(759, 'HU-CRS-01', NULL, '46', 'Act on general rules of the protection of the Environment', 'General principles of environmental protection', 'Act LIII of 1995 codifies the general principles of environmental protection and creates the legal basis for all the subsequent regulations that are related to the environment.', '1995', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'HU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.6', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
