(760, 'HU-CRS-02', NULL, '47', 'New Hungary Development Plan', 'Utilisation of the EU Structural Funds', 'In the framework of the NHDP some 7000 billion HUF may be spent on Hungary&rsquo;s development between 2007&ndash;2013.<br />The specific goals of the NHDP are to be achieved through operative programmes. Many of the Operative Programmes include elements that affect and assist GHG emission mitigation activities:<br />&bull; The intervention of priority axis 2. of the GOP on the &bdquo;Technological modernisation of the enterprises&rdquo; - in order to support sustainable development as horizontal principle &ndash; encourages the spread of such environment-friendly, low-waste, energy and material saving production technologies, that apart from the primary objective of competitiveness improvement can also contribute to lowering pressure on the environment. Among GOP&rsquo;s horizontal objectives the development of the harmonic, sustainable development of the environment, society and economy is of primary importance.<br />&bull; Improving urban and agglomeration public transport is among K&Ouml;ZOP&rsquo;s priority axes. Substantial developments will be carried out in Budapest, major provincial towns and their agglomerations in order to improve the accessibility and traversability of the cities, to alleviate the crowdedness of urban transport and to reduce transport safety risks. The developments may encourage the use of public transport, which will in turn also reduce urban environment impacts (air and noise pollution). The objective is to establish a public transport, which offers a real alternative to individual transport and is economically and environmentally sustainable.<br />&bull; Social Renewal OP contributes to the attainment of the comprehensive aims of the NHDP such as growth and the expansion of employment primarily through measures intended to affect the supply side of the labour market, the development and improvement of human resources. As declared in the basic document of the programme itself, T&Aacute;MOP can promote sustainability by creating the chances for a change in the approach. The training and projects implemented in the framework of T&Aacute;MOP must contribute to learning that is conducive to sustainable development.<br />&bull; The intentions of the Environment and Energy Operational Programme&rsquo;s developments are to reduce the environmental problems of our country, improving the quality of life of society, and to assist our economy to adapt to environmental practices. The following priority axes of KEOP are directly or indirectly related to GHG emission mitigation:<br />o Increase of the usage of renewable energy sources.  A key role of the New Hungarian Development Plan is to influence the energy source structure: to assist the move from traditional energy source towards renewable energy source usage. The effect of increased proportion of renewable energy usage has a big significance from the point of view of the structural changes in agriculture and forestry which leads to increased competitiveness as well.<br />o Efficient energy usage. Besides modifying the structure of energy sources, the important task is to create a system which could assist to save energy and increase energy efficient usage, both in the consumption and the production sectors. To fulfil the obligations of the 2006/32/EC directive, KEOP has to assist in the field of energy savings. To reach 1% of energy savings, the KEOP operations have to be completed with arrangements of other OPs and national programmes.<br />o Promotion of sustainable production and consumption patterns. Giving priority to environmental considerations (with the idea of saving materials, the prevention of waste creation and improvement of secondary raw material usage; energy saving; prevention of further damage to the human environment and nature conservation assets) can lead to increases in economic efficiency in several areas.', '2007', '2013', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'HU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.7f', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(761, 'HU-CRS-03', NULL, '48', 'New Hungary Rural Development Strategic Plan', 'Utilisation of support provided by the European Agricultural Orientation and Guarantee Fund', 'In conformity with 1698/2005/EC and 2006/144/EC a new development plan was worked out for 2007-2013. The so called New Hungary Rural Development Strategic Plan (NHRSP) for the first time in strategic documents establishes the fact of climate change and sets targets to mitigate this process. The NHRSP is in many aspects related to GHG mitigation, but two objectives are specially important to mention:<br />&bull; As a general objective mitigation of climate change explicitly appears in the programme. The tools for addressing the problem are the increase of energy plantations and energy forests.<br />&bull; Besides the sustainable management of forests the increase of forestation is among the important specific objectives.', '2007', '2013', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'HU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.9', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(762, 'HU-CRS-04', NULL, '49', 'The National Climate Change Strategy', 'General framework for mitigation and adaptation policies', 'Hungary&rsquo;s National Climate Change Strategy (N&Eacute;S) is under preparation. It is planned to be submitted to the Parliament in the second half of 2007. The work is coordinated by the Ministry of Environment and Water. As this regularly updated document will create the general framework for mitigation and adaptation policies, it is important to mention already in this report. According to the drafts available, the N&Eacute;S will set quantitative targets and identify tools with which targets can be reached.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'HU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.10', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(763, 'HU-CRS-05', NULL, '50', 'National Energy Strategy', 'National Energy Strategy', 'The currently valid energy strategy documents will soon be replaced - most probably in the second half of 2007 - by a new national energy strategy document, currently under preparation by the Ministry of Economy and Transport.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'HU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.10', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(764, 'HU-CRS-06', NULL, '51', '2nd National Environmental Protection Programme', 'Environmental Protection', 'The key elements of NEP-II are<br />&bull; The protection of the ecosystem <br />&bull; Provision of a harmonic relationship between society and environment<br />&bull; Enforcement of environmental criteria in economic development. <br />&bull; Strengthening knowledge on, and awareness of environmental processes, impacts, environment and nature conservation and co-operation <br />The relevant foreseen actions are referred to in the current document.', '2003', '2008', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'HU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.11', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(765, 'HU-CRS-07', NULL, '52', 'Emission Trading System', 'Reduce the risk of climate change', 'In compliance with the relevant Community acts (2003/87/EC; 2004/156/EC) the Hungarian Parliament approved the Act XV of 2005 on the trading system of greenhouse gas emission units. This created the official framework for the allocation, trade, utilisation of GHG emission units and also codified those activities that are subject to emission licences.<br />Further pieces of lower level legislation (Governmental Decrees 272/2004. (IX. 29.) Korm. and 143/2005. (VII. 27.) Korm) regulate the details of the EU ETS system.<br />The system operative for the first trading period (2005-2007) on the basis of approved National Allocation Plan and the detailed Allocation List. <br />The Allocation plan for the second period (2008-12) was finalised subsequent to intensive public discussion and submitted to the Commission for approval. The Comission, however in April, 2007 ruled that the overall allocated emission will have to be reduced by 10.8%.<br />The ultimate objective of the entire trading system is to reduce the risk of climate change. This is to be achieved by creating incentives for GHG emission-conscious behaviour; in order that the biggest polluters implement emission reduction measures.', '2005', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'The indirect impacts of the ETS on GHG emission reduction are not yet possible to measure or forecast. It is commonly agreed, however, that the first and most important impact of the ETS was that it considerably increased the awareness of the large companies &ndash; this has been strongly confirmed by their feedback during and since the preparation of the legislation, and the interest in taking part in the actual transactions, and the auctions e.g. in December 2006, and March 2007. <br />The companies rather soon realised the fact that they can generate extra revenues by reducing their GHG emissions. At the same time the limited availability of &ldquo;free&rdquo; emission rights for new entrants puts a constraint of energy use reduction on new developments.<br />However, quantitative forecasts will only be possible when the experience of the first trading period is already available.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Quantity of traded emission rights', 'Mitigation effect not directly quantifiable, but included in the overall emission forecasts', 'HU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.20f, 37', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(766, 'HU-CRS-08', NULL, '53', 'R&amp;D for energy efficiency and renewables', 'Improved R&amp;D with emphasis on energy efficiency and renewable energy', 'The Act XC of 2003 created the Research and Technology Innovation Fund. The Fund is managed by the National Office for Research and Technology (NKTH). Apart from the micro- and small enterprises, every firm is obliged to pay at least 0.25% of its turnover into the Fund. The Hungarian government contributes to the Fund with an equivalent amount. <br />Many of the NKTH supported programmes are either directly aimed at energy efficiency or renewables, or contains such components, thus indirectly contribute to GHG emission reduction.', '2003', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'No separate data of the subsidies for the GHG mitigation related programmes are available. It is not possible to identify the quantitative effects of R&amp;D on GHG mitigation. It is obvious that much of the results appear in the development of renewable energy generation (e.g. the availability of Hungarian-developed energy crops, energy grass) the bioethanol programme and in other areas but these effects are indirect and are incorporated in the forecasts that are relevant for those sectors.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Supported project budgets, number of projects', 'Mitigation effect included in the forecasts for related measures', 'HU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.27f, 38', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(767, 'IE-ENS-01', NULL, '1', 'Renewable Energy Feed-In Tariff', 'Increase supply of final electricity consumption from renewable sources', 'The Renewable Energy Feed-In Tariff (REFIT) replaces the previous renewable electricity support structure, the Alternative Energy Requirement. The RES-E Directive requires Ireland to ensure that 13.2% of gross electricity consumption comes from renewable sources by 2010. Renewable energy consumption accounted for 6.8% of gross electricity consumption in 2005. (Source SEI, Energy in Ireland 1990-2005.)', '2006', NULL, NULL, NULL, '1470', NULL, NULL, NULL, '3260', NULL, NULL, 'Reduction assumes full compliance with RES-E Directive. Calculation by ICF Integrated Power Model (IPM) based on displacement of fossil fuel power generation in 2008-2012 period.', NULL, 'Yes', 'National Climate Change Strategy 2007-2012 http://www.environ.ie/en/PublicationsDocuments/FileDownLoad,1861,en.pdf', 'Percentage of gross national electricity consumption from renewable sources', NULL, 'IE Submission 07', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(768, 'IE-ENS-02', NULL, '2', 'Natural Gas Transmission and Distribution', 'Modernisation of existing natural gas network which will reduce fugitive emissions of natural gas', 'A major upgrade programme of the national natural gas network, which will replace all remaining cast-iron piping, is due to be completed by 2009', NULL, '2009', NULL, NULL, '60', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Difference between projected emissions in 2008-12 due to methane losses and the equivalent 1990 figure', NULL, NULL, 'National Climate Change Strategy 2007-2012 http://www.environ.ie/en/PublicationsDocuments/FileDownLoad,1861,en.pdf', 'Amount of cast-iron piping, in km, replaced and remaining', NULL, 'IE Submission 07', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(769, 'IE-ENS-03', NULL, '3', 'Electricity Infrastructure Development Programme', 'Investment in strategic energy infrastructure for national security of supply to bring strategic energy infrastructure up to date and foster continued economic and regional development', 'Investment of approximately &euro;7 billion is envisaged for electricity and gas networks under Ireland&#39;s National Development Plan 2007-2013', '2007', '2013', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Replacement of electricity transmission / distribution and gas transmission / distribution in km', NULL, 'IE Submission 07', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(770, 'IE-ENS-04', NULL, '4', 'Electricity Demand Side Management Programmes', 'Promotion by electricity supplier (ESB Customer Supply) of reduction in electricity consumption', 'This consists of a number of schemes to reduce electricity consumption by business, industrial and residential customers. It is estimated that between 1991 and 2005 cumulative savings of 6,300 GwH have been achieved.', '1991', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Electricity savings in GwH', NULL, 'IE Submission 07', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(771, 'IE-CRS-01', NULL, '5', 'EU Emissions Trading Scheme', 'Cap-and-trade scheme for large point-source emitters of carbon dioxide', 'In operation from 2005 on a three year pilot phase, currently 110 installations participating in Ireland', '2005', NULL, NULL, NULL, '3020', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Based on apportionment of total projected national emissions  between ETS and non-ETS sectors, as recommended in ICF-BOC Report, &#39;Determining the share of national greenhouse gas emissions for emissions trading in Ireland 2008-2012,&#39; March 2006', NULL, 'Yes', 'National Climate Change Strategy 2007-2012 http://www.environ.ie/en/PublicationsDocuments/FileDownLoad,1861,en.pdf', 'Verified emissions from ETS participants', NULL, 'IE Submission 07', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(772, 'IE-TRA-01', NULL, '6', 'Vehicle Efficiency', 'This measure is attributable to the voluntary agreement between the EU and car manufacturers to reduce specific CO2 emissions', 'As Ireland is a technology taker in this regard, it has little ability to influence the devloment of cleaner technology. Emissions savings attributable to this measure are based on achievement of EU objective of limiting average emissions from private cars to no more than 120g/km', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '480', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'See ICF-BOC report 2006 section 3.8', NULL, 'Yes', 'National Climate Change Strategy 2007-2012 http://www.environ.ie/en/PublicationsDocuments/FileDownLoad,1861,en.pdf', 'Average g/km of vehicle fleet', NULL, 'IE Submission 07', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(773, 'IE-TRA-02', NULL, '7', 'Mineral Oil Tax Relief for Biofuels', 'This measure aims to achieve a 2% penetration of biofuels by 2008', 'The scheme was launched on a pilot phase in 2005. 16 Biofuels projects have been granted excise relief under the 2006 Mineral Oil Tax Relief Scheme. The scheme will cost in excess of &euro;200 million over 5 years', '2005', '2010', NULL, NULL, '270', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Replacement of 2% of transport liquid fuels market by 2008 with biofuels. Assumes 2% reduction in projected emissions', NULL, 'Yes', 'National Climate Change Strategy 2007-2012 http://www.environ.ie/en/PublicationsDocuments/FileDownLoad,1861,en.pdf', 'Amount of biofuel, in litres, placed on market', NULL, 'IE Submission 07', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(774, 'IE-TRA-03', NULL, '8', 'Dublin Transport Infrastructure', 'This refers to a range of investments under the National Development Plan 2000-2006 for the Greater Dublin Area transportation system', 'Completion of orbital motorway, Dublin Port Tunnel, two light rail lines and significantly expanded bus and cycle network', '2000', '2006', NULL, NULL, '270', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'See ICF-BOC report 2006 section 3.8', NULL, NULL, 'National Climate Change Strategy 2007-2012 http://www.environ.ie/en/PublicationsDocuments/FileDownLoad,1861,en.pdf', 'Completion of planned infrastructural projects', NULL, 'IE Submission 07', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(775, 'IE-TRA-04', NULL, '9', 'National Car Test', 'To improve road safety and environmental protection and to comply with the EU Directive 96/96/EC, which makes car testing compulsory in all EU member states', 'The National Car Test was introduced in Ireland in 2000 and is conducted every two years on vehicles to ensure, inter alia, that vehicles are maintained and operated as fuel efficiently as possible. Number of cars undergoing a full text in 2005 was 625,000', '2000', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Numbers of vehicles tested per annum', NULL, 'IE Submission 07', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(776, 'IE-TRA-05', NULL, '10', 'Changes to Motor Tax and Vehicle Registration Tax', 'More closely align registration and circulation taxes with the C02 emissions from private motor vehicles', 'This measure aims to provide a further incentive for consumers to purchase lower emission vehicles and will be supported by an enhancement of the existing mandatory labelling system to provide more information on C02 emission levels and on fuel economy. The Government is also considering the extension beyond 20007 of existing preferential VRT treatment for hybrid-electric, flexible fuel and electric vehicles.', '2008', NULL, NULL, NULL, '50', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'See ICF-BOC report 2006 section 3.8', NULL, 'Yes', 'National Climate Change Strategy 2007-2012 http://www.environ.ie/en/PublicationsDocuments/FileDownLoad,1861,en.pdf', 'Average g/km of vehicle fleet', NULL, 'IE Submission 07', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(777, 'IE-TRA-06', NULL, '11', 'Modal Shift', 'Investment in and promotion of use of public transport', 'Building on significant investment under the National Development Plan 2000-2006, a &euro;34 billion capital investment framework for the transport system has been put in place through Transport 21. This will operate between 2006 and 2015.', '2000', NULL, NULL, NULL, '510', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Savings based on projections of changed modal share in 2010 as a result of Transport 21 investment without demand management. Base year for modal share comparison is 2002.', NULL, NULL, 'National Climate Change Strategy 2007-2012 http://www.environ.ie/en/PublicationsDocuments/FileDownLoad,1861,en.pdf', 'Numbers of passengers using public transport and overall modal share', NULL, 'IE Submission 07', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(778, 'IE-TRA-07', NULL, '12', 'Alignment of transport investment with spatial planning', 'To facilitate a closer link between land-use planning and transport investment', 'Capital investment in transport infrastructure will complement that National Spatial Strategy 2002-2020 and Regional Planning Guidelines by better integrating land-us planning and spatial development and concentrating development in close proximity to transport infrastructure', '2002', NULL, NULL, NULL, '83', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Based on projections of 2% reduction in passenger-kilometres in 2010 from 2002 figures as a result of appropriate spatial planning and the integration of land use and transport infrastructure.', NULL, NULL, 'National Climate Change Strategy 2007-2012 http://www.environ.ie/en/PublicationsDocuments/FileDownLoad,1861,en.pdf', 'Passenger/km, numbers of passengers using public transport and overall modal share', NULL, 'IE Submission 07', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(779, 'IE-TRA-08', NULL, '13', 'Biofuels Obligation Scheme', 'To oblige fuel distributors to achieve an average of 5.75% biofuels of their total annual fuel business by 2009', 'Measure will enable Ireland to achieve the Biofuels Directive Target of 5.75% by 2010 and provide a basis for achieving 10% penetration by 2020', '2009', NULL, NULL, NULL, '500', NULL, NULL, NULL, '878', NULL, NULL, 'Replacement of 5.75% of transport liquid fuels market by 2010 with biofuels. Assumes 5.75% reduction in projected emissions', NULL, 'Yes', 'National Climate Change Strategy 2007-2012 http://www.environ.ie/en/PublicationsDocuments/FileDownLoad,1861,en.pdf', 'Amount of biofuel, in litres, placed on market', NULL, 'IE Submission 07', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(780, 'IE-TRA-09', NULL, '14', 'Efficient Driving Awareness Campaign', 'To raise public awareness of potential for reducing fuel consumption and emissions through driver behaviour', 'This campaign will be developed as part of a broader Sustainable Transport Action Plan, to be published by Government by end 2007', '2008', '2012', NULL, NULL, '130', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Assumes 50% of drivers adopt efficient driving behaviour, delivering a 20% improvement in fuel efficiency', NULL, NULL, 'National Climate Change Strategy 2007-2012 http://www.environ.ie/en/PublicationsDocuments/FileDownLoad,1861,en.pdf', 'Average fuel consumption per km (corrected for average rated fuel consumption for vehicle fleet)', NULL, 'IE Submission 07', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(781, 'IE-ENC-01', NULL, '15', 'Building Regulations 2002 and 2005', 'Sets thermal performance standards for new domestic (2002) and commercial (2005) buildings', 'Higher thermal performance standards for new dwellings took effect from 1 January 2003, including higher thermal performance standards for replacement doors, windows and roof lights. These higher standards are estimated to reduce energy requirements for domestic space and water heating by 23% - 33% depending on size and type of dwelling. 2005 Amendments to Part L of the Building Regulations for non-domestic buildings took effect from 1 July 2006', '2003', NULL, NULL, NULL, '405', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Based on estimates of emissions savings per dwelling with C02 savings based on Ireland-specific average energy consumption per dwelling for space/water heating and oil/gas split, multiplied by expected number of unit completions to 2012', NULL, NULL, 'National Climate Change Strategy 2007-2012 http://www.environ.ie/en/PublicationsDocuments/FileDownLoad,1861,en.pdf', 'Domestic dwelling / commercial building completions to specified standard', NULL, 'IE Submission 07', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(782, 'IE-ENC-02', NULL, '16', 'Residential Density Guidelines', 'To encourage energy efficient housing layouts', 'Existing 1999 Guidelines on Residential Density will be replaced in 2007 with Guidelines on Sustainable Residential Development. New Guidelines will  set more quantifiable sustainable development standards, maximise access to sunlight and daylight, facilitate greater movement by pedestrians and cyclists and use of public transport.', '1999', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'IE Submission 07', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(783, 'IE-ENC-03', NULL, '17', 'Building Energy Ratings', 'Certificate of energy demand and C02 performance of buildings', 'This measure implements a key requirement of the Energy Performance in Buildings Directive in Ireland. BER requirement is being introduced on a phased basis from 1 January 2007 for new dwellings; from 1 July 2008 for new non-domestic dwellings and for existing buildings from 1 January 2009', '2007', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', NULL, 'Number of BERs issued', NULL, 'IE Submission 07', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(784, 'IE-ENC-04', NULL, '18', 'Greener Homes Scheme', 'Grant assistance to householders for installation of renewable heat technologies', 'The Scheme will provide &euro;47 million for grant assistance to homeowners for renewable energy heating system. The scheme applies to both new and existing dwellings and will assist in excess of 10,000 dwellings.', '2006', '2010', NULL, NULL, '37', NULL, NULL, NULL, '52', NULL, NULL, 'Based on expected number of system installations with available grant aid', NULL, NULL, 'National Climate Change Strategy 2007-2012 http://www.environ.ie/en/PublicationsDocuments/FileDownLoad,1861,en.pdf', 'Uptake on available grant-aid', NULL, 'IE Submission 07', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(785, 'IE-ENC-05', NULL, '19', 'Planning Exemptions for micro-renewables', 'To exempt from planning permission certain technologies to encourage the update of cleaner energy sources in domestic dwellings.', 'The objectives of the Greener Homes Scheme are supported through exemptions from planning permission for the installation of certain micro-renewable technologies. Consideration being given to extending exemptions for commercial use.', '2007', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'IE Submission 07', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(786, 'IE-ENC-06', NULL, '20', 'Building Regulations 2008', 'Sets higher thermal performance standards for new domestic dwellings', 'Revision of existing requirements to aim to achieve up to 40% improvement on current standards', '2008', NULL, NULL, NULL, '120', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Based on estimates of additional emissions savings per dwelling with higher thermal performance requirements.', NULL, NULL, 'National Climate Change Strategy 2007-2012 http://www.environ.ie/en/PublicationsDocuments/FileDownLoad,1861,en.pdf', 'Domestic dwelling completions to specified standard', NULL, 'IE Submission 07', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(787, 'IE-ENC-07', NULL, '21', 'Smart Metering', 'To deliver enhanced demand-side management opportunities for the residential and commercial sectors', 'Following a pilot project of 200 houses and a technical and economic review underway by CER, ESB Networks and SEI, a decision will be taken by end-2007 on the roll-out and funding of a national five-year programme to install smart meters for all householders in new and existing housing stock', '2008', '2012', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Number of meters installed', NULL, 'IE Submission 07', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(788, 'IE-ENC-08', NULL, '22', 'Power Of One', 'National Energy Efficiency Awareness Campaign to achieve behavioural changes and energy savings across all economic sectors', '4-year campaign on energy efficiency across all sectors, including an all-island dimension from 2007', '2006', '2009', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'IE Submission 07', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(789, 'IE-ENC-09', NULL, '23', 'Levy on Incandescent light bulbs', 'To encourage increased usage of low-energy light bulbs', 'Government will introduce an environmental levy to reduce the price advantage of incandescent lightbulbs vis-&agrave;-vis low-energy alternatives. Income generated from the levy will support climate change awareness initiatives', '2008', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Sales of energy-efficient alternatives', NULL, 'IE Submission 07', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(790, 'IE-ENC-10', NULL, '24', 'Large Industry Energy Network', 'To assist member companies achieve energy savings through energy auditing, report and sharing of best-practice information', 'A voluntary networking initiative of eighty-five of the largest industrial energy users, focuses on improving competitiveness by reducing energy costs through a structured approach to energy auditing and management, and an annual statement of energy accounts. Participants report energy performance, progress and target realisation. Information and experience, to achieve best practice, are shared through fora including workshops, members&rsquo; internet sites, networking, courses, and case studies.', '1995', NULL, NULL, NULL, '145', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Energy efficiency activity among member firms between 2000 and 2010 results in total abatement of 5% against a without-measure scenario. Approximately 25% of savings arise in ETS sectors and is therefore discounted from abatement figure', NULL, NULL, 'National Climate Change Strategy 2007-2012 http://www.environ.ie/en/PublicationsDocuments/FileDownLoad,1861,en.pdf', 'Energy saving per participant', NULL, 'IE Submission 07', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(791, 'IE-ENC-11', NULL, '25', 'Energy Agreements Programme', 'Provides support for participant companies to work towards certification with Irish Standard on Energy Management (IS 393)', 'IS 393 requires that energy use is managed by companies through formalised structures to achieve significant savings in energy use and greenhouse gas emissions. The Standard covers all aspects of a company&rsquo;s approach to managing its energy costs and use. It is designed for large energy intensive enterprises, which may be more exposed than others to changes in energy costs', '2006', NULL, NULL, NULL, '37', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Assumes efficiency gains of 1.5% in year 1 of participation, growing to 4.5% end of year 3, growing 0.5% p.a. after that (additional to autonomous changes). Assumes participation of 60 as per recruitment in 2006 and 2007, giving a total programme-related CO2 abatement of approx 150 kt p.a. at end 2010. 75% of savings covered in ETS sector and therefore discounted from abatement figure.', NULL, NULL, 'National Climate Change Strategy 2007-2012 http://www.environ.ie/en/PublicationsDocuments/FileDownLoad,1861,en.pdf', 'Energy saving per participant', NULL, 'IE Submission 07', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(792, 'IE-ENC-12', NULL, '26', 'Commercial Bioheat Scheme', 'Grant assistance for commercial deployment of renewable heat technologies', 'Scheme will support conversion to renewable heat energy in up to 600 installations over 5 years, aiming to replace 150-175Mw of heating capacity', '2006', '2010', NULL, NULL, '160', NULL, NULL, NULL, '224', NULL, NULL, 'Assumes specific numbers of different technologies involved and specific CO2 abetment from such technologies', NULL, NULL, 'National Climate Change Strategy 2007-2012 http://www.environ.ie/en/PublicationsDocuments/FileDownLoad,1861,en.pdf', 'Uptake on available grant-aid', NULL, 'IE Submission 07', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(793, 'IE-ENC-13', NULL, '27', 'CHP Deployment Programme', 'Grant assistance for installation of CHP units', 'Support for deployment of units up to 1 Mw with target deployment of 400 Mw by 2010', '2006', '2010', NULL, NULL, '162', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Assumes specific numbers of small-scale fossil CHP, as well as Biomass and AD CHP with normal emissions abatement factors for these technologies', NULL, 'Yes', 'National Climate Change Strategy 2007-2012 http://www.environ.ie/en/PublicationsDocuments/FileDownLoad,1861,en.pdf', 'Uptake on available grant-aid', NULL, 'IE Submission 07', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
