(813, 'IT-ENS-16', NULL, '11', 'PV systems (Decree 19 February 2007)', 'Support the expansion of photovoltaic plants through feed-in tariffs until a maximum capacity of 1200 MW is reached', 'The huge number of applications received and the potential for success of this policy paved the way for the revision and improvement of Decree 28 July 2005. In February 2007 a new decree was passed that brought in several changes to the existing system. The previous decrees will still apply only to those plants which have already been granted the right to the incentive tariffs by the end of 2006. The decree 19 February 2007 applies to all the applications received after that date. The new scheme applies to all PV plants connected to the grid with a nominal capacity higher than 1 kWp. The tariffs are still guaranteed for 20 years but they have been slightly changed to further incentive installations integrated in buildings. <br />A 5% increase is granted to PV systems: installed in public schools and public health centres/ used as a replacement for asbestos roofs/ installed in public buildings owned by municipalities with less than 5000 inhabitants. The tariffs can be further incremented in case of adoption of energy efficiency interventions, envisaged in the energy certificate of the building, that lead to a decrease in the energy performance index of at least 10%.<br />The new decree raised the national indicative target for PV installed capacity by 2016 to 3,000 MW. The new supporting mechanism will operate until an installed capacity of 1,200 MW is reached. Plants built within 14 months after the total capacity is reached will nonetheless continue to receive the incentive.', '2007', NULL, NULL, NULL, '190', NULL, '530', NULL, '640', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'IT-4th National Communication, p.89f, 111', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(814, 'IT-ENS-17', NULL, '12', 'PV systems (Budget Law 2007)', 'Supporting the installation of photovoltaic systems in new buildings', 'Another important provision to further support the installation of photovoltaic systems in new buildings was introduced by the Budget Law 200714. Art. 350 of the new law introduces the obligation for municipal Building Regulations to allow the issuing of construction permits for new buildings only if the submitted plan provides for the installation of a PV system granting the production of at least 0.2 kW for each household.', '2007', NULL, NULL, NULL, '190', NULL, '530', NULL, '640', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'IT-4th National Communication, p.90, 111', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(815, 'IT-ENS-18', NULL, '13', 'Simplification of authorisation procedures (Law 55 of 9 April 2002)', 'Simplify the authorisation procedure for the construction and operation of power plants with a capacity of over 300 MW', 'Law 55 of 9 April 2002 was introduced to simplify the authorisation procedure for the construction and operation of power plants with a capacity of over 300 MW. From 2002 to the end of 2006 the Ministry of Economic Development issued 45 authorisations for 21,400 MWe of new capacity; among these 23 authorisations, for an overall capacity of 9,897 MW, were issued according to the new procedure brought in by law 55/02.', '2002', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'IT-4th National Communication, p.93, 111', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(816, 'IT-ENS-19', 'CL-IT-ENS-02', '14', 'White Certificates for CHP (Legislative decree 20/07)', 'Supporting energy saving through CHP', 'Legislative decree 20/2007, introduced to transpose directive 2004/8/CE into the national legal system, provides for a set of comprehensive measures designed to promote high-efficiency cogeneration based on a useful heat demand through the White Certificates system. High efficiency cogeneration is defined as the simultaneous generation of thermal energy and electrical and/or mechanical energy that exceed the limit values specified in AEEG16 Decision 42/02 (after 2010 these limits will be replaced by those provided for by Annex III of the same law). The new law confirms some previously adopted measures and introduces new ones.<br />The main benefits currently granted to co-generation are: dispatch priority; exemption from the obligation to purchase Green Certificates; incentive prices for the electricity produced by co-generation plants having a capacity of less than 10 MVA; right to obtain White Certificates for all cogeneration plants (the implementing measures of legislative decree 20/07, still at the drafting stage, will modify the current scheme to ensure stronger support); right to obtain Green certificates for those cogeneration plants using geothermal energy or firing/cofiring biomass;<br />net metering for the electricity produced in high-efficiency cogeneration plants with a nominal capacity not over 200kW; simplified authorisation procedure (plants with a thermal capacity of over 300 MW are  subject to the authorization procedure provided for by law 55/02, while new simplified procedures have to be adopted for smaller plants); obligation for new buildings and buildings subject to major renovation to lay down all the necessary works to allow the connection to district heating systems, when existing (and not further than 1 km) or planned.', '2010', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CL-IT-ENS-02', NULL, 'CL-IT-ENS-02', NULL, 'CL-IT-ENS-02', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'IT-4th National Communication, p.91f, 112', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(817, 'IT-ENS-20', 'CL-IT-ENS-02', '15', 'White Certificates for CHP', 'Supporting energy saving through CHP', 'Further supporting CHP through the White Certificates System', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CL-IT-ENS-02', NULL, 'CL-IT-ENS-02', NULL, 'CL-IT-ENS-02', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'IT-4th National Communication, p.92, 112', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(818, 'IT-ENS-21', NULL, '16', 'Simplification of authorisation procedures (Law 239 of 23 August 2004)', 'Further speeding up the authorisation process for the construction of new power plants and infrastructures', 'Law 239 of 23 August 2004 introduced some important changes in the energy sector. One of its main purposes was to speed up the authorisation process for the construction of new power plants and energy infrastructures, particularly grid lines. Since the entry into force of law 239/04, new energy infrastructures for approximately 2,300 MW have been developed and new CCGT plants for about 3,200 MW have been constructed, which led to consistent emissions reductions.', '2004', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'IT-4th National Communication, p.93,111', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(819, 'IT-ENS-24', NULL, '17', 'Cement production', 'Substitution of fossil fuels with waste derived fuels', 'Reducing CO2 emissions through the substitution of fossil fuels with waste derived fuels in cement production, e.g. by simplifying the relevant authorization processes. The use of non conventional fuels in the industrial sector in Italy is among the lowest in Europe, since the implementation of such projects is often delayed by administrative problems at local level.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '400', NULL, '800', NULL, '1200', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'IT-4th National Communication, p.97,112', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(820, 'CL-IT-ENS-02', 'CL-IT-ENS-02', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1650', NULL, '5440', NULL, '9330', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(821, 'IT-ENS-25', NULL, '18', 'Rotation Fund (Art. 1110 - 1115 of Budget Law 2007)', 'Efficient energy supply', 'The Fund will finance a number of priority actions, among which: the promotion of high performance distributed microcogeneration plants for electricity and heat generation, small size RES plants (heat and electricity), replacement of industrial electric engines with a power of over 45 kW with highly efficient engines, end use energy efficiency in the domestic and tertiary sector; industrial processes nitrous oxide emissions reduction and pilot projects for the research and development of new low emissions or zero emissions energy sources and technologies.', '2007', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'IT-4th National Communication, p.87', NULL, NULL, '200000000', NULL, 'IT-4th Nat. Comm., p.87', NULL),
(822, 'IT-IND-08', NULL, '19', 'Reduction of N2O emissions from the production of nitric acid', 'Reduction of emission from nitric acid production', 'In the production of nitric acid, the most advanced technology calls for installation of SCR (selective catalytic reduction) systems for the treatment of process gases with the adoption of the BAT-TALuft standard equal to (2.5 kgN2O/tHNO3). The measure could be applied to the main production plant in Italy.', '2006', NULL, NULL, NULL, '1400', NULL, '1480', NULL, '1570', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'IT-4th National Communication, p.103, 112', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(823, 'IT-IND-09', NULL, '20', 'Aluminium production', 'Increase of recycling rate in aluminium production', 'Reducing greenhouse gas emissions from the aluminium industry through a strong increase of its recycling rate', '2008', NULL, NULL, NULL, '600', NULL, '700', NULL, '800', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'IT-4th National Communication, p.97,112', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(824, 'IT-TRA-13', NULL, '21', 'Fleet update', 'Subsidy to change older cars with new ones with average emissions of 140 g CO2/km', 'The measure is starting from 1 January 2007, the actual circulating fleet will continue to be renewed at the same path of the more recent years (higher than the average of the last 10 years). The share of diesel and petrol car will be constant at 50-50 with a slight reversal of more recent trends. It is also hypothesized an increase of sales of new vehicles using LPG / natural gas, that contribute to the target emission value.<br />Actual (2004) average emissions are about 150 g CO2/km.', '2009', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2960', NULL, '4380', NULL, '4400', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'IT-4th National Communication, p.102, 112', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(825, 'IT-TRA-14', NULL, '22', 'Biofuels', 'Promoting the use of biofuels', 'The estimate of the impact of this measure at 2010 is of 2.39 Mt CO2 per year. In Italy there is the industrial structure to produce this amount of fuel, with raw material produced in Italy or imported. The impact is lower than the total potential of the measure because the trend scenario for 2010 already includes a small quantity of biodiesel. The impact of this measures at 2020 is assessed taking into account a share of biofuels of about 10% to replace diesel or petrol for transport purposes.', '2005', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2390', NULL, '2410', NULL, '2170', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'IT-4th National Communication, p.103, 111', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(826, 'IT-TRA-15', NULL, '23', 'Measures for new infrastructures in public transport', 'Reducing private car use and traffic congestion', 'It has been proposed to invest additional 20 billions of euro with the result of increasing the total p-km transported by public transport by 23%, 38 billion p-km in total, and reducing CO2 emissions of 4.5 Mt. The breakdown of this figure in different types of transport is : 5 billion p-km in tram, other 5 billion in underground lines, and 20 billion in trains (both commuter and intercity) and 8 billion in buses.<br />All additional cost are included for tram, metro and buses, while only the additional costs for equipment is included for trains as the investment in infrastructure is supposed to be done anyway for other objectives. Such an investment would promote a impressive change in the respective modes of collective transport, with reference to actual figures (2005) the passenger in tram and metro will be doubled, total passengers using trains will increase by 50% and passenger in buses for public transport will increase by about 20%.<br />The time frame of such a group of measure is of medium &ndash; long period, due to the long construction time of infrastructure. The total impact of those measures can be considered only in year 2020, with about 1/3 in 2015.', '2010', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1350', NULL, '4500', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'IT-4th National Communication, p.102f, 112', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(827, 'IT-TRA-16', NULL, '24', 'Biofuels', 'Promoting the use of biofuels', 'The impact of this measures at 2020 is assessed taking into account a share of biofuels of about 10% to replace diesel or petrol for transport purposes.', '2012', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '6030', NULL, '8690', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'IT-4th National Communication, p.103, 112', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(828, 'IT-TRA-17', NULL, '25', 'Fleet update', 'Subsidy to change older cars with new ones with average emissions of 120 g CO2/km', 'The case of a new fleet at a much lower emission rate, 120 gCO2/km, from 2010, with additional reductions has been envisaged too.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2700', NULL, '4700', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'IT-4th National Communication, p.102, 112', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(829, 'IT-TRA-18', NULL, '26', 'Sustainable Mobility Fund (Art. 1122 of Budget law 2007)', 'Sustainable Mobility', 'The Fund will finance primarily: the strengthening of public transport, with particular reference to low emissions transport means; the promotion of intermodality; the introduction of an incentive system to promote sustainable mobility; the promotion of mobility management and car sharing; the promotion of safe travel plans in every school; the improvement of the efficiency of goods transport and delivery; the setting up and/or improvement of methane, hydrogen, electricity and Lpg distribution networks; the promotion of urban cycling paths.', '2007', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'IT-4th National Communication, p.87', NULL, NULL, '90000000', NULL, 'IT-4th Nat. Comm., p.87', NULL),
(830, 'IT-ENC-03', NULL, '27', 'Building Regulation (Decree 27 July 2005)', 'Energy saving in new and existing buildings', 'Decree 27 July 2005 implemented the provisions of article 4 of law n. 10 of 9 January 1991. It requested stricter standards for the construction and the renovation of buildings and promoted the<br />implementation of the decrees on energy efficiency.', '2006', NULL, NULL, NULL, '660', NULL, '1590', NULL, '2860', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'IT-4th National Communication, p.99, 111', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(831, 'IT-ENC-04', 'CL-IT-ENC-03', '28', 'End use efficiency and energy services in the Civil sector', 'Increase energy efficiency in final energy uses', 'Achieving an overall energy savings target of 9% within 2017 through the implementation of directive 2006/32/CE', '2008', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CL-IT-ENC-03', NULL, 'CL-IT-ENC-03', NULL, 'CL-IT-ENC-03', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'IT-4th National Communication, p.100,112', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(832, 'IT-ENC-05', NULL, '29', 'Building Regulation (Legislative decree 192/05 as amended by legislative decree 311/06)', 'Energy saving in new and existing buildings', 'Legislative decree 192/2005 implemented the directive into national law but it required the adoption of further ministerial decrees to become fully operational. Measures introduced included: methodology for calculating the energy performance of buildings; application of performance standards on new and existing buildings; certification schemes for all buildings; regular inspection and assessment of boilers/heating and cooling installations.<br />At the end of 2006, legislative decree 192/2005 was amended by legislative decree 311/2006 to strengthen the buildings thermal demand requirements. The new law applies to new buildings and to existing buildings subject to major renovation17 and provides for some important measures. Amongst the main provisions, the following obligations are worth citing:<br />- Installation of technical blinds for solar protection and insulation of new buildings and buildings subject to overall renovation (limited to buildings over 1000 m2);<br />- laying down of all the necessary works to allow the connection of new buildings (and buildings subject to major renovation) to district heating systems, when existing (and not further than 1 km) or planned;<br />- installation of solar thermal systems that cover at least 50% of hot water demand for all new buildings and in case of replacement or renovation of the existing heating system;<br />- Installation of PV systems (with a power capacity to be defined in a subsequent ministerial decree) in all new buildings and in existing buildings with a total floor area over 1000m2;', '2008', NULL, NULL, NULL, '660', NULL, '1590', NULL, '2860', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'IT-4th National Communication, p.99, 111', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(833, 'IT-ENC-08', NULL, '30', 'Law 10 of 1991', 'Increase energy efficiency in the industrial sector', 'Law 10 of 1991, that along with law 9 implemented the National Energy Plan, made the appointment of an energy manager compulsory, as from 1991, in industrial plants, consuming more than 10,000 toe per year of primary energy and in services companies consuming more than 1000 toe per year. In 2005, about 816 industries and 1309 service companies had appointed their energy managers, with total increment of 15% from 2001.', '1991', NULL, '400', NULL, '400', NULL, '400', NULL, '400', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'IT-4th National Communication, p.99; IT-Progress report, p.13, 32', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(834, 'IT-ENC-09', NULL, '31', 'Replacement of low efficiency motors and inverters (Budget law 2007)', 'Increase energy efficiency in the industrial sector through tax incentives for the installation of highly efficient electric engines', 'The Budget law 2007 provides for tax credits of up to &euro; 1,500 for high efficiency electric engines and inverters purchased and installed within 31.12.2007.', '2007', NULL, NULL, NULL, '3600', NULL, '3600', NULL, '3600', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'IT-4th National Communication, p.97,111; IT-Progress report, p.13, 33', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(835, 'IT-ENC-11', 'CL-IT-ENC-01', '32', 'White Certificates in the Industry sector', 'Extension of the primary energy targets to 2012', 'The extension to 2012 of the primary energy saving targets provided for by the White certificates system is quite likely to be approved in the next few months.', '2009', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CL-IT-ENC-01', NULL, 'CL-IT-ENC-01', NULL, 'CL-IT-ENC-01', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'IT-4th National Communication, p.97,112', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(836, 'IT-ENC-12', 'CL-IT-ENC-01', '33', 'White Certificates in the Industry sector', 'Further extension of the primary energy targets to 2020', 'The extension to 2012 of the primary energy saving targets provided for by the White certificates system is quite likely to be approved in the next few months, while a further extension to 2016 and 2020 is still under discussion', '2009', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CL-IT-ENC-01', NULL, 'CL-IT-ENC-01', NULL, 'CL-IT-ENC-01', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'IT-4th National Communication, p.97,112', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(837, 'IT-ENC-13', 'CL-IT-ENC-01', '34', 'End use efficiency and energy services in the Industry sector', 'Energy savings through the implementation of directive 2006/32/CE', 'Achieving an overall energy savings target of 9% within 2017 through the implementation of directive 2006/32/CE', '2009', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CL-IT-ENC-01', NULL, 'CL-IT-ENC-01', NULL, 'CL-IT-ENC-01', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'IT-4th National Communication, p.97,112', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(838, 'IT-ENC-14', 'CL-IT-ENC-01', '35', 'Energy use in machinery', 'Mandatory energy efficiency standards for machinery', 'Further measures will be introduced to implement directive 2006/32/CE on energy end use efficiency and energy services.One option currently under discussion concerns the introduction of mandatory energy efficiency standards for machinery.', '2009', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CL-IT-ENC-01', NULL, 'CL-IT-ENC-01', NULL, 'CL-IT-ENC-01', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'IT-4th National Communication, p.97,112', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(839, 'IT-ENC-15', 'CL-IT-ENC-01', '36', 'Replacement of low efficiency motors and inverters', 'Obligation to install highly efficient electric motors, inverters, etc.', 'Further measures will be introduced to implement directive 2006/32/CE on energy end use efficiency and energy services. One option currently under discussion concerns the introduction of  the obligation to install highly efficient electric motors, inverters, etc when replacing the existing ones.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CL-IT-ENC-01', NULL, 'CL-IT-ENC-01', NULL, 'CL-IT-ENC-01', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'IT-4th National Communication, p.97,112', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(840, 'IT-ENC-17', NULL, '37', 'Energy efficiency in buildings (Budget Law 2007)', 'Energy saving in new and existing buildings', 'Budget law 2007 The Budget law 2007 provides for the following fiscal incentives for the implementation of energy efficiency projects in the civil sector:<br />- tax incentive of up to &euro; 100.000 for owners and tenants of existing buildings who reduce energy use by at least 20% relative to the requirements provided for by legislative decree 192/05 (end of project within 31.12.2007);<br />- Tax incentive of up to &euro; 60.000 to improve the insulation of existing buildings (end of project within 31.12.2007);<br />- Tax incentive of up to &euro; 60.000 to support the installation of solar thermal applications (within 31.12.2007);<br />- Tax incentive of up to &euro; 30.000 to replace the existing boilers with condensing boilers (within 31.12.2007);<br />- Tax incentive of up to 200 &euro; for any A+ refrigerator and freezer purchased within 31.12.2007;<br />- Tax incentive of 36% for the installation of energy saving lighting systems in non residential buildings (within 31.12.2009);<br />- contribution of 55% of the extra costs incurred to reduce the energy consumption of new buildings (with a surface of over 10.000 cubic meters) of at least 50% relative to the requirements provided for by legislative decree 192/05 (end of project within 31.12.2010). The Budget law sets up a specific Fund and authorizes up to 15 million euro annually for three years (2007 &ndash; 2009).', '2007', NULL, NULL, NULL, '1320', NULL, '2120', NULL, '2460', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'IT-4th National Communication, p.99f, 111', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(841, 'IT-ENC-18', NULL, '38', 'White Certificates in the Civil Sector', 'Extending the current obligation to 2012', 'There is a realistic chance that the White certificate system will soon be extended to 2012. The competent Ministries are currently working on a proposal that would set stronger obligations for the period 2010 &ndash; 2012, lower the minimum customer&rsquo;s threshold and involve more distributors in the system.', '2009', NULL, NULL, NULL, '600', NULL, '3400', NULL, '4420', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'IT-4th National Communication, p.100,112', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(842, 'IT-ENC-19', NULL, '39', 'White Certificates in the Civil Sector', 'Further extension of the primary energy saving targets to 2020', 'A further extension of the scheme to 2020 is also envisaged.', '2012', NULL, NULL, NULL, '600', NULL, '3400', NULL, '4420', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'IT-4th National Communication, p.100,112', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(843, 'IT-ENC-20', 'CL-IT-ENC-03', '40', 'Energy efficiency standards', 'Mandatory energy efficiency standards for appliances', 'Consistent reductions are expected also from the introduction of mandatory energy efficiency standards for appliances, currently under discussion in the competent Ministries.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CL-IT-ENC-03', NULL, 'CL-IT-ENC-03', NULL, 'CL-IT-ENC-03', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'IT-4th National Communication, p.100,112', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(844, 'IT-ENC-21', NULL, '41', 'Energy efficiency in buildings', 'Further reducing energy use in buildings and promoting the diffusion of renewable energy sources', 'The measure that has a realistic chance to be introduced in the near future is the further strengthening of energy efficiency requirements for new and existing buildings, reducing energy<br />consumption and promoting the diffusion of renewable energy sources', '2010', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '8750', NULL, '9110', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'IT-4th National Communication, p. 100, 112', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(845, 'CL-IT-ENC-01', 'CL-IT-ENC-01', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '930', NULL, '5920', NULL, '9500', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(846, 'IT-ENC-22', NULL, '42', 'Fund for new buildings (Art 351 - 352 of Budget law 2007)', 'Energy efficiency of new buildings', 'Contribution of 55% of the extra costs incurred to reduce the energy consumption of new buildings with a surface of over 10.000 cubic meters) of at least 50% relative to the requirements provided for by legislative decree 192/05 . This Fund provides for 15 million euro per year for three years (2007 - 2009).', '2007', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'IT-4th National Communication, p.86', NULL, NULL, '15000000', NULL, 'IT-Nat. Comm., p.86', NULL),
(847, 'IT-ENC-23', NULL, '43', 'Fund for energy efficiency and fuel poverty (Art 353 - 364 of Budget law 2007)', 'Energy efficiency in buildings', 'The Fund (11 million euro per year for three years) will finance: - the tax incentive of 36% for any energy saving lighting systems installed by 2009 in non residential buildings; - the tax incentive of up to 200 &euro; for any A+ refrigerator and freezer purchased by 31.12.2007; - the tax incentive of up to 1500 &euro; for highly efficient electric engines and inverters (5&lt;power&lt;90 kW) purchased and installed by 31.12.2007.', '2007', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'IT-4th National Communication, p.86', NULL, NULL, '100000000', NULL, 'IT-Nat. Comm., p.86', NULL),
(848, 'CL-IT-ENC-03', 'CL-IT-ENC-03', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '600', NULL, '3400', NULL, '4420', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(849, 'IT-AGR-01', NULL, '44', 'Common Agricultural Policy', 'Reduce emissions from agriculture', 'The implementation of the measures of the Common Agricultural Policy has influenced the major driving forces of agricultural GHG emissions in Italy: livestock number, use of fertilizers and crop surface. Livestock number and fertilizer consumption have also been affected by the enforcement of Directive 91/676/EC (the so-called Nitrates Directive) both directly and through its provisions related to the establishment of Codes of Good Agricultural Practice. Italy is also the country in Europe with the highest surface area devoted to organic farming (around 1 million hectares) and this could have an impact on the total amount of fertilizers used and on N2O emissions from soil.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'IT-4th National Communication, p.105', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(850, 'IT-AGR-02', NULL, '45', 'Code of good agricultural practice', '5% decrease in the consumption of nitrogen fertilizers', 'A decline in current trends of N2O emissions from soil might be obtained through a more rational use of fertilisers, as prescribed by the Code of Good Agricultural Practice (i.e. slow release nitrogen). To this regard, Italy has been one of the first countries of the European Union to draw up, under the provisions of EU Directive no. 676/91, a &ldquo;Code of Good Agricultural Practice for the Protection of Water from Nitrates&rdquo;, adopted under Ministerial Decree no. 86 of 19 April 1999.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'IT- 4th National Communication, p.105', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(851, 'IT-AGR-03', NULL, '46', 'Reduction in the use of nitrogen fertilizers', 'Reduce emissions from agriculture', 'Emission reduction from the Agricultural soil source is mainly related to the rationalisation in the use of fertilizers. In order to achieve the objective is essential to consider ongoing efforts to heighten awareness of the practise, the adoption of the code of agricultural practice, and the integrated production of agricultural holding and organic farming.<br />Further reductions of 2.5% (2010) and 5% (2010, 2015) in the use of nitrogen fertilizers have been considered as additional measure for the reduction of nitrous oxide emissions.', '2008', NULL, NULL, NULL, '250', NULL, '420', NULL, '490', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'IT-4th National Communication, p.105, 112', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(852, 'IT-AGR-04', NULL, '47', 'Collection and use of biogas from animal waste', 'Reduce emissions from agriculture', 'Electricity generation from animal waste has increased in Italy up to 25.7 GWh in 2005, thanks to the support provided by the feed-in prices granted by Resolution no. 6/92 of the Inter-ministerial Price Committee (CIP 6/92) and the renewable quota obligation for electricity producers/importers established by the Legislative Decree of March 16, 1999, No. 79, and subsequent legislation. In 2005, methane from biogas recovery has reduced methane emissions from manure management in 3.9%.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'IT-4th National Communication, p.105', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(853, 'IT-AGR-05', NULL, '48', 'Animal Storage', 'Recovery of biogas from animal storage systems', 'Additional measures for the reduction of methane emission are concentrated in two animal categories: cattle and swine. We have considered percentage of reduction for the manure<br />management source of 10% (2010), 15% (2015) and 20% (2020).<br />An investment analysis, taking into account the value of the electricity produced, generates a positive VAN, though the result is not enough to convince operators tested to invest. Therefore, the dimension of the initiative would depend on: the level of incentives available for the production of electricity from renewable energy sources, plus, the availability of subsidies for the construction of the systems, and a clear regulation with respect to the authoritative procedure for the final destination of the effluents.<br />Another measure oriented towards the same objective is the Integrated Pollution Prevention and Control Directive (96/61/EC), which calls for the introduction of an authorisation process based on the adoption of the Best Available Technology (BAT) for poultry farms with more than 40,000 birds and pig farms with more than 2,000 animals (heavier than 30 kg) or 750 sows. In terms of structural initiatives for existing facilities, financial incentives could be drawn from the Rural Development Plans (PSR) financed by the EAGGF.', '2008', NULL, NULL, NULL, '250', NULL, '420', NULL, '490', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'IT-4th National Communication, p.105, 112;', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(854, 'IT-WAM-02', NULL, '49', 'Separate collection', 'Compliance with separate collection targets and biodegradable waste disposed into landfills', 'A sharp decrease of methane emissions is expected in the future, through the implementation of directive 99/31/EC (the so-called Landfill Directive), which prescribes by 2016 a 35% reduction based on 1995 levels of biodegradable municipal waste sent to landfill by 2016. According to Decree 22/97, from the year 2000 landfilling will only be acceptable as a disposal option for inert waste and treated residues.', '2005', NULL, NULL, NULL, '1800', NULL, '2400', NULL, '2700', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'IT-4th National Communication, p.107, 111', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(855, 'IT-WAM-03', NULL, '50', 'Bio digradable waste', 'Treatment of 100% biodegradable waste prior to landfill', 'This measure regards the pre-treatment of all the biodegradable wastes which will be disposed into landfills, encouraging the anaerobic digestion of MSW also in co-digestion with other type of waste such as sludge from municipal waste water treatment plants and animal waste. This practice will increase also the energy recovery from the biogas production.', '2010', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4600', NULL, '4400', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'IT-4th National Communication, p.107, 112', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(856, 'IT-LUC-01', NULL, '51', 'Forestry', 'Forest Management', 'Italy has elected Forest Management as an activity under Article 3.4 of Kyoto Protocol, while has not elected Cropland Management, Grazing Land Management or Revegetation.<br />Forest management and art 3.3 activities shall be tracked and certified by the National Registry for forest carbon sinks in order to be accountable.', '2008', NULL, NULL, NULL, '10200', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'IT-4th National Communication, p.109, 112', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(857, 'IT-LUC-02', 'CL-IT-LUC-01', '52', 'Forestry', 'Afforestation and reforestation (old plantations) and induced recolonisation areas', 'Italy has elected Forest Management as an activity under Article 3.4 of Kyoto Protocol, while has not elected Cropland Management, Grazing Land Management or Revegetation.<br />Forest management and art 3.3 activities shall be tracked and certified by the National Registry for forest carbon sinks in order to be accountable.', '2008', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CL-IT-LUC-01', NULL, 'CL-IT-LUC-01', NULL, 'CL-IT-LUC-01', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'IT-4th National Communication, p.109, 112', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(858, 'IT-LUC-03', 'CL-IT-LUC-01', '53', 'Forestry', 'Afforestation and reforestation (new plantations)', 'Italy has elected Forest Management as an activity under Article 3.4 of Kyoto Protocol, while has not elected Cropland Management, Grazing Land Management or Revegetation.<br />Forest management and art 3.3 activities shall be tracked and certified by the National Registry for forest carbon sinks in order to be accountable.', '2008', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CL-IT-LUC-01', NULL, 'CL-IT-LUC-01', NULL, 'CL-IT-LUC-01', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'IT-4th National Communication, p.109, 112', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(859, 'CL-IT-LUC-01', 'CL-IT-LUC-01', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '15100', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(860, 'IT-CRS-01', NULL, '54', 'EU -ETS', 'Achieve the obligations in the frame of the Kyoto Protocol in terms of economic efficiency', 'Since 1st January 2005, operators of installations have been required to monitor their emissions and to ensure that they surrender allowances equivalent to their emissions in any calendar year.<br />On 15 May 2007, the European Commission has accepted Italy&rsquo;s National Allocation Plan for the period 2008-2012 on condition that certain changes were made, including a reduction in the total number of emission allowances proposed by 13.25 million tonnes of CO2 equivalent per year, to 195.75 million tonnes.', '2005', NULL, NULL, NULL, '13250', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '13250', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'IT-4th National Communication, p.85', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(861, 'IT-CRS-02', NULL, '55', 'Use of the kyoto mechanism', 'Achieve the obligations in the frame of the Kyoto Protocol in terms of economic efficiency', 'The contribution of the Kyoto mechanisms to the national emissions reduction target has been assessed at 20.75 MtCO2. <br />The credits, predominantly CERs and ERUs, will be mainly purchased through the Italian Carbon Fund (ICF), which was set up in 2003 following an agreement between the World Bank and the Italian Ministry for the Environment, Land and Sea. The ICF is open to the participation of the Italian private and public sector; the minimum contribution from each additional participant is set at US$1 million. Italy also contributes to the Community Development Carbon Fund (CDCF) and to the BioCarbon Fund (BioCF).<br />The average price of the credits purchased so far is about 6, 65 US dollars/tCO2. Assuming the average price will remain stable in future years, by the end of the commitment period 2008 &ndash; 2012 the economic resources already transferred to the World Bank will allow the purchase of about 3,42 MtCO2 per year.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'IT-4th National Communication, p.86', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(862, 'IT-CRS-3', NULL, '56', 'White Certificates (Decrees 20 July 2004)', 'Supporting energy saving in different sectors', 'The system was firstly introduced in July 2001 by means of two ministerial decrees, later repealed and substituted by two new decrees approved in April 2004. The new decrees set the obligation on electricity and gas distributors with more than 100,000 customers as of 31 December 2001, to achieve the primary energy saving target of 2.9 Mt of oil equivalent per year by 2009. The distributor&rsquo;s quota of national savings is determined according to the ratio of own electricity/gas distributed to the national total in the previous year. The annual energy saving targets can be achieved through the implementation of energy saving projects in all energy end-use sectors. Projects contribute to the achievement of targets for 5 years; only for specific projects (buildings thermal envelope, bioclimatic design, reduction of cooling needs, etc) the time limit is raised up to 8 years. Compliance with the target is verified through the surrender to the competent authority of the corresponding amount of White Certificates by May 1 of every year, starting with 2006. Each Certificate testifies the saving of 1 Mt of oil equivalent. Only additional savings over legislative requirements can be taken into consideration: projects implemented to abide the law cannot be awarded White Certificates. Projects can be implemented either by distributors - directly or through controlled companies - or by energy saving companies (E.S.Co.). Target-bound distributors can therefore gain their own certificates, or buy them on the market from other parties. Certificates can be traded bilaterally or else through an organized market.<br />Eligible projects:<br />- Rephasing of electric systems;<br />- Electric motors and their applications;<br />- Lighting systems;<br />- Reduction of electricity leaking;<br />- Switching from electricity to other fuels when this produces primary energy savings;<br />- Reduction of electricity consumption for heating purposes;<br />- Reduction of electricity consumption for air conditioning;<br />- High efficient electric appliances;<br />- High efficient office equipment;<br />- Switching from other fuels to electricity when this produces primary energy savings', '2006', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'IT-4th National Communication, p.84, 111', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(863, 'IT-CRS-4', NULL, '57', 'Interregional Operational Plan Renewable energy and energy efficiency', 'Supporting renewable energy and energy efficiency', 'The following projects will be financed: renewable energy plants; distributed cogeneration and trigeneration plants; district heating and cooling projects; promotion of energy efficiency projects; biofuel production', '2007', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'IT-4th National Communication, p.87', NULL, NULL, '114842857142857', NULL, 'IT-4th Nat. Comm., p.87', NULL),
(864, 'IT-CRS-5', NULL, '58', 'Regional Energy Plans', 'Harmonization of  important decisions at regional and local level', 'The Regional Energy Plan (PER) is the main tool through which the Regions can plan their intervention in the energy sector in their territory and regulate the functions of the Local Agencies, harmonizing the important decisions at regional and local level. The energy-environmental Plans are structured to guarantee coherent targets with the national energy policy and to insure that environmental and public health considerations are taken into account. They constitute the reference framework for private and public entities that operate in the energy sector at local level. The PER describes the regional guidelines, targets, available tools, legislative and normative references and financial opportunities.<br />All Italian Regions activated initiatives in the renewable energy sources field through two main<br />instruments. The first instrument is represented by the &quot;Photovoltaic Roofs&quot; Programme and the &quot;Solar thermal&quot; Programme, which were introduced in 2000 to implement the provisions of a decree issued by the Ministry for the Environment, Land and Sea. The second instrument is represented by the specific measures of the Regional Operative Programme (POR) financed through the Structural funds of the Community Support Framework 2000-2006.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'IT-4th National Communication, p.114ff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(865, 'LT-CRS-800', NULL, '1', 'National allocation plan for GHG emission allowances for the period 2005-2007', 'Substantial Reduction of GHG emissions', 'Substantial Reduction of GHG emissions through an emissions trading scheme', '2005', '2007', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Change in emission factors as a result of higher efficiency', 'Yes', 'National Energy Strategy', NULL, NULL, 'LT-2007 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC 07, p.7f, 30, 37', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(866, 'LT-ENS-01', NULL, '2', 'Installation of combined cycle gas turbine unit in the Lithuanian Power Plant', 'Increasing efficiency of power generation', 'The National Energy Strategy approved by the Seimas in January, 2007 requires to increase efficiency of the thermal power plants and to reduce costs of energy production. As an important step towards this direction, installation of combined cycle gas turbine unit 400 MW capacity in the Lithuanian Power Station is planned in 2010. Currently operated inefficient 150 MW capacity units will be dismantled after installation of the new unit.<br />Evaluated investment costs for installation of the combined cycle gas turbine unit are Euro 162 million.', '2007', '2010', '304', NULL, '345', NULL, '404', NULL, '483', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Change in emission factors as a result of higher efficiency', 'Yes', 'National Energy Strategy', 'Installation of combined cycle gas turbine unit', NULL, 'LT-2007 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC 07, p.8, 30, 37', 'Reduction of CO, NOx emissions', NULL, '40500000', '162 M &euro; evaluated investment costs in 2007-2010', 'LT-2007 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC 07, p.8', NULL),
(867, 'LT-ENS-02', NULL, '3', 'Construction of Combined heat and power plants', 'Increase the power production in CHP plants to 35% by 2020', 'The target set in the National Energy Strategy will be attained by construction of new CHP plants in Klaip?da, Panev?≈æys, &Scaron;iauliai, Alytus, Marijampol? and other cities with the total capacity of 400 MW.<br />Required investment costs are evaluated at Euro 449 million.', '2007', '2020', '235', NULL, '302', NULL, '379', NULL, '451', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Change in emission factors', NULL, 'National Energy Strategy', 'Construction of CHP plants', NULL, 'LT-2007 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC 07, p.8, 30, 37', 'Reduction of CO, NOx emissions', NULL, '32000000', '449 M &euro; evaluated investment costs in 2007-2020', 'LT-2007 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC 07, p.8', NULL),
(868, 'LT-ENS-03', NULL, '4', 'Use of renewable energy resources', 'Increase the share of renewable energy resources in the total energy balance to 7% in 2010 and 10 % in 2025', 'The target will be attained by promotion of construction of new wind power plants, small hydro power plants and CHP plants using bio fuel. According to expert evaluation energy potential of forest cutting waste in 2025 will be approximately 180 thou. TOE. In addition, energy potential of straw generated annually in agriculture is approximately 120 TOE. The National Energy Strategy requires the system of logistics for collection, storage, transportation and use of forest cutting waste and straw waste.<br />Investments for use of forest cutting waste are evaluated at Euro 27 million, investments for use of straw at Euro 13 million.', '2007', '2020', NULL, NULL, '300', NULL, '300', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Change in activity rate', 'Yes', 'National Energy Strategy', 'Construction of new wind, hydro or biomass power plants', NULL, 'LT-2007 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC 07, p.8, 30, 37', NULL, NULL, '3000000', '40 M &euro; (27 M &euro; for forest cutting waste + 13 M &euro; for use of straw) evaluated investment costs in 2007-2020', 'LT-2007 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC 07, p.8', NULL),
(869, 'LT-ENC-04', NULL, '5', 'Energy saving in residential houses', 'Reduction of energy consumption in residential houses', 'Residential houses built 15 or more years ago are very inefficient from energy performance perspective. The National Energy Strategy foresees upgrading of residential houses including insulation and upgrading of heat supply systems. It is planned to change up to 75% of heat supply networks by 2015. According to the National Energy Strategy final energy consumption in residential sector in the future should remain at the current level or even decrease as a result of upgrading.<br />Investments for upgrading of residential houses are evaluated at Euro 405 million.<br />In 2004 the Government of the Republic of Lithuania approved the Lithuanian Housing Strategy.  One of the key objectives of the Strategy is to ensure efficient use, maintenance and modernization of the existing housing stock, and rational use of energy resources. The Strategy provides for, by 2020, modernisation based on the economic feasibility principle of heating systems in the existing multi-apartment buildings, renovation and insulation of roof structures, change or replacement of windows and entrance doors, removal of joint defects of panel walls and increase of the thermal resistance of external walls, as well as reduction of heat energy costs per unit of useful floor space up to 30 %. Based on provisions of National energy strategy and by implementing Lithuanian housing strategy Government adopted &ldquo;The programme for the financing of modernization of multi-flat buildings&rdquo;. The main aim of the programme is to help owners of multi-flat houses to modernize multi-flat buildings, increase efficiency of energy use, reduce heating expenses and ensure favorable conditions for low income population to modernize them apartments in multi-flat buildings.', '2007', '2015', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Change in emission factors', NULL, 'National Energy Strategy', 'Upgraded residential houses', NULL, 'LT-2007 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC 07, p.9, 30, 38', NULL, NULL, '45000000', '405 M &euro; evaluated investment costs in 2007-2015', 'LT-2007 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC 07, p.9', NULL);
