(870, 'LT-TRA-02', NULL, '6', 'Promotion of biofuel use in transport', 'Increasing share of biofuel consumption in transport sector to 5.75% in 2010 and to 15%  (450 TOE) in 2025.', 'The promotion of the production and use of biofuel is foreseen in the Law of the Republic of Lithuania on Biofuel, Biofuels for Transport and Bio-oils. The Law sets a target to increase the share of bio fuel consumed in the transport sector to 5.75% in 2010. The National Energy Strategy foresees expansion of areas of plants used for biodiesel production with the aim to increase biofuel consumption to 15% by 2020 and 450 toe in 2025 corresponding to 20% of the total fuel consumption in the transport sector.<br />The Programme for Promotion of Production and Use of Biofuel in 2004-2010 approved by the Government in 2004 foresees sowing of 66.7 thou. ha under rapes intended for the production of bio diesel and 16.22 thou. ha under cereals intended for the production of bioethanol in 2010. Provisions set in the Law of Biofuel (Article 4) regulates the production of biofuel from local raw materials and establishes the procedure for promotion of such biofuel. Guarantees are provided for producers, users of biofuel as well as investors to production of biofuel.<br />Required investments for expansion of biofuel use in transport are evaluated at Euro 87 million.', '2004', '2010', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Change in emission factors', NULL, 'Programme for Promotion of Production and Use of Biofuel', 'Production of biofuel', NULL, 'LT-2007 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC 07, p.10, 30, 38', 'Reduction of CO, NOx emissions', NULL, '12500000', '87 M &euro; evaluated investment costs in 2004-2010', 'LT-2007 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC 07, p.10', NULL),
(871, 'LT-ENC-06', NULL, '7', 'Increase in energy efficiency', 'To increase power production in CHP plants to 20% by 2010 and to 35% by 2020;<br />?To increase the share of RES in the total primary energy supply to 12 % by 2010;<br />?To increase the share of RES in the total power generation to 7% by 2010;<br />?To reduce heat consumption in buildings by 7% in 2010<br />?To produce 2 TWh of energy from waste in 2010.', 'The National Energy Efficiency Programme for 2006&ndash;2010 adopted in 2006 foresees several important organizational and institutional measures aimed at increasing energy efficiency. The measures include ?drafting of legal acts and regulations, promotion of R&amp;D in energy efficiency, information dissemination, energy audits, pilot and demonstration projects, training, education and consultation activities. The objectives of the National energy efficiency programme is increasing the efficiency of energy production and consumption, and extension of use of renewable energy sources.', '2006', '2010', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LT-2007 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC 07, p.10f', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(872, 'LT-TRA-01', NULL, '8', 'Implementation of Energy efficiency programme', 'Increase of  energy use efficiency in transport sector', 'The National Energy Efficiency Programme for 2006&ndash;2010 states that the energy efficiency potential in the transport sector is on average 1,7 TWh or 0.15 Mtoe per year. The reduction in greenhouse gas emissions as a result of the introduction of energy efficiency measures in the transport sector will amount to 0,442 Mt per year. The measures aimed at increasing energy efficiency in transport sector include promotion of public transport by strengthening its competitiveness, investments in new routes of public transport, pedestrian and bicycle tracks, promotion of competitiveness of railway transport by zoning and planning the transport network.', '2001', NULL, '442', NULL, '442', NULL, '410', NULL, '410', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Change in emission factors', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LT-2007 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC 07, p.10, 31, 38', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(873, 'LT-IND-01', NULL, '9', 'Pollution prevention in industry', 'Reduction of Energy intensity in industry, EMS and cleaner production', 'Reduction of energy intensity in industry will be pursued by upgrading of production facilities and implementation of cleaner production methods. Introduction of best available techniques as part of the implementation of the Integrated Pollution Prevention and Control (IPPC) directive will, to a certain extent, reduce GHG emissions from industrial installations. EU environmental requirements for BAT, requirements in the field of minimization of environmental impact by industry will speed up the implementation of environment friendly technologies and cleaner production methods, as well as application of more effective environmental protection measures.', NULL, NULL, '510', NULL, '480', NULL, '440', NULL, '420', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Change in emission factors', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LT-2007 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC 07, p.10, 31, 38', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(874, 'LT-LUC-01', NULL, '10', 'Expansion of forest area', 'Additional increase of forest area by 196 thou. ha in 2004-2020 or approximately 12 thou. ha annually', 'Forest expansion strategy for 2004-2020 and its implementation measures are set in the Lithuanian Forest Area Expansion Program developed and approved by the joint Order of the Ministers of Environment and Agriculture No. 616/471 on December 2, 2002.<br />The Programme aims at additional increase of forest area by 196 thou. ha or approximately 12 thou. ha annually. It is estimated that forest area is currently expanding by approximately 4-5 thou. ha annually as a result of natural, spontaneous forest growth in unmanaged land areas. In order to attain the target set in the Programme,  it is planned to plant additionally 7 thou. ha of forest each year.', '2004', '2020', NULL, NULL, '33', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '165', NULL, 'Change in activity rate', NULL, 'Lithuanian Forest Area Expansion Program approved by the Ministers of Environment and Agriculture', 'Forest area', NULL, 'LT-2007 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC 07, p.10, 31, 38', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(875, 'LT-WAM-01', NULL, '11', 'Reduction of biodegradable waste disposed of in landfills', 'Reduction of methane emissions fromlandfills', 'Separate collection and composting of green and kitchen waste (22% of the total biodegradable waste) in 2010; Incineration of municipal waste from Vilnius, Utena, Kaunas, Alytus and Marijampol? counties (60% of the total municipal waste for disposal) in 2013; Incineration of municipal waste from Klaip?da, Tel&scaron;iai and Taurag? counties (20% of the total municipal waste for disposal) in 2020.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '10,5', NULL, '42', NULL, '21', NULL, '84', NULL, 'Change in activity rate', NULL, 'National Strategic Waste Management Plan', 'Quantity of biodegradable waste disposed in landfills', NULL, 'LT-2007 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC 07, p.11, 31, 38', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(876, 'LT-ENS-04', NULL, '12', 'Construction of new nuclear power plant', 'Reduction of energy costs, reduction of GHG emissions', 'The National Energy Strategy sets the target to construct new NPP in 2015. Bearing in mind huge investment costs required for construction of the NPP, regional cooperation with neighbouring countries (Estonia, Latvia, Poland) is necessary. Negotiations on cooperation has been started but final agreement is not yet reached. Therefore, though construction of the NPP is foreseen in the  National Energy Strategy, the final decision is not yet taken and the measure is included as additional.<br />Investments required for construction of new NPP are evaluated at Euro 3 billion.', '2010', '2015', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2300', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Change in activity rate', NULL, 'National Energy Strategy', 'Nuclear power plant', NULL, 'LT-2007 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC 07, p.9, 31, 38', NULL, NULL, '500000000', '3 billion &euro; evaluated investment costs in 2010-2015', 'LT-2007 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC 07, p.9', NULL),
(877, 'LT-TRA-03', NULL, '13', 'Fuel taxes: excise exemptions for biofuel', 'Increased use of biofuel', 'Provisions set in the Law of Biofuel (Article 4) regulates the production of biofuel from local raw materials and establishes the procedure for promotion of such biofuel. Guarantees are provided for producers, users of biofuel as well as investors to production of biofuel. Moreover, the Law on Biofuel sets a target for a share of biofuels consumed in the transport sector to 2% in 2005 and to 5.75% by in 2010.', NULL, NULL, '78', NULL, '255', NULL, '313', NULL, '390', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Change in emission factors', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LT-2007 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC 07, p.31, 38', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(878, 'LT-TRA-04', NULL, '14', 'Limitation of emissions of volatile organic compounds', 'Limitation of emissions of volatile organic compounds', 'Legal act of the Ministers of Environment, social security and labor, and transport and communications was approved in 2000 and revised in 2001 determining limitations for emissions of volatile organic compounds from modern equipment of petrol storage, distribution and transportation.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LT-2007 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC 07, p.9', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(879, 'LU-TRA-01', NULL, '1', 'Implementation of biofuel directive', 'Increasing the share of biofuels in overall fuel consumption', 'Increasing the share of biofuels in overall fuel consumption: from 2008-10, 2% of overall CO2 emissions in transport sector; from 2008-2020, 5.75% of overall CO2 emissions in transport sector. Luxembourg has implemented the Directive end 2005. The law implements a tax reduction for gasoline and diesel with a minimum fraction of biofuel content: for gasoline a tax reduction of 45.61 &euro;/1000 litres and for diesel of 42.34 &euro;/1000 litres is granted.', '2005', NULL, NULL, NULL, '160', NULL, '540', NULL, '620', NULL, NULL, 'Data standard availabe in early 2005;WM:adoption 2003-2005;WAM:adopted after 2005', NULL, NULL, 'LU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC 2008, p.23ff', NULL, NULL, 'LU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.11, 17', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(880, 'LU-TRA-02', NULL, '2', 'Excise duty on gasoline', 'Reduction of fuel sales by raising excise duty on gasoline', 'The excise duties on gasoline was raised by 70.00 &euro;/1000 litres by the 1st of January 2004. This  change in the excise rate was accompanied by an increase in the VAT rate from 12 to 15% from 2005 on. The overall price effect was estimated to about 0.07 &euro; per litre of gasoline for 2004 and to 0.08 to 0.10 &euro; per litre of gasoline from 2005 on.', '2004', NULL, '540', NULL, '540', NULL, '540', NULL, '540', NULL, NULL, 'Data standard availabe in early 2005;WM:adoption 2003-2005;WAM:adopted after 2005', NULL, NULL, 'LU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC 2008, p.23ff', NULL, NULL, 'LU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.12, 17', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(881, 'LU-TRA-03', NULL, '3', 'Excise duty on diesel', 'Reduction of fuel sales by raising excise duty on diesel', 'The excise rate on diesel was raised by 12.50 &euro;/1000 litres by the 1st of January 2005. In combination with the increase of the VAT rate from 12 to 15%, the price effect was estimated to 0.03 to 0.04 &euro; per litre from 2005 on.', '2005', NULL, '390', NULL, '390', NULL, '390', NULL, '390', NULL, NULL, 'Data standard availabe in early 2005;WM:adoption 2003-2005;WAM:adopted after 2005', NULL, NULL, 'LU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC 2008, p.23ff', NULL, NULL, 'LU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.12, 17', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(882, 'LU-TRA-04', NULL, '4', 'Vehicle tax reform', 'Carbon oriented taxation of vehicles in Luxembourg', 'Luxembourg planned to implement a reform of vehicle taxation based on specific CO2 emissions. The vehicle tax reform only affecting the vehicle fleet based in Luxembourg, the effect on energy consumption and emissions would therefore be limited to emissions generated by the residents. In the long run, this tax reform should offer incentives to buy more fuel efficient cars and, thus, should lower the average specific fuel consumption of the national vehicle fleet.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '97', NULL, '220', NULL, '504', NULL, NULL, 'Data standard availabe in early 2005;WM:adoption 2003-2005;WAM:adopted after 2005', NULL, NULL, 'LU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC 2008, p.23ff', NULL, NULL, 'LU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.18, 20', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(883, 'LU-TRA-05', NULL, '5', 'Improvement of modal split', 'Increasing the share of public transport', 'In 2005, Luxembourg planned to implement measures that should increase the share of public transport up to 25% in 2020.<br />The program consisted of the following elements:<br />&bull; expansion of the international railway network: link to the TGV-Est, EUROCAP RAIL: linking Brussels, Luxembourg and Strasbourg;<br />&bull; expansion of national railway network: new railway connections from Luxembourg to Bettembourg and Luxembourg to Esch-sur-Alzette;<br />&bull; construction of suburban train stations to enhance the opportunity to use Park&amp;Ride more<br />extensively;<br />&bull; creation of a &ldquo;Centrale de Mobilit&eacute;&rdquo;, which will serve as an integrated public transport service platform to promote the use of public transport in Luxembourg.<br />This measures are mainly under the authority of Ministry of Transport. Yet there is no detailed assessment of the possible GHG emissions reduction volume available.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.18, 20', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(884, 'LU-TRA-06', NULL, '6', 'Excise duty on gasoline', 'Reduction of fuel sales by raising excise duty on gasoline', 'The increase of excise duties on gasoline and diesel were planned to go on from 2006 onwards. Yet, in 2005, it was not decided to what extent. Thus, no estimation was feasible for this report.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.19f', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(885, 'LU-TRA-07', NULL, '7', 'Excise duty on diesel', 'Reduction of fuel sales by raising excise duty on diesel', 'The increase of excise duties on gasoline and diesel were planned to go on from 2006 onwards. Yet, in 2005, it was not decided to what extent. Thus, no estimation was feasible for this report.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.19f', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(886, 'LU-CRS-01', NULL, '8', 'Energy efficiency and Renewables in the Civil sector', 'Promotion of energy efficiency and usage of Renewables in the Civil sector', 'From 2001 to 2005, a set of laws has been implemented to promote energy efficiency improvements in buildings as well as a wider use of renewable energy sources. Both the law of the 22nd of February 2004 and the two regulations of the 3rd of August 2005 aimed at promoting the utilisation of renewable energy sources and energy efficiency in Luxembourg. The two regulations are classified as &ldquo;measures&rdquo; since they were modifying already existing legal provisions. Some subsidies and grants have also been especially defined for the small &amp; medium sized enterprises (manufacturing industries, retail, services). These financial aids are covering measures taken in favour of environment protection and a more reasonable use of natural resources, including investments relating to energy use.<br />The measures taken to promote a more reasonable use of energy and renewable energy sources have been complemented by tax allowances and by special feed-in tariffs for electricity produced from renewable energy sources.', '2004', NULL, '10', NULL, '60', NULL, '120', NULL, '170', NULL, NULL, 'Though no detailed assessment of the impact on CO2 emissions in the residential, commercial and institutional sectors has been carried out with respect to the particular laws implemented, some indications on the magnitude of the potential effect on CO2 emissions can be drawn from a study by the Luxembourg engineering consultants G&amp;L. G&amp;L estimated an overall annual reduction potential in the construction and housing sector of 21,000 t CO2e per year. For this report it is assumed that at least &ndash; as a rough estimate - 50% of this reduction potential are assigned to the &ldquo;baseline&rdquo; reductions that are not motivated by the legal initiatives described above and that are offset by growth in the building stock. Thus, about 10,500 t CO2e reduction per year is estimated being the result of the implemented policies and measures.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.13f, 17', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(887, 'LU-CRS-02', NULL, '9', 'Energy efficiency and Renewables in the Industry and Powergen Sector', 'Promotion of energy efficiency and usage of Renewables in the Industry and Powergen sector', 'In the industrial sector, financial incentives such as investment subsidies are granted for certain projects in favour of renewable energy use and improvement of energy efficiency as well as for the electricity produced using renewable sources that is introduced in the public network.', '2004', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Only a relatively small fraction of overall electricity consumption in Luxembourg was generated by installations in Luxembourg &ndash; especially since the generation from blast furnace gas was stopped. Therefore, in line with the IPCC allocation rule of GHG emissions based on the territorial principle, the promotion of renewable energy sources in the electricity sector as well as the promotion of CHP does not contribute to CO2 reductions in Luxembourg. Consequently, measures taken in the area of the promotion of electricity from renewable energy sources are not assessed in this report.', NULL, NULL, 'LU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC 2008, p.15, 23ff', NULL, NULL, 'LU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.16f', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(888, 'LU-CRS-03', NULL, '10', 'Emissions Trading Scheme', 'Emissions from installations covered by the Directive are regulated by a fixed carbon cap.', 'The main policy implemented to control emissions in the industry and power generation sector is the Emissions Trading Directive (2003/87/EC). In 2003, GHG emissions in industry and power generation amounted to 3.6 Mio. t CO2e. However, not all installations included in this emissions volume are subject to the regulation of the Emissions Trading Directive. The first NAP 2005-07 enforced a reduction potential of 185,000 t CO2 from 2005 on for the ETS sector compared to the baseline scenario.', '2005', NULL, '185', NULL, '185', NULL, '185', NULL, '185', NULL, NULL, 'The first NAP 2005-07 enforced a reduction potential of 185,000 t CO2 from 2005 on for the ETS sector compared to the baseline scenario. Other reduction potentials mentioned in the NAP regarding installations not covered by the Directive are not considered as measures in this report.', NULL, NULL, 'LU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC 2008, p.15, 23ff', NULL, NULL, 'LU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.15, 17', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(889, 'LU-CRS-04', NULL, '11', 'Energy efficiency and Renewables in the Civil sector', 'Promotion of energy efficiency and usage of Renewables in the Civil sector', 'Luxembourg planned to set out financial incentives for the promotion of energy efficiency and renewable energy projects. One priority area is the injection of biogas into the natural gas network. The substitution of natural gas by biogas reduces the CO2 emissions assigned to the Luxembourg account, especially for power generation and for building heating systems. A GHG reduction, in contrast, would not occur if biogas would burn in additional power generation capacities. In this case, the electricity generated would only substitute carbon neutral electricity imports.<br />Yet, it is not clear how the promotion of renewable energy sources in Luxembourg will be implemented. A study by the Fraunhofer ISI is currently being carried out to evaluate the overall potential of renewable energy sources in Luxembourg. The study will also give advice on efficient schemes to promote renewable energy sources.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.19f', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(890, 'LU-CRS-05', NULL, '12', 'Emissions Trading Scheme (second trading period)', 'Emissions from installations covered by the Directive are regulated by a fixed carbon cap.', 'The second NAP, that was due in 2006, required Luxembourg to further limit emission volumes in the ETS sector, compared to the first NAP. In 2005, it was not decided yet to what extent emissions would be cut. For the quantitative estimate of the reduction potential this report expects an additional decrease of emissions by about 0.045 Mio. t CO2e from 2008 on compared to the reduction enforced by the first NAP.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '45', NULL, '45', NULL, '45', NULL, NULL, 'In 2005, it was not decided yet to what extent emissions would be cut. For the quantitative estimate of the reduction potential this report expects an additional decrease of emissions by about 0.045 Mio. t CO2e from 2008 on compared to the reduction enforced by the first NAP.', NULL, NULL, 'LU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC 2008, p.19, 23ff', NULL, NULL, 'LU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.19f', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(891, 'LU-ENC-01', NULL, '13', 'Energy efficiency campaigns', 'Campaigns to promote energy efficiency', 'The Ministry for the Environment regularly launches campaigns to raise awareness about climate change. In 1991, the Energy Agency was created to promote renewable energy projects and to inform citizens, the economic sector as well as municipalities on a better use of energy, renewable energy sources and financial public support: more on www.ael.lu.', '1991', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.14, 17', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(892, 'LU-ENC-02', NULL, '14', 'Voluntary agreement with the FEDIL (Union of Luxemburg Enterprises)', 'Increasing energy efficiency in the Industry sector', 'In April 2002, the members of the FEDIL agreed upon a voluntary agreement promoting the improvement of energy efficiency in the industrial sector. The agreement includes the establishment of energy management systems in order to enable companies to monitor their energetic performance. For this purpose companies are committed to collect data on energy consumption and corresponding output figures in order to generate &ldquo;energy efficiency indicators&rdquo;. Moreover, energy audits shall be introduced to disclose energy efficiency potentials in the production processes. In cooperation with the Energy Agency, the FEDIL agreed to conduct information campaigns to raise its members&rsquo; awareness of the issue of energy efficiency and renewable energy usage. <br />In April 2005, a target for the improvement of energy efficiency in the industrial sector was introduced into the voluntary agreement. The FEDIL and the Ministry of Economy and External Trade as well as the Ministry of the Environment finally agreed upon the adoption of a minimum improvement of energy efficiency of 15% in the time period between 1990 and 2005.', '2002', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LU-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC, p.16f', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(893, 'LV-ENS-01', NULL, '1', 'Investment programmes to support energy efficiency &amp; promote RES use in the DH systems', 'More effective use of fuel in the DH system, promotion of co-generation of heat and power, reducing energy loss and emissions, increasing  the share of RES in the fuel balance earmarked for district heating', 'Years 2001-2006: Fuel-switch projects in a number of municipal DH companies to replace fossil fuel  with biomass. National programme &ldquo;Improvement of Heat Supply Systems, Reducing the Sulphur Content of fuel&rdquo; to eliminate the use of HFO with high sulpur content.   Public investment programme for renovation of municipal DH systems. Years 2007-2013: financial support will be provided by 1) for DH systems efficiency increase and RES utilisation - national operational programme &quot;Infrastructure and services&quot; (activity No3521), 2) for RES-based CHP development - national operational programme &quot;Infrastructure and services&quot; (activity No3522), and 3) for rural villages DH renovation - national &quot;Rural Development programme&quot; (activity No 321) &quot;Renovation or construction of RES-based energy supply system in rural villages&quot;', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LV-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC; LV-Submission 2007', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(894, 'LV-ENC-03', NULL, '2', 'Support of projects improving energy performance of buildings', 'Involving end-users to increase energy performance of buildings, thus reducing energy consumption and emissions', 'Financial support will be provided by the national operational programme &quot;Infrastructure and services 2007-2013&quot; (activity No344) with two target audiences - multidwelling houses and social dwelling houses.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '7,54', NULL, '60,91', NULL, '92,2', NULL, '49,59', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LV-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC; LV-Submission 2007', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(895, 'LV-ENC-05', NULL, '3', 'Projects improving energy performance of buildings', 'Involving end-users to increase energy performance of buildings, thus reducing energy consumption and emissions', '&quot;The National Energy Strategy 2007-2016&quot; provides the targets for reducing specific energy consumption in buildings and determines the quantitative target for the first stage (to reach 195 kWh/m2 per year). This is considered as the voluntary measure performed by stakeholders, in addition to previous measure (which defines the state support for this target).', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3,46', NULL, '21,95', NULL, '481,51', NULL, '6,03', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LV-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(896, 'LV-ENS-07', NULL, '4', '&ldquo;Law on Energy&rdquo; (1998), followed by &quot;Electricity Market Law&quot; (2005).', '(inter alia) Encouraging development of local and renewable energy resources and efficient use of fuel', 'Establishment of conditions and methodology  for applying instruments of obligatory purchase requirement and feed-in tarifs for power produced by renewable sourcies or in the CHP mode', '2006', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LV-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC; LV-Submission 2007', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(897, 'LV-ENS-02', NULL, '5', 'Support for power generation in small hydropower plants', 'Increase the share of renewables in the energy balance', 'The support is provided in the form of obligatory purchase requirement and feed-in tarif; initially introduced by the &ldquo;Energy Law&rdquo;, from 05.2005 - by the new &quot;Electricity Market Law&quot; and related Regulations of CM No.503, 2007, determining methodology for calculation of feed-in tarif for small HPP up to 5 MW. Quantitative target for electricity production in small HPP development is defined by national &quot;Strategy for Utilisation of Renewable Resources 2006-2013&quot; (adopted by CM, 2006).', NULL, NULL, '3,6', NULL, '4,52', NULL, '4,52', NULL, '4,52', NULL, '20,76', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LV-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC; LV-Submission 2007', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(898, 'LV-ENS-03', NULL, '6', 'Support for power generation in wind plants', 'Increase the share of renewable sources in the energy balance', 'The support is provided in the form of obligatory purchase requirement, feed-in tarifs (initially introduced by the &quot;Energy Law&quot;) and investment support. The Regulations of CM No. 503, issued 2007 under &quot;Electricity Market Law&quot; (05.2005) determines methodology for calculation of feed-in tarif for small WPP up to 0.25 MW capacity and application of obligatory purchase requirement on the basis of applicants competition for WPP with higher capacity. Investment support for WPP development will be provided by national operational programme &quot;Infrastructure and services 2007-2013&quot;, activity No3523. Quantitative targets for wind energy development is set by National energy strategy 2007-2016 and National Strategy for Utilisation of Renewable Resources 2006-2013 (adopted by CM, 2006).', NULL, NULL, '2,73', NULL, '19,95', NULL, '23,2', NULL, '29,52', NULL, '67,22', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LV-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC; LV-Submission 2007', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(899, 'LV-ENS-16', NULL, '7', 'Support for energy generation in biogas plants from agriculture waste', 'Increase the share of renewable sources in the energy balance. Reduction of GHG emissions by appropriate waste management process', 'Generating CH4 in anaerobic degradation process, collection of biogas and its use in production of power and heat has a considerable potential to reduce GHG emissions. The support is provided in the form of obligatory purchase requirement and feed-in tarifs for power (initially introduced by the &quot;Energy Law&quot;) and investment support. The Regulations of CM No. 503, issued 2007 under &quot;Electricity Market Law&quot; (05.2005) determines methodology for calculation of feed-in tarif for biogas plants. Investment support will be provided by national &quot;Rural Development Programme&quot; activity No312(311)/3. Quantitative targets is set by the National project on the &quot;Biogas Generation and Development Programme 2007-2011 (adopted by CM, 2007). Development of biogas production is included in both National energy strategy and National Strategy for Utilisation of Renewable Resources (adopted by CM, 2006)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '14,81', NULL, '55,08', NULL, '55,08', NULL, '78,42', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LV-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC; LV-Submission 2007', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(900, 'LV-ENS-16', NULL, '8', 'Support for power genaration in biogas plants from landfill waste', 'Increase the share of renewable sources in the energy balance. Reduction of GHG emissions by appropriate waste management process', 'Collection of biogas (landfill gas) and its use in production of power and heat has a considerable potential to reduce GHG emissions. The support is provided in the form of obligatory purchase requirement and feed-in tarifs for power (initially introduced by the &quot;Energy Law&quot;) and investment support. The Regulations of CM No. 503, issued 2007 under &quot;Electricity Market Law&quot; (05.2005) determines methodology for calculation of feed-in tarif for biogas plants. Development of biogas production is included in both National energy strategy and National Strategy for Utilisation of Renewable Resources (adopted by CM, 2006).', NULL, NULL, '119,93', NULL, '174,9', NULL, '249,85', NULL, '249,85', NULL, '822,13', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LV-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC; LV-Submission 2007', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(901, 'LV-ENS-18', NULL, '9', 'Support the power generation in combined heat-power plants utilising renewable fuel', 'Increase the share of renewable sources in the energy balance', 'The support is provided in the form of obligatory purchase requirement and feed-in tarif (initially introduced by the &quot;Energy Law&quot;). The Regulations of CM No. 503, issued 2007 under &quot;Electricity Market Law&quot; (05.2005) determines methodology for calculation of feed-in tarif for biomass CHP plants with the capacity up to 4MW and conditions for applying obligatory purchase requirement for bioenergy CHP with capacity more than 4 MW. Quantitative targets for biomass CHP development is set by National energy strategy 2007-2016 and National Strategy for Utilisation of Renewable resources (adopted by CM, 2006).', NULL, NULL, '2,69', NULL, '99,63', NULL, '196,57', NULL, '278,71', NULL, '362,18', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LV-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC; LV-Submission 2007', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(902, 'LV-ENS-19', NULL, '10', 'Support the power generation in combined heat-power plants', 'More effective use of fuel', 'The support is provided in the form of obligatory purchase requirement and feed-in tarif (initially introduced for small scale CHP by the &quot;Energy Law&quot;). In 05.2005 new  &ldquo;Electricity Market Law&rdquo; was adopted stating new methodology for support. The Regulations of CM No. 921, issued 2006 under &quot;Electricity Market Law&quot;, determines the feed-in tarif for CHP with the capacity up to 4MW and conditions for applying obligatory purchase requirement for CHP with capacity more than 4 MW (the tarif set by the Regulator). Quantitative targets for new CHP development is set by National energy strategy (adopted by CM, 2006).', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '165,42', NULL, '401,74', NULL, '401,74', NULL, '496,27', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LV-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(903, 'LV-ENS-20', NULL, '11', 'Support for biofuels farmers and producers', 'Increase the share of renewables in the energy balance', 'The support is provided in the form of 1) subsidies for biofuels producers - per 1 liter of produced biofuel in the frame of defined quotas; 2) energy culture areas payments for farmers. Quantitative targets for biofuels development up to year 2020 is set by National energy strategy (adopted by CM, 2006) - 5.75% (2010), 10% (2016) and 15% (2020) from the total fuel consumption in transport sector.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LV-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(904, 'LV-ENS-21', NULL, '12', 'Support for fuel production form agriculture and forestry products (except biogas)', 'Increase the share of renewables in the energy balance &amp; promote the type of non-agriculture production activities and employment in rural regions', 'The financial support is provided for enterprises situated in rural regions under the national Rural Development Programme activity 312(311)/3', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LV-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(905, 'LV-IND-03', NULL, '13', 'Promote the implementation of best available techniques (BAT), environmentally friendly technologies and cleaner production', 'Promote the implementation of best available technologies and cleaner production', 'The implementation of BAT is closely linked to the permitting procedure for integrated pollution prevention and control. The concept of integrated permits appeared in Latvia&rsquo;s environmental protection legislation with the transposition of EU environmental legislation, specifically &ndash; the Council Directive 96/61/EC of 24 September 1996 concerning integrated pollution prevention and control. Thus a transition to an integrated permitting system has continued since 2001, where three categories &ndash; A, B and C, depending on the type and amount of polluting activities, are identified. Approximately 113 companies in Latvia fall under the scope of the directive on integrated pollution prevention and control (category A operations).', '2001', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LV-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC; LV-Submission 2007', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(906, 'LV-ENC-04', NULL, '14', 'Regulations for labelling of household air conidtioners, electric bulbs, dish washing machines, washing machines, drying machines, refrigerators, freezers and ovens', 'Reducing energy consumption in households', NULL, '2002', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LV-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC; LV-Submission 2007', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(907, 'LV-WAM-04', NULL, '15', 'Processing biologically degradable waste', 'To reduce by 2020 the amount of biodegradable waste for disposal by 35% of the amount of biodegradable waste for disposal in 1995; increase the share of biodegradable waste recovery (recycling and energy recovery)', 'A network of stations for the collection of sorted municipal waste will be established in Latvia. The European Regional Development Fund (hereinafter, &ndash; ERDF) provides support for the establishment of waste collection and sorting areas on the basis of the waste management plan of the respective region.In 2003, the EU LIFE project &ldquo;Treatment of Biodegradable Organic Municipal Waste Using Composting Technologies&rdquo; was launched. In two Latvia  municipalities &ndash; Stopini and Kekava, biodegradable organic waste sorting and recycling is carried out, using two different methods: open-air composting and bioreactor method. Proposals are being prepared for implementing biodegradable organic waste treatment methods in the municipal waste management systems of other Latvian municipalities.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LV-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC; LV-Submission 2007', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(908, 'LV-WAM-06', NULL, '16', 'Restoration of small municipal dumpsites not meeting environmental requirements', 'Closing of existing dumpsites by 2009 and their complete restoration by 2012', 'One of the most significant problems of in municipal waste management is the large number of small municipal waste dumpsites and the negative impact they have on the environment. Of more than 500 dumpsites identified during the elaboration of the State Investment Programme &ldquo;Strategy for Municipal Waste Management in Latvia, 500-&ldquo;, 176 dumpsites with the total area of 261 ha were restored in the period 1998-2004, that is, 33% of the total number of dumpsites. Nevertheless, in the territory of Latvia 28% of the waste dumpsites that were initially identified as not meeting environmental requirements, are still operational. Annually, on average about 4% of the identified dumpsite areas are restored.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LV-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC; LV-Submission 2007', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(909, 'LV-WAM-07', NULL, '17', 'Law on waste management', 'Prevention of waste generation, recycling for material and energy reocovery, close and restore existing dumpsites and establish new municipal waste landfills', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LV-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC; LV-Submission 2007', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(910, 'LV-WAM-08', NULL, '18', 'National Plan for waste management (2003-2012)', 'Prevention of waste generation, reduction of the volume and harmfulness of waste, recycling for material and energy reocovery, safe and environmentally friendly disposal, close and restore existing dumpsites and establish new municipal waste landfills.', 'In accordance with the &ldquo;National Plan for Waste Management for 2003 &ndash; 2012&rdquo;, several municipal waste management projects are being implemented, using funding from the Cohesion Fund (previously also Instrument for Structural Policies for pre-Accession resources). In various regions in Latvia, 11 waste management projects have been developed, providing comprehensive approach to waste management, including establishment of facilities forseparate collection of recyclable waste, installation of sorting, processing and disposal equipment and establishment of biogas collection systems in municipal waste landfills.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LV-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC; LV-Submission 2007', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(911, 'LV-TRA-01', NULL, '19', 'Improvement of the public transport system in Riga', 'To improve public transport systems', 'One of the objectives of Riga Traffic Concept is to provide city passengers a comfortable, safe and integrated public transport system identifying public transport as a priority in comparison with other transport vehicles in the downtown area streets of the city.At the same time, public transport should be competitive with passenger cars, which is possible with the adequate quality of service &ndash; speed, safety, regularity and comfort. Public transport should also be environmentally friendly. Development of the public transport network in the city will result in the 15-20% reduction of CO, CO2, nitric oxides and volatile hydrogen emissions in the central part of the city. Introduction of higher-class busses will also reduce NOx emissions.', '2000', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LV-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC; LV-Submission 2007', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(912, 'LV-TRA-02', NULL, '20', 'Development of cycling', 'To include cycling transport in the general transport system of Riga', 'Main objective of the State Program on the Development of Cycling is to include cycling transport in the general system of Riga transport and to convert cycling into a sustainable, equal to all other transports, safe and environmentally and human health friendly transport. With the development of cycling the number of people using motor transport to get to their workplaces in the centre of the city would go down resulting, respectively, in lower level of exhaust gas emissions created by road transport. It is forecasted that automobile-created exhaust gas emissions in Riga in the result of this measure will go down by 5-8%', '2001', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LV-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC; LV-Submission 2007', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(913, 'LV-TRA-06', NULL, '21', 'Creation of environmentally friendly transport system', 'Development of transport infrastructure, optimisation of transport types and flows', 'The issue of a long-term agreement on the priority of railroad for passenger transportation has become topical, although at the same time residents are not offered adequate transportation services with other modes of transport. To look for solutions to the problem, &ldquo;National Order Concept on Passenger Traffic over the Railroad&rdquo; was approved in 2005. In this document, the national policy for the following 10 years is defined to secure the implementation of the objectives set in the &ldquo;Strategy for Public Transport Development, 2005&ndash;2014&rdquo;.<br />Optimisation of the traffic flow in cities has been approved as one of the measures eligible to receive financing from the EU Cohesion Fund (according to the Objective 1 Programme of the &ldquo;Development Plan (Single Programming Document) for Latvia, 2004&ndash;2006&rdquo;).', '2001', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LV-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC; LV-Submission 2007', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(914, 'LV-TRA-07', NULL, '22', 'Optimisation of the traffic flow in cities', 'To improve the penetrability of streets, provide a confortable, safe and competitive public transport system', 'The number of vehicles in Latvia is increasing rapidly &ndash; in the previous ten years the number of vehicles on average increased by 4&ndash;6% annually; as a result the pollution caused by transportation is also increasing. Therefore the issue of a long-term agreement on the priority of railroad for passenger transportation has become topical, although at the same time residents are not offered adequate transportation services with other modes of transport. To look for solutions to the problem, &ldquo;National Order Concept on Passenger Traffic over the Railroad&rdquo; was approved in 2005. In this document, the national policy for the following 10 years is defined to secure the implementation of the objectives set in the &ldquo;Strategy for Public Transport Development, 2005&ndash;2014&rdquo;.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LV-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC; LV-Submission 2007', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(915, 'LV-CRS-800', NULL, '23', 'Implementation of the EU Emissions Trading Scheme', NULL, 'Latvia has transposed the provisions of this directive in the national legislation (Appendix 1) and in the period 2005 &ndash; 2007, 91 installations were participating in the emission allowance trading scheme. 13,706,012 emission allowances will be emitted, including 1,572,037 emission allowances for installations that would start operation after 2005.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LV-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC; LV-Submission 2007', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(916, 'LV-CRS-801', NULL, '24', 'Participation in Kyoto protocol flexible mechanisms', 'To facilitate global climate change mitigation efforts, attract investment for projects reducing GHG', 'AIJ are the pilot phase of JI projects being one of the means of implementation of energy sector development programs in Latvia. Until now, joint projects with Sweden, Germany and Netherlands have been implemented covering following areas:<br />&middot; Creation of new renewable energy sources using wind energy and biomass (16 projects);<br />&middot; Rational use of environmentally adapted fuel in small capacity co-generation plants (2 projects);<br />&middot; Raising efficiency in energy transmission by reconstructing centralised district heating networks (5 projects);<br />&middot; Improvement of the final energy consumption efficiency by heat insulation of public buildings and introducing heat consumption regulation (4 projects).', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LV-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC; LV-Submission 2007', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(917, 'LV-CRS-802', NULL, '25', 'Active participation in Joint Implementation projects', 'Attract financial resources for GHG emissions reducing investment projects', 'Due to considerable interest of investors to implement JI projects in Latvia, &ldquo;Concept on the Implementation of JI Projects under the Kyoto Protocol to the UN Framework Convention on Climate Change, 2002 &ndash; 2012&rdquo; and &ldquo;Strategy of JI Projects under the Kyoto Protocol to the United Nations Framework Convention on Climate Change for 2002 &ndash; 2012&rdquo; were adopted in 2002. The Cabinet of Ministers approved the option stating that Latvia would participate in JI actively &ndash; local specialists identify and prepare potential JI projects and announce tenders for investors for their implementation. The strategy sets up the institutional system for identifying of potential projects and attraction of investors, specifying the competence areas in JI process management. Implementation of the strategy will initiate the development of the technical, financial and administrative management system and preparation of project portfolio. JI commission approves projects, assigning them JI status and decide about contract signing between foreign partners, Latvian partners and Latvian government as well.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LV-2008 Submission under Decision 280/2004/EC; LV-Submission 2007', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
