(1044, 'PL-TRA-06', NULL, '21', 'Improvement of vehicle energy effectiveness, including measures connected with vehicle construction', 'reduction in fuel consumption', 'as a result of technological progress declared by the producers of passenger cars and decisions of car buyers the consumption of fuels dropped markedly and thus CO2 emissions decreased. For instance, a unit emission of CO2 from passenger cars decreased from the level of 165 g/km<br />in 2001 to 154 g/km in 2004. Introduction of noise limitations at airports in air transport is connected with the use of aircrafts with engines with technologically lowest possible fuel consumption,', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'PL-NC4, p.49, PL Submission 07', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1045, 'PL-TRA-07', NULL, '22', 'Technical measures connected with vehicle construction', 'reduction in fuel consumption', 'there is an on-going progress in the improvement of fuel consumption efficiency in new passenger cars, trucks, buses, rail vehicles and aircrafts put into service in Poland,', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'PL-NC4, p.49, PL Submission 07', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1046, 'PL-TRA-08', NULL, '23', 'Introduction of restrictions in speed rates in towns', 'reduction in fuel consumption', 'a legislative obligation has been introduced on speed<br />limits in urban built-up areas during daytime up to 50 km/h<br />(and up to 60 km/h during the hours between 23.00 and<br />5.00)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'PL-NC4, p.49, PL Submission 07', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1047, 'PL-TRA-09', NULL, '24', 'Improvement of the infrastructure for cyclists and pedestrians', 'promoting bicycles as a means of transport and building bicycle routes.', 'activities that were undertaken focused on promoting bicycles as a means of transport and on building bicycle routes. Promotion of bicycle transport is favoured by the setting or building of bicycle paths and pedestrian pathways for the every-day local and tourist transport, both in the urbanised areas and beyond them. In 2003 the total area of pavements and bicycle routes in Poland for roads within the administrative<br />limits of towns amounted to 79,910 thousand m2, and for roads outside the administrative limits of towns 16,399 thousand m2. Actions of non-governmental organisations promoting bicycle use as a means of transport, as well as attractive bicycle prices, which encourage their purchasing and use play a significant role in the popularisation of bicycles. Furthermore, the idea of multimodal transport (bicycle and collective means of transport) is being implemented by creating bicycle parking places close to places where modes of transport are changed and by providing<br />possibilities for transporting bicycles by collective transportation means.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'PL-NC4, p.49, PL Submission 07', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
