(1315, 'GR-TRA-300', NULL, '47', 'CNG Buses', 'Promotion of natural gas in road transport', 'Small quantities of natural gas (roughly 13 ktoe in 2005) are consumed in the transport sector, where 416 natural gas moving buses have already been placed in the public transportation system of Athens. The measure progresses satisfactory concerning the targets that had been placed within the 2nd National Climate Change Program.<br />National targer for 2010: 555 CNG buses', '2000', NULL, '7', NULL, '7', NULL, '12', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Number of CNG buses', NULL, 'Climate Change - Emissions Projections Policies And Measures, May 2008 (Greece&#39;s submission under Decision 280/2004/EC), p.11,17,23', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1316, 'GR-CRS-800', NULL, '48', 'EU Emission trading', 'CO2 reduction', 'In Greece, the trading system for the period 2008-2012 comprises 140 industrial installations. An allowance reserve is also created which is intended to cover possible unknown new entrants in the period. According to the 2nd National Allocation Plan (NAP), the allowances of<br />CO2 emissions that were allocated to installations included in the EU-ETS were fixed to 341.547.710 t CO2, which requires a considerable decrease of emissions by the enterprises that participate in the system comparing to the with measures projections scenario presented in 4th National Communication.', '2005', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Climate Change - Emissions Projections Policies And Measures, May 2008 (Greece&#39;s submission under Decision 280/2004/EC), p.7f', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1317, 'GR-CRS-801', NULL, '49', 'Operational Programme Competitiveness (OPC)', 'Promotion of interventions that may lead to GHG emissions reduction.', 'The OPC includes 9 priority sectors with 41 measures, which in turn comprise a total of 134 actions. These actions are designed to implement the corresponding policies in the Programme&rsquo;s areas of intervention. A central feature of the Operational Programme is to support entrepreneurship in such areas as new technologies, the liberalized energy markets, environment, tourism but also to fund actions for business modernization, especially addressed to small and medium-sized enterprises engaged in manufacturing-processing, tourism and the service sectors. Under the OPC, projects are promoted projects to upgrade industrial regions, the national quality assurance system, energy infrastructures and regional structures providing information, consultation, education and management support to businesses.', '2000', '2006', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Climate Change - Emissions Projections Policies And Measures, May 2008 (Greece&#39;s submission under Decision 280/2004/EC), p.16', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1318, 'GR-AGR-01', NULL, '50', 'Manure management systems', 'Optimization of manure management systems', 'This measure promotes systems for the &ldquo;liquid treatment&rdquo; of animal manure in the swine and dairy cattle farms. As far as the swine units, according to the Ministry of Rural Development and Food, the system of &ldquo;liquid treatment&rdquo; of manure is already used in the 100% of the units, and<br />thus only improvements of these systems could be performed, such as the cover of tanks.<br />National target for 2010: 95% of produced animal waste to be processed in wastewater treatment systems.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '67', NULL, '64', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Percentage of produced animal waste that is processed in<br />wastewater treatment systems.', NULL, 'Climate Change - Emissions Projections Policies And Measures, May 2008 (Greece&#39;s submission under Decision 280/2004/EC), p.14,21,26', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1319, 'GR-AGR-02', NULL, '51', 'Organic farming', 'Promotion of organic farming', 'This measure deals with the restriction of nitrogen fertilizers use in combination with the promotion of organic farming. According to the Ministry of Rural Development and Food records, significant increase of organic farming was noted in the last years. Organic farming in Greece has increased from the 1.4% of total of cultivated land in 2004 to 2.71 in 2005 and 3.14% in 2006. This increase is mainly attributed to the 100 % increasing of subsidies.<br />National target for 2010: 190.000 Ha organic farming area', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '67', NULL, '88', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Percentage of cultivated area with organic farming<br />Organic farming area (&Eta;a)', NULL, 'Climate Change - Emissions Projections Policies And Measures, May 2008 (Greece&#39;s submission under Decision 280/2004/EC), p.14,21,26', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1320, 'GR-LUC-01', NULL, '52', 'CO2 removals', 'CO2 reduction', 'The 2nd National Climate Change Program (2000-2010) does not determine additional measures of removals through sinks (measures in the sector of Land Use, Land Use Change and Forestry). However, in recognition of the role of forests in addressing the greenhouse effect, the sustainable management of the Greek forests was strengthened through financing of forest management practices as well as measures for the prevention and control of forest fires.<br />Also, in the frame of the program Agricultural Land Forestation of the Ministry of Rural Development and Food, which targets the non-public sector, projects for agricultural lands forestation and improvement of existing forest lands have been financed. On the basis of the Regulation 2080/92,<br />35,840 ha of agricultural lands were forested during the period 1994-2001 while 4,835 ha were forested in the years 2002 and 2003 based on the Regulation 1257/99.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '-700', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Climate Change - Emissions Projections Policies And Measures, May 2008 (Greece&#39;s submission under Decision 280/2004/EC), p.15', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
